description:
* Experience in a similar role as a Technical Account Manager, Consultant, Solutions Architect, Platform Engineer, Systems Engineer, Cloud Architect etc.
* Understand operational parameters and troubleshooting for 2 or more of the following: Compute, Storage, Networking, CDN, Databases, DevOps, Big Data and Analytics, Security, Applications Development
* Internal enterprise or external customer-facing experience with the ability to clearly articulate to small and large audiences
* Ability to juggle tasks and projects in a fast-paced environment
* Customer obsessed

An AWS Technical Account Manager is a trusted advisor and cloud operations architect for our Enterprise Support customers. As a trusted advisor you’ll have a direct impact in helping our customers gain the most value from cloud technology. You’ll craft and execute strategies to drive our customers’ adoption and use of AWS services. You will provide advocacy and strategic technical guidance to help plan and build solutions using best practices, and proactively keep your customers’ AWS environments operationally healthy. The close relationships developed with your customers will allow you to understand their business/operational needs and technical challenges, and help them achieve the greatest value from AWS.

Our Technical Account Managers partner with some of the most iconic businesses in the country. These range from rising startups building their business from scratch through to large enterprises going through significant transformation. You’ll provide advice on architecture, support strategy, project, and launch planning as well as ongoing operational issues.

AWS Sales, Marketing, and Global Services (SMGS) is responsible for driving revenue, adoption, and growth from the largest and fastest growing small- and mid-market accounts to enterprise-level customers including public sector.

The AWS Global Support team interacts with leading companies and believes that world-class support is critical to customer success. AWS Support also partners with a global list of customers that are building mission-critical applications on top of AWS services.

Key job responsibilities
* You’ll build solutions, provide technical guidance and advocate for the customer
* Ensure AWS environments remain operationally healthy whilst reducing cost and complexity
* Develop trusting relationships with customers, understanding their business needs and technical challenges
* Using your technical acumen and customer obsession, you’ll drive technical discussions regarding incidents, trade-offs, and risk management
* Consult with a range of partners from developers through to C-suite executives
* Collaborate with AWS Solutions Architects, Business Developers, Professional Services Consultants, and Sales Account Managers
* With a bias for action, you'll proactively find opportunities for customers to gain additional value from AWS
* Solve a variety of problems across different customers as they migrate their workloads to the cloud
* Uplift customer capabilities by running workshops and other enablement sessions.

As we continue to rapidly expand in EMEA, you’ll have plenty of opportunities to develop your technical, consulting and leadership skills. You’ll work with talented cloud technologists whilst expanding your knowledge of AWS products. You’ll also have the chance to receive mentor-ship and gain AWS certifications.

Do you want to be part of history and transform businesses through cloud computing adoption? We would love to hear from you.

About the team
About AWS
Diverse Experiences
AWS values diverse experiences. Even if you do not meet all of the qualifications and skills listed in the job description, we encourage candidates to apply. If your career is just starting, hasn’t followed a traditional path, or includes alternative experiences, don’t let it stop you from applying.

Why AWS?
Amazon Web Services (AWS) is the world’s most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. We pioneered cloud computing and never stopped innovating — that’s why customers from the most successful startups to Global 500 companies trust our robust suite of products and services to power their businesses.

Inclusive Team Culture
Here at AWS, it’s in our nature to learn and be curious. Our employee-led affinity groups foster a culture of inclusion that empower us to be proud of our differences. Ongoing events and learning experiences, including our Conversations on Race and Ethnicity (CORE) and AmazeCon (gender diversity) conferences, inspire us to never stop embracing our uniqueness.

Mentorship & Career Growth
We’re continuously raising our performance bar as we strive to become Earth’s Best Employer. That’s why you’ll find endless knowledge-sharing, mentorship and other career-advancing resources here to help you develop into a better-rounded professional.

Work/Life Balance
We value work-life harmony. Achieving success at work should never come at the expense of sacrifices at home, which is why we strive for flexibility as part of our working culture. When we feel supported in the workplace and at home, there’s nothing we can’t achieve in the cloud.

* Professional experience with cloud offerings such as AWS, Azure, Google Cloud Platform etc.
* Programming or scripting skills with a combination of Java, Python Perl, Ruby, C#, and/or PHP a plus but not a requirement
* Previous experience as a Software Engineer, Developer, DevOps Engineer etc.
* Understanding of DevOps practices and tools including Continuous Integration / Deployment, Puppet, Docker, Kubernetes, Chef is a plus

Amazon is an equal opportunities employer. We believe passionately that employing a diverse workforce is central to our success. We make recruiting decisions based on your experience and skills. We value your passion to discover, invent, simplify and build. Protecting your privacy and the security of your data is a longstanding top priority for Amazon. Please consult our Privacy Notice (https://www.amazon.jobs/en/privacy_page) to know more about how we collect, use and transfer the personal data of our candidates.

Our inclusive culture empowers Amazonians to deliver the best results for our customers. If you have a disability and need a workplace accommodation or adjustment during the application and hiring process, including support for the interview or onboarding process, please visit https://amazon.jobs/content/en/how-we-hire/accommodations for more information. If the country/region you’re applying in isn’t listed, please contact your Recruiting Partner.

description:
Grow with us

About this opportunity

Cloud RAN PEU Engineering Environment & Services unit is now looking for a skilled and motivated CICD DevOps and Data Analytics Engineer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will play a substantial role in developing and maintaining continuous integration and continuous deployment (CICD) pipelines for data analytics projects, as well as supplying to the overall DevOps strategy.

As a CICD DevOps and Data Analytics Engineer, you will be responsible for designing and implementing CICD pipelines for data analytics solutions, as well as driving the DevOps strategy to enable flawless integration and deployment processes. You will collaborate with multi-functional teams to ensure the reliability, scalability, and performance of data analytics platforms and supply to the development of standard methodologies for the entire software development lifecycle.

Join our team and make a significant impact by championing Data analytics in our software development and delivery processes and delivering secure, resilient production systems and applications to our customers.

What you will do
• Design and implement CICD pipelines for data analytics projects, including data ingestion, processing, and visualization.
• Collaborate with data scientists, data engineers, and software developers to streamline deployment processes and ensure the integrity of data analytics platforms.
• Drive the DevOps strategy to automate infrastructure provisioning, configuration management, and supervising for data analytics environments.
• Implement best practices for version control, automated testing, and continuous integration to improve the efficiency and reliability of the development lifecycle.
• Supervise and optimize system performance, troubleshoot issues, and ensure the security and compliance of data analytics solutions.
• Continuous learning on the job and experimenting with new technology(s)

Join our Team

You will bring
• Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience in computer science, Engineering, or a related field.
• Validated experience in crafting and implementing CICD pipelines for data analytics platforms.
• Hands-on experience with DevOps practices and tools, such as GitLab, Jenkins, Kubernetes and Docker.
• Proficiency in scripting and programming languages, such as Python, Bash, or Go for automation and tool development.
• Familiarity with data analytics tools and frameworks, such as ElasticSearch, Grafana, Kibana, Flink, etc.
• Experience with cloud platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP) and infrastructure as code (e.g., Terraform, CloudFormation) is a plus.
• Excellent problem-solving skills and strong communication and collaboration skills with the ability to work optimally in multi-functional teams.

If you are passionate about data analytics, DevOps, and driving technological innovation, we would love to hear from you. Join us and be a member of a dynamic team crafting the future of data-driven decision-making!

description:
We're looking for an experienced developer to join us at Årsredovisning Online! Your opinions and ideas will be valued and celebrated here. Help us enhance our product, which supports Sweden's small businesses in generating their annual reports and tax returns digitally.

Who are we?

Årsredovisning Online came about in 2014 to help entrepreneurs with a simple and smart user-friendly solution for creating annual reports and tax returns. Since December 2020, we have been part of the Visma group. We take pride in being the top choice for small businesses in Sweden, offering the leading do-it-yourself solution for annual reports and tax returns. Årsredovisning Online can be used with all accounting services on the Swedish market. Today we are approximately 10 employees spread across four different locations.

We are a brand that is part of Visma Spcs - we are a small team within a larger context. A small business feel within a stable and well-renowned company.

About the role

We are in search of a motivated Ruby on Rails developer to help advance our application tailored for small business owners in Sweden. Our app is highly appreciated for its straightforwardness, leading to high customer satisfaction, which shapes our new development initiatives.

In 2024, more than 26,000 annual reports were submitted through our platform. You'll have the opportunity to work on a variety of projects with other talented developers, becoming an essential part of a small, passionate development team. Your role will involve daily activities such as solving problems, implementing new features, refining the system, troubleshooting, and optimizing performance.

We are looking for someone who thrives in a small, dynamic team setting, where open communication, idea sharing, and questioning the norm are encouraged. Still with the benefit of being part of the Visma group. You should be driven to improve your own skills and contribute to the technical community around you, aiming to build a positive and collaborative work environment. You possess the ability to link technical solutions to user needs and effectively discuss them with other developers.

Who are you?

You have a relevant IT education

You have a minimum of 3+ years of relevant work experience

You have good knowledge of English and Swedish, both written and spoken. As we are a diverse team with different backgrounds many meetings are being held in English

You have strong problem-solving skills and the ability to handle technical challenges

You are a skilled Ruby on Rails developer, have previous experience or curiosity about working with Ruby on Rails or having good experience with Java, Python or C#

You appreciate working on projects and with agile methods

You are efficient and quality is important to you

Proficiency in Git version control and CI/CD pipelines

Experience with test-driven development (TDD) and automated testing

Knowledge of front-end technologies (HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript)

What can we offer?

The chance to grow alongside enthusiastic colleagues in a small, entrepreneurially-minded SaaS company, while also enjoying the benefits of being part of Europe's largest tech group

A warm and inclusive work environment, with generous and helpful colleagues

A secure workplace with a focus on diversity and inclusion

A Visma-family with countless colleagues, who can share experiences and create valuable relationships across companies

A hybrid working day with a high degree of flexibility and independence

Health and well-being are close to our hearts. That's why we invest in activities that make you feel good, both mentally and physically

"My Competence Day" - dedicated days for your personal and professional development

Sounds exciting, right? We will be conducting interviews continuously. Tests and work samples may be part of the recruitment process. We would like to receive your application latest by January 5, 2025, via the link on our website. If you have any questions about the position, please feel free to contact mathias.eliasson@visma.com. We look forward to answering any questions you may have, and we look forward to hearing from you!
Department
Software Development
Roll
Software Developer
Platser
Stockholm, Malmö, Göteborg, Växjö
Distansarbete
Hybridarbete
Application deadline
5 januari 2025
Competencies
Ruby, Java

description:
Do you want to be part of digitizing the heavy construction industry and become a Team Lead of Cloud Developers and Testers in a dynamic project environment? At Leica Geosystems Technology, we are now looking for a Team Lead and Cloud Engineer for our Machine Control Division.

We are a global company of great diversity with employees working across the world, hence you will collaborate with colleagues in Poland, Denmark, Switzerland, and the USA, among others. We deliver state-of-the-art GPS guidance and automation technology for heavy construction machinery, and our ambition is to become the world market leader.

We are seeking an experienced Team Lead for our Development team in Liljeholmen, Stockholm, with a focus on rapid value delivery for our cloud solution.

Job Description – The Role and Responsibilities
Leica ConX is a revolutionary product that offers our customers the possibility to monitor work on heavy construction sites, plan work for entire projects, communicate in real time between machines, operators, and office staff. You will be part of our R&D Software department leading a team of seven developers and testers, creating and delivering a world-class, cloud-based system that integrates the Leica portfolio of surveying and machine control technologies. The product portfolio ecosystem spans many products, and the cloud is the central point for a variety of data both in transit and refined to produce valuable insights to our customers. ConX is the mission critical glue that connects many of Leica’s machine control solutions together.
Your responsibility will be twofold. You will dedicate some of your time to your team and ensure the right support, including but not limited to goalsetting, coaching and professional development. In addition, you will also support and develop our position through managing releases of our top-quality software and helping to ramp up our CI/CD practices and the team’s output for a mission critical product. You will work with a diverse cross-functional team to design, develop, operate, and maintain software that brings real-world value to our customers. You will have the support of your team in the Stockholm office and will work very closely with our sister team in Poland.

We are looking for an experienced Cloud Engineer with an open, honest and supportive approach to leadership. We are open to candidates at senior level; title and compensation will be commensurate with experience.

This is you
You have a formal relevant education, bachelor’s or higher degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field, or equivalent experience. You are honest, engaged, structured, analytical, and willing to be part of a great team where we value and use our differences to push the limit of quality and performance.

In addition, we expect you to have:
Experience with managing people.
5+ years of cloud development experience.
Self-sufficient, structured with an eye for details.
Fluent spoken and written English is a requirement for this position.
Strong understanding of software development life cycles (Agile/Scrum/SAFe).
Strong problem-solving skills and interpersonal skills.
Ability to manage and prioritize tasks effectively, working both independently and as part of a team.

Desired Skills:
AWS
Django
CI/CD pipelining
Python
C#
JavaScript front-end frameworks such as Vue, React, or Angular
Docker, Kubernetes, or other container technologies
GIS visualization
3D graphics
IoT
Knowledge of heavy construction machines or machine control applications.

We offer:
We offer an exciting position in a company with a complete supply chain. We believe that world leading products are developed by engaged people. For this reason, Leica Geosystems strives to create an atmosphere of innovation with a talented, motivated, and engaged workforce. The combination of the small office mentality with the power that comes with a strong global organization is inspiring and allows great career growth opportunities both horizontally and vertically. We enjoy social activities, offer beneficial healthcare insurance, pension provisions per collective agreement, as well as grants for wellness and parental leave. Our nice office is centrally located in Liljeholmen, Stockholm. We have embraced a flexible hybrid environment as we see value in having in-office interactions alongside the ability to choose to work where you feel the most productive. More information about Leica is available at www.leica-geosystems.com

INTERESTED?
Apply using the link and upload your CV and cover letter in English.
Interviews will be held as and when relevant candidates apply; candidates may be asked to carry out a case task during the interview process. All applications are treated as fully confidential.
For questions regarding the position, please get in touch with Martin Reich, R&D Software Manager (martin.reich@leica-geosystems.com ) or HR Business Partner, Casper Bang (casper.bang@leica-geosystems.com).
We kindly but firmly refrain from direct contact with staffing and recruitment companies as well as sellers of additional job advertisements.

ABOUT LEICA GEOSYSTEMS MACHINE CONTROL DIVISION
Leica Geosystems Machine Control is part of Hexagon’s Geosystems division. Leica Geosystems creates complete solutions for professionals in a diverse mix of industries, such as aerospace and defense, safety and security, construction, and manufacturing. With precise and accurate instruments, sophisticated software, and trusted services, Leica Geosystems delivers value every day to those shaping the future of our world. In Machine Control Division we are offering simplified and connected machine control solutions for increasing productivity, efficiency and safety in heavy construction operations.
Hexagon is the global leader in digital reality solutions, combining sensor, software and autonomous technologies. Our solutions free our customers to harness the rapidly increasing amounts of data, putting it to work to boost efficiency, productivity, quality and safety across industrial, manufacturing, infrastructure, public sector and mobility applications. Hexagon (Nasdaq Stockholm: HEXA B) has approximately 24,000 employees in 50 countries and net sales of approximately 5.2bn EUR.

description:
Swedium Global is the growing System Engineering and Solution Company, offers services like Semiconductor Engineering R&D Services, Embedded Systems Development, Custom Application Software Development, Web and Cloud Application Development, Testing Services, Consultancy and Outsourcing services to our clients across the globe for an onsite and offshore business model. Swedium Global is having presence in Sweden, Finland, Poland, Czech Republic and in India.

Location : Gothenburg, Sweden

Expected Start Date : ASAP

Job Role : Senior Test Engineer

*Here's what we want you to do: *

We are a product company where you as a Test Engineer will play a vital role in shaping our products from concept to completion. We set the bar high for user-friendliness and feature excellence, which makes your collaboration with customers, developers, and testers even more essential. Your contributions together with the team will help us make a real diYerence in the lives of our customers.

*Key Responsibilities: *
* Analyze and review requirements
* Innovate and craft new test cases for both existing and emerging features
* Conduct exploratory testing, whether it's on the bench or out in the field in an

excavator, boat, or truck
* Develop automated test scripts tailored to various testing environments
* Except from executing manual and exploratory tests, we invite you to enhance

our testing strategies and processes.

*Meritorious qualifications: *
* Proficiency in Python
* Competence in Robot Framework
* Wi-Fi Communication Skills
* Proficiency in CAN communication

*Is this you? *

We are searching for Test Engineers who hold a degree in software or electronics and are genuinely enthusiastic about testing. You have a natural ability to empathize with end-users, visualizing how our products and features impact their lives.
While it's a bonus if you come with some years of experience, we also value a diversity of perspectives and backgrounds. We encourage a culture of open communication, creativity, and collaboration. Furthermore, you are proficient in communicating effectively in English.

You can reach out to us at Pratik.pandey@swediumglobal.com or deepthi.meka@swediumglobal.com or hr@swediumglobal.com

Job Type: Full-time

Work Location: Hybrid remote in Kista

description:
Are you enthusiastic about driving the green transition in a dynamic, fast-paced environment? Ingrid Capacity is an energy tech company committed to tackling the toughest challenges in fossil-free energy. We develop flexible assets like large-scale energy solutions to balance surplus and shortages, stabilize the grid, and boost renewable energy adoption efficiently. Join us to be part of this impactful journey. Today, Ingrid Capacity is in a rapid growth phase with a historic expansion of energy storage in Sweden, while also expanding internationally. We are in the final phase of construction of around 200 MW and will soon enter a new phase of construction of another 200 MW, with a total development pipeline of over 6 GW across Europe and in parallel becoming a leading energy software player.

About the team
Software and smart solutions is a cornerstone of solving the bottlenecks in the power system and Ingrid Capacity’s company strategy. Our Ingrid Technology teams builds and maintains software for grid analyses and simulations, power trading and optimization algorithms to maximize efficiency within the grid. We also focus on creating a data-driven culture by building data pipelines and a Business Intelligence layer to provide stakeholders with actionable insights. Our team plays a key role in driving strategic decision-making and overall company success, and we work closely together to ensure a smooth transition of ideas from concept to reality. At Ingrid Tech, we foster a collaborative and inclusive environment where everyone’s voice is valued. We believe in empowering our team members to make a real impact and being part of shaping the energy system of the future.

About the Role:
We are on the lookout for a Platform Engineer, who will be at the forefront of designing and managing cloud infrastructure that drive innovation and efficiency for the Ingrid Tech team. This role involves developing cloud strategies, ensuring the security and efficiency of cloud systems, and collaborating with the rest of the Ingrid Tech team to deliver integrated solutions. You will have the opportunity to lead impactful cloud projects that align with our commitment to be part of shaping the energy system of the future. Explore and utilize a diverse range of tools to maximize developer experience across our data solutions, machine-learning capabilities, and software suite.

Key responsibilities:

Design Cloud Solutions that can scale. Create scalable, secure, and cost-efficient GCP architectures tailored to business needs.
Manage IaC with Terraform configurations for automated infrastructure provisioning and updates.
Ensure Security by implementing robust IAM policies, encryption, and compliance standards for secure cloud environments.
Streamline Development with efficient CI/CD pipelines to empower faster and smoother software delivery.
Observe and monitor resource usage to take action to improve performance and cost-efficiency across a diverse system.
Collaborate & Improve: Work with teams to align cloud solutions with goals while staying updated with trends and advancements in cloud, observability, and DevOps.

Key Qualifications

Cloud experience with a strong knowledge of Google Cloud Platform or similar (AWS, Azure).
Cloud storage and databases with an understanding of cloud storage and databases, e.g., S3 buckets, BigQuery, PostgreSQL.
DevOps concepts such as infrastructure as code (Terraform), containerization (Docker, Kubeflow), CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions).
Security embedded in the workflow, always considering security implications and risk-mitigation. Experience with authorization and IAM policies would be meritable but not required.
Solid coder with proficiency in Python and JavaScript.
Expertise in monitoring with tools like Cloud Logging, Prometheus, ElasticSearch, or similar.
MLOps experience with tools like Vertex AI, which is meritable but not required.
Curiosity and innovation with a strong interest in exploring and evaluating the latest innovations.

Your personal skills

In addition to your qualifications we believe that below skills will make you a star in the Ingrid Tech team:

Solution-oriented with ability to focus on finding practical solutions balancing speed and technical debt effectively.
Curious and a natural inclination to explore new technologies, methodologies, and approaches, driving continuous improvement and actively seeks growth opportunities and takes initiative in dynamic settings.
Comfortable in fast-paced start-up environment and willingness to test out ideas, fail fast and take on new tasks when relevant.

What We Offer
At Ingrid Capacity, we are more than employees -we are pioneers and visionaries leading the global energy transition. Our company fosters a culture of trust, growth, and continuous learning, with a commitment to innovation and bold ideas. We prioritize well-being, regularly hosting social activities and group training, creating an environment where our team thrives.

Application
Sounds like a match? Apply today! We review applications on an ongoing basis and look forward to finding the perfect fit. We are looking for people with diverse levels of experience, and we encourage you to apply if you feel you can contribute to our great team, even if you don't meet all the listed requirements.

/Team Ingrid Capacity

We are on the lookout for a Platform Engineer, who will be at the forefront of designing and managing cloud infrastructure that drive innovation and efficiency for the Ingrid Tech team. This role involves developing cloud strategies, ensuring the security and efficiency of cloud systems, and collaborating with the rest of the Ingrid Tech team to deliver integrated solutions. You will have the opportunity to lead impactful cloud projects that align with our commitment to be part of shaping the energy system of the future. Explore and utilize a diverse range of tools to maximize developer experience across our data solutions, machine-learning capabilities, and software suite.

Key responsibilities:

  • Design Cloud Solutions that can scale. Create scalable, secure, and cost-efficient GCP architectures tailored to business needs.
  • Manage IaC with Terraform configurations for automated infrastructure provisioning and updates.
  • Ensure Security by implementing robust IAM policies, encryption, and compliance standards for secure cloud environments.
  • Streamline Development with efficient CI/CD pipelines to empower faster and smoother software delivery.
  • Observe and monitor resource usage to take action to improve performance and cost-efficiency across a diverse system.
  • Collaborate & Improve: Work with teams to align cloud solutions with goals while staying updated with trends and advancements in cloud, observability, and DevOps.

Key Qualifications

  • Cloud experience with a strong knowledge of Google Cloud Platform or similar (AWS, Azure).
  • Cloud storage and databases with an understanding of cloud storage and databases, e.g., S3 buckets, BigQuery, PostgreSQL.
  • DevOps concepts such as infrastructure as code (Terraform), containerization (Docker, Kubeflow), CI/CD pipelines (GitHub Actions).
  • Security embedded in the workflow, always considering security implications and risk-mitigation. Experience with authorization and IAM policies would be meritable but not required.
  • Solid coder with proficiency in Python and JavaScript.
    Expertise in monitoring with tools like Cloud Logging, Prometheus, ElasticSearch, or similar.
  • MLOps experience with tools like Vertex AI, which is meritable but not required.
  • Curiosity and innovation with a strong interest in exploring and evaluating the latest innovations.

Your personal skills

In addition to your qualifications we believe that below skills will make you a star in the Ingrid Tech team:

  • Solution-oriented with ability to focus on finding practical solutions balancing speed and technical debt effectively.
  • Curious and a natural inclination to explore new technologies, methodologies, and approaches, driving continuous improvement and actively seeks growth opportunities and takes initiative in dynamic settings.
  • Comfortable in fast-paced start-up environment and willingness to test out ideas, fail fast and take on new tasks when relevant.

What We Offer
At Ingrid Capacity, we are more than employees -we are pioneers and visionaries leading the global energy transition. Our company fosters a culture of trust, growth, and continuous learning, with a commitment to innovation and bold ideas. We prioritize well-being, regularly hosting social activities and group training, creating an environment where our team thrives.

Application
Sounds like a match? Apply today! We review applications on an ongoing basis and look forward to finding the perfect fit. We are looking for people with diverse levels of experience, and we encourage you to apply if you feel you can contribute to our great team, even if you don't meet all the listed requirements.

/Team Ingrid Capacity

description:
Flightradar24 is one of the most successful growth-stage tech companies in Stockholm. Each day, more than 4 million aviation enthusiasts use our app or website, and we have many of the biggest names in aviation as business customers.

The position requires that you are able to work from our office in Stockholm, Sweden. Relocation is not offered for this role.

Flightradar24 is looking for a skilled Test Automation Engineer to join our team. The successful candidate will be responsible for developing and implementing automated test cases for our products . The candidate must have experience working with automation of APIs (REST and gRPC), Backend Testing and the ability to work with cross-platform teams to set up CI/CD pipelines. The candidate must also be able to work independently and identify opportunities for automated testing improvements across teams.

What you’ll do
Test Automation & Framework Development:
Design, develop, and maintain scalable automated test frameworks.
Implement robust automated scripts for functional and regression testing of APIs and Webservices.
API Automation & Performance Testing:
Create and execute test strategies, plans, and cases to ensure high-quality releases of APIs.
Conduct performance and load tests, analyze results, and communicate findings effectively.
Continuous Integration & Delivery:
Integrate automated tests into the CI/CD pipeline to support rapid, reliable releases.
Collaborate with teams to optimize testing workflows and maintain high code quality.
Collaboration & Communication:
Partner closely with developers, product managers, and QA peers to define testing requirements.
Working closely with backend teams.
Communicate test results, defects, and quality metrics to both technical and non-technical audiences.
Participate in code reviews, design discussions, and agile ceremonies.
Who you are
Skilled in building and maintaining API test automation frameworks (e.g.,Karate, REST Assured, Pytest, etc..)
Experienced with performance testing tools (e.g., JMeter, Gatling)
Knowledgeable in CI/CD tools (e.g., Jenkins, GitHub Actions, GitLab CI, Azure DevOps)
Proficient in at least one programming language (e.g., Java, Python, JavaScript)
Excellent communicator, adept at conveying complex ideas to diverse audiences
Strong collaborator who thrives in cross-functional, distributed team environments
Detail-oriented problem solver with a proactive approach
About Flightradar24

With over 4 million daily users, Flightradar24 is the world’s most popular flight tracking service. Our app regularly tops the App Store and Google Play Travel charts. We also offer a wide range of commercial services, and our customers include many of the biggest names in aviation.

We're constantly adding new services and improving existing products. To help us meet those challenges, we're looking for creative, collaborative, and tech-savvy applicants to join us.

Benefits of working at Flightradar24 include:

Opportunity to impact a service with millions of end users from all around the world
Flexible and social work environment with free beverages, fruit, and snacks
Modern office in the heart of beautiful downtown Stockholm, Sweden
Being part of a diverse team with +30 nationalities and 6 continents represented with English being our main language

description:
We are seeking a Process System Engineer with a strong background in process engineering and fluid system design, coupled with expertise in advanced working fluids and system optimization. Experience in multiphase operations, heating/cooling processes, and hydraulic network design is highly desirable. This role focuses on designing, analyzing, and optimizing process systems to meet stringent safety and performance standards. The successful candidate will collaborate with cross-disciplinary teams to deliver innovative solutions for cutting-edge nuclear energy systems.

What we do at Blykalla

At Blykalla, we’re transforming the future of nuclear power by developing innovative Small Modular Reactors (SMRs). Our mission is to create a new generation of nuclear energy systems that are safer, more efficient, and environmentally friendly. As Sweden’s only developer of SMRs, we’re at the forefront of a groundbreaking industry.

What you’ll get to do

Design and analyze fluid systems, including heat exchangers (HEX), pumps, hydraulic networks, and separation systems.

Develop process flow diagrams (PFDs), piping and instrumentation diagrams (P&IDs), and detailed system specifications.

Perform engineering calculations for multiphase operations, pressure drop, and thermal performance.

Define and implement control philosophies, collaborating with automation teams to ensure operability.

Evaluate advanced working fluids, focusing on safety and efficiency.

Participate in technical reviews, risk assessments, and design optimizations.

Provide technical input for equipment specifications and supplier selection.

Support commissioning, startup, and performance testing activities.

Develop and maintain technical documentation, including design reviews and system manuals

Who you are

You will be part of a highly skilled team with a can-do attitude. We value personnel chemistry and strive to create a workplace where you enjoy coming to. There are however a few things that we think will help you to succeed in this role, these are:

A Master’s degree in Chemical Engineering, Nuclear Engineering, Process Engineering, Mechanical Engineering, or a related field.

Proven experience in process engineering, including the design and optimization of HEX, pumps, and separation systems.

Knowledge of control philosophies and instrumentation for process systems.

Proficiency with process engineering tools such as ASPEN, Flownex, Flomaster, Thermoflow, or Apros.

Excellent communication and teamwork abilities.

Strong problem-solving skills and adaptability to dynamic projects.

Fluent in English, both spoken and written (Swedish is a plus).

Meritorious skills:
The following skills are not required but will be considered an advantage:

Experience with lead or other advanced coolants.

Familiarity with nuclear waste system design.

Programming skills in Python, C++, or MatLab.

Field experience in commissioning or startup of industrial plants.

Location
This position is for our office in Stockholm.

So, what do you think?

Joining our team means being part of a supportive and innovative environment where your ideas are valued and your expertise is recognized. You will have the opportunity to work with industry leaders and contribute to the safe and sustainable use of nuclear power.

Note: We encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds and are an equal-opportunity employer.

Due to GDPR, we do not accept applications over email.

We are not open to external help from recruitment agencies.

description:
Odevo is a group of exciting brands with a shared vision of challenging the status quo in the property management industry. We're committed to revolutionizing the industry with innovative software solutions that make managing properties easier, more efficient, and more effective. Our cloud-based platform is unique, and we have proven ourselves as a leading and innovative player in a brief time. Our global product development department acts as a SaaS supplier to all the companies in the Odevo group and several other players in the industry. Together, we will continue to challenge and change this industry. To continue our ambitious growth journey, we seek more great people to join us to build market-leading property management software products. Are you one of them?

About the role

In this role, you’ll be an integral part of our mission to deliver high-quality software products. Working in a collaborative, agile environment, you’ll design, develop, and execute automated tests that ensure our products meet the highest standards. Your work will directly contribute to creating a culture of continuous improvement and excellence, helping us push boundaries in the property management technology space.

Your Key Responsibilities Will Include
Designing and developing automated test frameworks and scripts to ensure robust software quality.
Implementing performance and load testing strategies to validate application scalability.
Integrating automated tests into CI/CD pipelines and monitoring their performance.
Collaborating with developers to identify test coverage needs and troubleshoot issues.
Analyzing test results to provide insights into product readiness and quality.
Leading cross-team quality initiatives and mentoring team members in test automation best practices.
Who You Are

You are a proactive problem solver with a passion for quality and innovation. With a detail-oriented mindset and a collaborative approach, you thrive in an agile, fast-paced environment where teamwork is key. You take pride in delivering excellent results and are eager to drive quality at every stage of development. Your strong communication skills enable you to work effectively with diverse teams, and your ability to adapt and learn ensures you stay ahead in the field. You are fluent in Swedish and English.

Experience
At least 5 years of experience in test automation or non-functional testing.
Proficiency in programming languages such as Java, Python, C#, or JavaScript.
Hands-on experience with test automation tools (e.g., Playwright, Cypress, Appium).
A solid understanding of performance testing, CI/CD pipelines, and cloud platforms like AWS or Azure.
Familiarity with Linux/Unix, shell scripting, and DevOps practices.
What We Offer
Remote friendly - you'll be part of a team that values collaboration and communication, regardless of location.
Professional growth - to work with the most talented developers in the industry.
Modern technology - we invest in the latest technologies and tools and encourage our team members to share their ideas and take ownership of their work.
Innovation - to work on exciting projects that push the boundaries of our industry and make a real impact.
Commitment to quality - a dynamic and forward-thinking company that values profitable and long-term product development.
Location

This role offers a hybrid work setup, blending the flexibility of remote work with access to collaborative office spaces. Our office is on the top floor in the newly built Sthlm 04, which offers stunning views over Stockholm.

Excited?

Join Odevo’s journey toward excellence! If this sounds like your next career move, we’d love to hear from you.

Why we formed Odevo
About Odevo
Our Software

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Front End Web Developer

Location: Västerås, Västmanlands län, Sweden

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Front End Web Developer

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

VIPAS AB is seeking a skilled Senior Front-End Developer to join our team and lead the development of next-generation HMI solutions for Substation Power Quality Applications. In this role, you will collaborate with design teams to create, test, and implement innovative HMI systems within MicroSCADA X. Your expertise in front-end web development, UX design, and power systems will be crucial as you work in an agile environment to deliver high-quality solutions for critical infrastructure projects.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop next-generation HMI solutions for Power Quality (PQ) Control and Protection Systems at the substation level.
Collaborate with the UX/UI conceptual design team to create innovative Substation HMI solutions in MicroSCADA X.
Test, debug, and optimize Substation HMI solutions to ensure peak performance.
Train and support teams in implementing HMI solutions for delivery projects.
Contribute to agile teams by developing new features and applications to enhance service offerings.
Engage with diverse stakeholders to understand requirements and ensure successful project outcomes.
Uphold core values of safety and integrity through accountability and fostering a supportive team environment.

Requirements:

Education: A university degree in a relevant technical field.
Experience:
Proven experience as a Web/HMI Front-End Developer.
Hands-on experience with HTML/XML markup languages.
Proficiency in JavaScript and HTML5.
Experience with HMI conceptual design, especially within Substation and/or Power Systems.
Familiarity with testing and debugging HMI solutions.
Comprehensive understanding of the full web development process (design, development, deployment).
Experience with MicroSCADA X HMI development and SCIL programming is a strong advantage.
Skills:
Excellent problem-solving skills and proactive initiative.
Demonstrated ability to work in agile environments (SCRUM, lean methodologies).
Strong collaboration skills, with a focus on continuous improvement and delivering results.
Fluent in English

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at sandhya@vipas.se

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Lead Logistics Developer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. Job Description:

We are looking for a Logistic Developer to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for setting up and improving external logistics processes for Product Builds and Complete Vehicle Sweden. The goal is to ensure smooth prototype parts logistics as well as inbound and outbound logistics connected to Product Builds in Sweden. You will take charge of an efficient and effective logistics day-to-day operation.

To thrive in this role, we believe you are innovative, pragmatic, and creative, with a positive spirit and a curious, entrepreneurial mindset. Recognized for your expertise, you are a forward-thinker who sees opportunities where others see risks. Valued by your peers, you enjoy connecting with a wide network, fostering win-win solutions, and building strong relationships.

You have a strong ability to turn ideas into action in a structured and organized manner. You are approachable and equally comfortable working hands-on as you are leading strategic discussions. If our entrepreneurial spirit, adaptability, and customer-focused mindset ignite your passion, we might be a great match

Key Responsibilities:

In cooperation with your colleagues identify, maintain, improve and develop the routines and processes for external logistics.
Drive continuous improvements for the logistic process, always with people in focus.

Some of the areas (but not limited to) in focus:

Improve logistic supply chain when it comes to cost, quality and efficiency.
Secure storage needs for products at the warehouse.
Develop cost models for business.

Requirements:

Solid knowledge of logistics processes and value-chains. Knowledge in EV (Electrical Vehicle) battery and Automotive logistics is appreciated but not a must.
Successful experiences in executing logistics processes, logistics operations.
Successful experiences of cross-functional work.
Knowledge in setting ways of working in cross-functional organizations.
Degree in supply-chain/logistics, project management, engineering, business or similar.
Fluent in English and Swedish, written and spoken.
Driver’s license for car will be needed.

You will be located in Lundby Area, Göteborg, Sweden.

descriptionHTML:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Lead Logistics Developer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

We are looking for a Logistic Developer to join our team. In this role, you will be responsible for setting up and improving external logistics processes for Product Builds and Complete Vehicle Sweden. The goal is to ensure smooth prototype parts logistics as well as inbound and outbound logistics connected to Product Builds in Sweden. You will take charge of an efficient and effective logistics day-to-day operation.

To thrive in this role, we believe you are innovative, pragmatic, and creative, with a positive spirit and a curious, entrepreneurial mindset. Recognized for your expertise, you are a forward-thinker who sees opportunities where others see risks. Valued by your peers, you enjoy connecting with a wide network, fostering win-win solutions, and building strong relationships.

You have a strong ability to turn ideas into action in a structured and organized manner. You are approachable and equally comfortable working hands-on as you are leading strategic discussions. If our entrepreneurial spirit, adaptability, and customer-focused mindset ignite your passion, we might be a great match

Key Responsibilities:

  • In cooperation with your colleagues identify, maintain, improve and develop the routines and processes for external logistics.
  • Drive continuous improvements for the logistic process, always with people in focus.

Some of the areas (but not limited to) in focus:

  • Improve logistic supply chain when it comes to cost, quality and efficiency.
  • Secure storage needs for products at the warehouse.
  • Develop cost models for business.

Requirements:


  • Solid knowledge of logistics processes and value-chains. Knowledge in EV (Electrical Vehicle) battery and Automotive logistics is appreciated but not a must.
  • Successful experiences in executing logistics processes, logistics operations.
  • Successful experiences of cross-functional work.
  • Knowledge in setting ways of working in cross-functional organizations.
  • Degree in supply-chain/logistics, project management, engineering, business or similar.
  • Fluent in English and Swedish, written and spoken.
  • Driver’s license for car will be needed.

You will be located in Lundby Area, Göteborg, Sweden.

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at shrini@vipas.se or +46728479197

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!


Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

description:
At Nepa, Marketing Mix Modeling (MMM) isn’t just a key focus area; it’s a passion that drives us to deliver exceptional value to our clients. Our advanced analytics empower businesses to optimize their marketing spend, enabling them to make informed, data-driven decisions that truly maximize ROI across all channels.
We’re excited about the future and are actively investing in enhancing our MMM capabilities. By continuously refining our methods and tools, we deliver actionable insights that help our clients succeed.
We’re on the lookout for a Data Scientist who is eager to make a difference by driving Marketing Mix Modeling (MMM) solutions for our clients. If you’re passionate about leveraging data science to tackle complex marketing challenges and delivering valuable insights to over 500 blue-chip companies, this could be the perfect opportunity for you!

Your role as our Data Scientist

As a Data Scientist in our Marketing Mix Modelling team at Nepa, you will work with research and development as well as the implementation of advanced models, with a focus on implementation and delivery of our Marketing Mix Modelling solutions. You will join a brilliant team of Data Scientists, working across Nepa’s core products. You will also be in close contact with other key stakeholders across the company, working together to take our products to the next level.

Your responsibilites:

- Client delivery: You will take lead on our Marketing Mix Modelling deliveries to our clients. This involves everything from data structuring and modelling to presenting technical solutions and results to our clients.

- Advanced analysis: You leverage in-depth technical expertise to help solve our clients’ most demanding problems. Furthermore, are mindful of how technical design choices impact client value.

- Method expert and mentor: You will support our client teams and junior colleagues as an internal and external method expert in our Marketing Mix Modelling solution.

- Participate in product development: You will be part of a cross-functional product team with other data scientists, data engineers and developers. You will help integrate new learnings and insights in the product development as well as improving workflows and processes. We value collaboration and believe that the best products are built when combining different domain expertise’s.

- Staying on top of industry trends: Both tech and marketing are rapidly evolving industries. Nepa takes pride in our position as thought leaders, and places a big focus on staying up-to-date in order to remain one step ahead

Your profile

- Bachelor's/Master’s degree in Engineering, Statistics, Mathematics, Economics, Business administration or similar

- Practical experience from working as a data scientist, analytics consultant, or similar role in the industry

- Hands-on experience from working with Marketing Mix Modelling

- You have a business mind-set and are able to turn data and results into actionable insights for our clients

- Excellent story telling and communication skills, ability to explain technical issues and solutions to non-technical people

- Competent in Python

- You are fluent in English, both in writing and speech.

- You have a work permit.

Although not required, previous experience of Bayesian statistics is highly valued.

A few more things

- You share our vision to become the world leading data-to-growth company.

- You live our values daily | We see what others don’t | We love it and it shows | We cut the crap | We care and act accordingly |.

- You take pride in delivering high level of services, we are known for that.

Who are we?

Nepa is a leading provider of marketing optimization solutions. By combining data analytics, technology, and industry expertise, we empower our clients to make informed decisions and drive success. Our innovative solutions enable businesses to understand and connect with their customers, creating lasting relationships and delivering measurable results.

Next step!

We review applications as we receive them, and interviews will be held continuously so please submit your application as soon as possible.

description:
Are you a skilled problem-solver with a passion for technology and innovation? Join our clients' dynamic team as a System Developer, where you will play a key role in designing, developing, and maintaining cutting-edge software solutions.

About the Role

As a System Developer, you will work closely with cross-functional teams to build reliable and scalable systems. Your tasks will include developing and maintaining software, troubleshooting, and ensuring the quality of solutions for various clients. This is a great opportunity to work on exciting projects with a talented team in a fast-paced environment.

Key Responsibilities
Design, develop, and maintain high-quality software solutions.
Collaborate with other developers, product owners, and stakeholders to define requirements.
Write clean, efficient, and testable code.
Participate in code reviews to ensure best practices and high standards.
Monitor and debug applications to ensure optimal performance.
Support continuous integration and delivery pipelines.
Document system designs, processes, and user guides.
Required Skills and Experience
Proficiency in programming languages such as Java, C#, Python, or C++.
Experience with web development frameworks (e.g., Angular, React, or Vue.js).
Knowledge of database management systems like SQL, PostgreSQL, or MongoDB.
Familiarity with DevOps tools (e.g., Docker, Kubernetes, Jenkins, CI/CD pipelines).
Understanding of cloud platforms such as AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.
Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.
Fluency in English, both written and spoken.
Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or related fields (or equivalent experience).
Preferred Qualifications
Experience in Agile development methodologies (Scrum/Kanban).
Knowledge of system architecture and software design patterns.
Certification in cloud technologies (e.g., AWS Certified Developer).
Interest in learning new technologies and improving existing systems.

If you’re excited about this opportunity and believe you’re a great fit, we’d love to hear from you!

Start: ASAP
Location: Stockholm

description:
We’re looking for a Technical Support Engineer to join us in our Stockholm office. Are you passionate about solving intriguing technical support cases that demand knowledge about an exciting product, understanding customer needs, and occasionally require you to think creatively and innovatively to come up with a solution? Awesome, then you should keep on reading!

What you'll do as Technical Support Engineer
Taking ownership of technical customer issues reported through our ticketing system and seeing problems through to resolution.
Provide technical support to customers using API integrations and assist customers with API setup and best practices.
Handling technical deliveries to customers, such as building logic in document templates, data migrations, implementing SSO and customized delta reports.
Document and track customer issues and resolutions.
Guide, advise and challenge our customers and work with their solutions in a way that optimizes the value of CatalystOne in their system landscape.
Work in the team, together with Technical consultants and Integration developers to bring out the best technical solution for our customer through all phases of the customer lifecycle.

Requirements
Knowledge and experience in scripting language such as Javascript, Python, C#, Powershell, etc.
Experience of configuring APIs based on architecture frameworks and guidelines.
Experience of troubleshooting performance and functional issues.
Fluent in a Scandinavian language, as well as English.
A Bachelor's or a Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Technology, or equivalent experience.

The type of person we're looking for
Has a high customer focus and the ability to translate IT language for others with specialization in different areas.
Has a deep technical interest.

Takes ownership and responsibility.
Has a positive mindset and naturally contributes to a team’s success and optimistic spirit.
Likes to deliver high quality, is structured, and has time management skills.
Has the drive to find good solutions when faced with a problem or new challenges.

Benefits

As well as your salary, you’ll receive:

30 days’ vacation per year
Pension and insurance package, including private healthcare
Wellness contribution
Laptop, Mobile phone & subscription, and home internet allowance
Flexibility to work in a hybrid setup
And more…

CatalystOne does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firms/recruiters. CatalystOne will not pay any fees to search firms/recruiters if a candidate is submitted by a search firm/recruiter unless an agreement has been entered into with respect to the specific open position(s). Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to CatalystOne on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.

We would like to inform you that all candidates who receive a job offer will be subject to a background check.
Contact Mark Mc Daid Talent Acquisition Manager – People & Culture
About CatalystOne

CatalystOne is a Scandinavian leader of HCM-software with nearly 250 employees throughout Norway, Sweden, Denmark, and India. We have, since 2004, built a strong value-based company driven by our customers' success. Our culture is characterized by a unique combination of emphasis on results and on people. We have experienced high growth in recent years and have the ambition to continue this growth both in Scandinavia and in other North-European countries.

CatalystOne is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. We prohibit discrimination and harassment of any kind based on race, color, sex, religion, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, genetic information, pregnancy, or any other protected characteristic.

Founded in 2004
Co-workers 250+

description:
Are you a passionate software developer ready to make an impact? Join us on an exciting journey to revolutionize surgical training! Our cutting-edge simulators empower healthcare professionals worldwide to practice life-changing procedures—without putting patients at risk. In this role, your work will directly support healthcare professionals in restoring vision, particularly in underserved communities worldwide.

At Surgical Science curiosity and innovation are in our DNA. We’re a stable, growing multinational team with a mission to transform healthcare through technology. Together, we’re not just building simulators; we’re creating opportunities for safer, more effective medical training—and you can be part of it!

The role

As a Software Developer, you’ll take part in crafting realistic ophthalmic surgery simulations. Collaborating with a talented, distributed team, you’ll play a key role in:

Designing new training content using 3D models of anatomical structures and surgical tools.
Enhancing visual effects and developing real-time 3D training guides.
Boosting the visual realism of simulations to elevate the training experience.
Maintaining and expanding a growing codebase that drives our simulator; the focus will be on complex Python code which ties into C++, OpenGL & GLSL

Your profile

You are more than just a programmer; you embody the qualities of a skilled problem solver, driven by curiosity and an eagerness to find innovative solutions. Here’s what makes you a great fit:

You’re self-driven and results-oriented, thriving in a fast-paced, multicultural environment.
Complex challenges? Bring them on. You approach them with focus and persistence.
You love collaborating with bright minds, sharing knowledge, and building better solutions.
You’re comfortable diving into intricate codebases and reaching out to teammates when tackling tough problems.

This isn’t just a job, it’s an opportunity to contribute to something meaningful. Your skills will help shape the future of surgical training and make a difference in the lives of countless patients.

To succeed in this role, we think you have:

2+ years of experience in a scripting language (preferably Python) and solid C++ knowledge.
A foundational understanding of 3D Graphics: Solid knowledge of 3D graphics concepts and technologies, including a strong grasp of linear algebra (vectors, matrices, and transformations).
A degree in computer science, software engineering, or equivalent.
A professional level of English.

It is beneficial (but not a must) if you also have any of the following:

Experience with a commercial game engine (e.g. Unity, Unreal engine, etc.)
Experience in project management software and version control systems, like Jira and Git.
Are comfortable working with technical requirements, performing code reviews, and regression tests to release staging.
Knowledge of CMake, test procedures, and continuous integration
Knowledge of OpenGL and GLSL is beneficial.

Surgical Science as an employer
Surgical Science is a stable and profitable company operating in a growing market. We're a global and continuously expanding organization, with offices all around the world including Tel Aviv, Seattle, Gothenburg, and Stockholm.

We cultivate an environment where all employees can influence and contribute with their own experience and knowledge. We value growth and development among our employees, and you will get the chance to be a part of a welcoming, open team and contribute with your creativity. We live by our values of respect, curiosity , and perseverance.

Apply today

If you think you would fit our awesome team and enjoy our work environment, apply as soon as possible as recruitment is ongoing. Let us meet and figure out together whether we are a match! We kindly request that you apply with a resume or CV in English

  • A degree in computer science, software engineering, or equivalent.
    • A professional level of English.


It is beneficial (but not a must) if you also have any of the following:

  • Experience with a commercial game engine (e.g. Unity, Unreal engine, etc.)
  • Experience in project management software and version control systems, like Jira and Git.
  • Are comfortable working with technical requirements, performing code reviews, and regression tests to release staging.
  • Knowledge of CMake, test procedures, and continuous integration
    • Knowledge of OpenGL and GLSL is beneficial.


Surgical Science as an employer
Surgical Science is a stable and profitable company operating in a growing market. We're a global and continuously expanding organization, with offices all around the world including Tel Aviv, Seattle, Gothenburg, and Stockholm.


We cultivate an environment where all employees can influence and contribute with their own experience and knowledge. We value growth and development among our employees, and you will get the chance to be a part of a welcoming, open team and contribute with your creativity. We live by our values of respect, curiosity , and perseverance.


Apply today

If you think you would fit our awesome team and enjoy our work environment, apply as soon as possible as recruitment is ongoing. Let us meet and figure out together whether we are a match! We kindly request that you apply with a resume or CV in English

description:
We’re looking for a Technical Support Engineer to join us in our Stockholm office. Are you passionate about solving intriguing technical support cases that demand knowledge about an exciting product, understanding customer needs, and occasionally require you to think creatively and innovatively to come up with a solution? Awesome, then you should keep on reading!

What you'll do as Technical Support Engineer
Taking ownership of technical customer issues reported through our ticketing system and seeing problems through to resolution.
Provide technical support to customers using API integrations and assist customers with API setup and best practices.
Handling technical deliveries to customers, such as building logic in document templates, data migrations, implementing SSO and customized delta reports.
Document and track customer issues and resolutions.
Guide, advise and challenge our customers and work with their solutions in a way that optimizes the value of CatalystOne in their system landscape.
Work in the team, together with Technical consultants and Integration developers to bring out the best technical solution for our customer through all phases of the customer lifecycle.

Requirements
Knowledge and experience in scripting language such as Javascript, Python, C#, Powershell, etc.
Experience of configuring APIs based on architecture frameworks and guidelines.
Experience of troubleshooting performance and functional issues.
Fluent in a Scandinavian language, as well as English.
A Bachelor's or a Master's degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Information Technology, or equivalent experience.

The type of person we're looking for
Has a high customer focus and the ability to translate IT language for others with specialization in different areas.
Has a deep technical interest.

Takes ownership and responsibility.
Has a positive mindset and naturally contributes to a team’s success and optimistic spirit.
Likes to deliver high quality, is structured, and has time management skills.
Has the drive to find good solutions when faced with a problem or new challenges.

Benefits

As well as your salary, you’ll receive:

30 days’ vacation per year
Pension and insurance package, including private healthcare
Wellness contribution
Laptop, Mobile phone & subscription, and home internet allowance
Flexibility to work in a hybrid setup
And more…

CatalystOne does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firms/recruiters. CatalystOne will not pay any fees to search firms/recruiters if a candidate is submitted by a search firm/recruiter unless an agreement has been entered into with respect to the specific open position(s). Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to CatalystOne on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.

We would like to inform you that all candidates who receive a job offer will be subject to a background check.

description:
We're looking for an experienced developer to join us at Årsredovisning Online! Your opinions and ideas will be valued and celebrated here. Help us enhance our product, which supports Sweden's small businesses in generating their annual reports and tax returns digitally.

Who are we?

Årsredovisning Online came about in 2014 to help entrepreneurs with a simple and smart user-friendly solution for creating annual reports and tax returns. Since December 2020, we have been part of the Visma group. We take pride in being the top choice for small businesses in Sweden, offering the leading do-it-yourself solution for annual reports and tax returns. Årsredovisning Online can be used with all accounting services on the Swedish market. Today we are approximately 10 employees spread across four different locations.

We are a brand that is part of Visma Spcs - we are a small team within a larger context. A small business feel within a stable and well-renowned company.

About the role

We are in search of a motivated Ruby on Rails developer to help advance our application tailored for small business owners in Sweden. Our app is highly appreciated for its straightforwardness, leading to high customer satisfaction, which shapes our new development initiatives.

In 2024, more than 26,000 annual reports were submitted through our platform. You'll have the opportunity to work on a variety of projects with other talented developers, becoming an essential part of a small, passionate development team. Your role will involve daily activities such as solving problems, implementing new features, refining the system, troubleshooting, and optimizing performance.

We are looking for someone who thrives in a small, dynamic team setting, where open communication, idea sharing, and questioning the norm are encouraged. Still with the benefit of being part of the Visma group. You should be driven to improve your own skills and contribute to the technical community around you, aiming to build a positive and collaborative work environment. You possess the ability to link technical solutions to user needs and effectively discuss them with other developers.

Who are you?

You have a relevant IT education

You have a minimum of 3+ years of relevant work experience

You have good knowledge of English and Swedish, both written and spoken. As we are a diverse team with different backgrounds many meetings are being held in English

You have strong problem-solving skills and the ability to handle technical challenges

You are a skilled Ruby on Rails developer, have previous experience or curiosity about working with Ruby on Rails or having good experience with Java, Python or C#

You appreciate working on projects and with agile methods

You are efficient and quality is important to you

Proficiency in Git version control and CI/CD pipelines

Experience with test-driven development (TDD) and automated testing

Knowledge of front-end technologies (HTML5, CSS3, JavaScript)

What can we offer?

The chance to grow alongside enthusiastic colleagues in a small, entrepreneurially-minded SaaS company, while also enjoying the benefits of being part of Europe's largest tech group

A warm and inclusive work environment, with generous and helpful colleagues

A secure workplace with a focus on diversity and inclusion

A Visma-family with countless colleagues, who can share experiences and create valuable relationships across companies

A hybrid working day with a high degree of flexibility and independence

Health and well-being are close to our hearts. That's why we invest in activities that make you feel good, both mentally and physically

"My Competence Day" - dedicated days for your personal and professional development

Sounds exciting, right? We will be conducting interviews continuously. Tests and work samples may be part of the recruitment process. We would like to receive your application latest by January 5, 2025, via the link on our website. If you have any questions about the position, please feel free to contact mathias.eliasson@visma.com. We look forward to answering any questions you may have, and we look forward to hearing from you!
