description:
For over 10 years, Comparo has been transforming the way businesses utilize IT to steer their customer-centric services. We have proven ourselves to be known for the efficiency and flexibility that an IT Services & Management company offers. This wouldn’t be possible without our interdisciplinary and international team achieving that impeccable balance of creativity and analytical problem-solving skills. We work in a fast-paced, dynamic and make it happen culture. Our people are some of the brightest and passionate in the industry that thrives on being the most trusted advisors amongst our client base. We are always looking to hire highly passionate, collaborative and humble people that want to make a difference.
About the role

The BSM Architect is a pre and post-sales role. You will be responsible for educating customers on how to run IT as a service-oriented business, responsible for helping create true business value and in the making keeping cost low and quality high. In order to be truly accountable for the delivery of the business service, IT needs a BSM Strategy that is flexible and easy to implement. It needs to allow focused, bi-directional monitoring, reporting on systems and services that are critical to all the enterprise functions. Such a system should be able to provide a single point of control for operations and line-of-business management.

This role requires a deep understanding of infrastructure and networking technologies, along with the ability to understand and interpret organizational dynamics and the ability to positively influence key technology and enterprise architecture decision-makers. Applicants must have excellent knowledge of how to secure and control the IT service management assets right from the stage of discovering to consolidated configuration management and finally enable service monitoring. You must be highly skilled with relevant hands-on experience with BMC Software’s DSM solutions such as BMC Discovery, BMC Truesight and BMC CMDB.

Proven experience as a solution architect with direct interaction with the customer and end-users across multiple organisations, with at least 8 years’ of experience in Banking and Telecommunication domain, under BMC Products will be highly preferred.

Responsibilities

This position works across Application Development, Service Delivery and Infrastructure to identify, research, discuss, design and implement key enterprise architecture standards. Other responsibilities include:

Research, design, document, build, and pilot prioritized topics for standards.

Work closely with Development, Infrastructure, and Service Delivery teams to understand their needs.

Drive the identification, development and implementation of both solutions and standards in areas such as Asset Discovery, Application Mapping, Performance and Availability Monitoring, Event Management etc.

Propose new enterprise standards based on business need, IT need and technology advances.

Assist development teams to implement the standards into business applications. Investigate new technology and techniques that should be developed into an agency enterprise architecture standard.

Leads key enterprise architectural design projects as necessary. Operate as a business-savvy technical leader across the organization.

Influences development teams to design high-quality technical solutions that fit the Enterprise Architecture and standards.

Educates application development managers, developers, and business analysts on State Enterprise Architecture Standards.

Technical Skills
Apart from being a strong communicator, c ontributing directly to the strategy, development and quality of IT Service Management and the company’s service delivery capability, t he ideal candidate for this position must be able to demonstrate skills related to the following disciplines of Service Management:

Enterprise Discovery & Software Asset Management

Working knowledge of BMC Discovery solution for automated asset management, discovery and dependency mapping.

Strong understanding of Infrastructure level
Develop custom patterns to enhance discovery data quality
Troubleshooting whenever the application components stopped being discovered.
Backup and recovery of the datacentre appliances
Integration with BMC Remedy/Salesforce
Sound knowledge of the Discovery Exception process management.
Perform system and application setup/support and maintenance in conjunction with the regularly scheduled maintenance
Scripting knowledge (Unix, Perl, Python, SQL)
Excellent communication, and presentation skills
Experience with appliance health monitoring
BMC Certified Professional/Expert for BMC Discovery 11.x

Infrastructure & Application Performance Monitoring

Execute application or the infrastructure, performance and availability monitoring primarily using BMC Truesight Suite of solutions

Operational fluency in both Windows and UNIX environments.
Experience with other monitoring tools such as Zabbix, Nagios, HP OpenView, SCOM, etc.
Expecience with Service Monitoring in context of business services (SLAs) and Event analytics
Planning/Deployment/Configuration/ Administration of the BMC TrueSight Operations Management and underlying components.
Background in working in an environment which uses BMC ITSM Suite of products such as Remedy, CMDB, My IT, RSSO.
Provide high-level functional systems analysis, design, integration, documentation, and implementation.
Advice on exceptionally complex problems that necessitate a high-level knowledge of the BMC’s Automation & Orchestration products for effective implementation.
BMC Certified Professional/Expert for BMC TSOM 11.x

Centralized Configuration Management Database

Tightly integrated with the discovery solution and monitoring solution with configuration management system

Service organisation design.
Service management process/procedure definition.
Customer engagement (to agree with processes & interfaces).
Service desk and service reporting design.
Service management / design proposals to customers.
Change Requests for projects which require out of scope deliverables.
Provide exceptional support during any of service lifecycle phases, but is usually focused on Transition.
Knowledge of ITIL v3.
Service Design/Architecture experience.
Service Implementation background.
Service Management Tool Design & Specification experience.
BMC Certified Professional/Expert for ITSM

description:
At Umain, we're not just creating software; we're crafting the future, one innovative project at a time. With our motto "Shape, Ship, Scale," we empower our team to not only envision the future but also play a pivotal role in building it. We're a dynamic team where you can shape the future, ship groundbreaking solutions, and scale your abilities in many different ways.

We're on the lookout for developers ready to join us in this journey, bringing passion, creativity, and dedication along with them. The role is relatively broad and focused on backend technologies, where we offer the opportunity to work on many interesting projects on modern technologies.

Job Summary:

We are looking for a Senior Backend Engineer with a genuine enthusiasm in building robust solutions to power innovative digital experiences.

What We Offer:

A chance to work on a range of diverse and unique projects that explore and push the boundaries of what's possible.

A fun and fair work environment where you have the opportunity to expand your skills through unique challenges and fantastic colleagues.

A personal coach, and a setting where you can grow professionally and personally.

Being part of multidisciplinary teams, participating in agile teams, being an important player in a highly ambitious setting.

As a Senior Backend Developer at Umain, your role will involve:

Building high-performance backend systems using modern languages like Go, NodeJS, Python, and Kotlin to power innovative experiences

Using modern backend frameworks such as Fiber, Ktor, Express and FastAPI to create robust solutions.

Designing and implementing cloud-native solutions across AWS, GCP and Azure, using Infrastructure-as-Code (Terraform) for resource management

Building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines with containerized deployments and scaling strategies

Developing robust data models and database architectures to support application requirements

Participating in projects & teams alongside some of the largest and most forward-thinking brands on the planet

Who You Are:

You're a developer with a passion for innovation and a knack for problem-solving.
You're eager to learn, grow, and take on new challenges.
You value collaboration, diversity, and the opportunity to make a significant impact.
You believe in the power of technology to shape the future.

Why Umain?

Career Framework:

We believe in fairness and clarity, which is why we've established a transparent career framework to ensure equal pay and equal opportunities for all. Your growth and success are as important to us as they are to you. Together with your coach, you will build your own development plan and grow in your career.

Work-Life Balance:

At Umain, diversity is our strength. We understand that life doesn’t pause when you walk into the office. That's why we've cultivated an environment that supports an excellent work-life balance. We welcome team members from all walks of life, recognizing the richness that different backgrounds, ages, and life stages bring to our team. We're committed to supporting each other, encouraging a healthy work-life balance that respects your needs, whether it's taking care of your family, your pets, or yourself.

Innovations and Learning:

Technology is always evolving, bringing new challenges and opportunities for collaboration and learning. Our developers work closely with designers, analysts, testers and more to tackle these challenges head-on, sharing knowledge and growing together.

Skills Over Degrees:

We’re more interested in what you can do than in the diplomas you hold. Talent, drive, and creativity are what count at Umain. Here, you’ll find opportunities to grow, learn, and excel in your career, regardless of your educational background. If you have the ambition and commitment to succeed, we have the environment and resources to support your journey.

Are you ready to SHAPE, SHIP, and SCALE with us?

descriptionHTML:
At Umain, we're not just creating software; we're crafting the future, one innovative project at a time. With our motto "Shape, Ship, Scale," we empower our team to not only envision the future but also play a pivotal role in building it. We're a dynamic team where you can shape the future, ship groundbreaking solutions, and scale your abilities in many different ways.

We're on the lookout for developers ready to join us in this journey, bringing passion, creativity, and dedication along with them. The role is relatively broad and focused on backend technologies, where we offer the opportunity to work on many interesting projects on modern technologies.


Job Summary:

We are looking for a Senior Backend Engineer with a genuine enthusiasm in building robust solutions to power innovative digital experiences.


What We Offer:


  • A chance to work on a range of diverse and unique projects that explore and push the boundaries of what's possible.

  • A fun and fair work environment where you have the opportunity to expand your skills through unique challenges and fantastic colleagues.

  • A personal coach, and a setting where you can grow professionally and personally.

  • Being part of multidisciplinary teams, participating in agile teams, being an important player in a highly ambitious setting.


As a Senior Backend Developer at Umain, your role will involve:


  • Building high-performance backend systems using modern languages like Go, NodeJS, Python, and Kotlin to power innovative experiences

  • Using modern backend frameworks such as Fiber, Ktor, Express and FastAPI to create robust solutions.

  • Designing and implementing cloud-native solutions across AWS, GCP and Azure, using Infrastructure-as-Code (Terraform) for resource management

  • Building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines with containerized deployments and scaling strategies

  • Developing robust data models and database architectures to support application requirements

  • Participating in projects & teams alongside some of the largest and most forward-thinking brands on the planet


Who You Are:


  • You're a developer with a passion for innovation and a knack for problem-solving.
  • You're eager to learn, grow, and take on new challenges.
  • You value collaboration, diversity, and the opportunity to make a significant impact.
  • You believe in the power of technology to shape the future.


Why Umain?


Career Framework:

We believe in fairness and clarity, which is why we've established a transparent career framework to ensure equal pay and equal opportunities for all. Your growth and success are as important to us as they are to you. Together with your coach, you will build your own development plan and grow in your career.


Work-Life Balance:

At Umain, diversity is our strength. We understand that life doesn’t pause when you walk into the office. That's why we've cultivated an environment that supports an excellent work-life balance. We welcome team members from all walks of life, recognizing the richness that different backgrounds, ages, and life stages bring to our team. We're committed to supporting each other, encouraging a healthy work-life balance that respects your needs, whether it's taking care of your family, your pets, or yourself.


Innovations and Learning:

Technology is always evolving, bringing new challenges and opportunities for collaboration and learning. Our developers work closely with designers, analysts, testers and more to tackle these challenges head-on, sharing knowledge and growing together.


Skills Over Degrees:

We’re more interested in what you can do than in the diplomas you hold. Talent, drive, and creativity are what count at Umain. Here, you’ll find opportunities to grow, learn, and excel in your career, regardless of your educational background. If you have the ambition and commitment to succeed, we have the environment and resources to support your journey.


Are you ready to SHAPE, SHIP, and SCALE with us?

If you're a developer who thrives on innovation, values a supportive and inclusive workplace, and is eager to make a tangible impact on the future, we’d love to hear from you. Let’s build something awesome together.

description:
In a world where product size labels are unreliable, Volumental is the footwear industry's leading FitTech company, using 3D scans and a one-of-a-kind, AI-powered recommendation engine to match everyone with the shoes that fit them best.

Our vision is “a world without sizes, where every body fits.” With top brand and retail partners across the world including New Balance, Fleet Feet, XXL, The Athlete’s Foot, Red Wing Shoes, Intersport and Crocs, our footprint spans 3000+ stores across 58 countries, and growing! To date, we’ve gathered more than 60 million foot scans.

These are exciting times at Volumental and we are looking for a full stack developer with front end focus to join us in crafting our new in-store foot scanning experience, powered by Artificial Intelligence (AI) and Computer Vision.

What will you do?

You will work on our web application which is used together with our 3D foot scanner to provide shoe size recommendations for shoppers. The application reconstructs 3D models of the shopper’s feet. A combination of foot scans, retail purchase data and AI is used to produce the best shoe fit recommendations.

We’re always working to innovate and come up with new ways to enhance the customer experience. In this creative process, you will play an important part!

We are excited about you because:

You have worked at least 3 years professionally with front-end and back-end web development.
You have experience with React and TypeScript and your primary focus is front-end.
You also have experience with Python/Go and API design.
You are a self-motivated and collaborative team member.
You are excited to learn new things and to solve challenging problems.

Bonus - Not required but nice to have, absolutely let us know if you have experience with any of the following:

You have experience with GCP and SQL.
You are interested in 3D and visualization frameworks like: Three.js, WebGL

You have a degree in Computer Science or similar.

What we can offer you:

Work in a supportive scale-up environment
Personal learning budget and access to coaching
Flexible hybrid-remote work policy
Opportunity to work with a great team of 20+ nationalities in our English-speaking office
Occupational pension at ITP1 level
Flexible Public Holidays Policy
Options Program
Parental pay top-up
Wellness allowance
Dog-friendly office

description:
Title: Senior Field Application Engineer
Location: Kista, Sweden

WIND RIVER

Wind River is a global leader in delivering software for mission-critical intelligent systems. For more than four decades, the company has been an innovator and pioneer, powering billions of systems that require the highest levels of security, safety, and reliability.

Wind River helps customers across automotive, aerospace, defense, industrial, medical, and telecommunications industries solve complex technology challenges on their journey toward the new intelligent machine economy. The company’s software powers generation after generation of the safest, most secure systems in the world. Examples include playing a key role in NASA space missions — such as Artemis I, the James Webb Space Telescope, and multiple Mars rovers — and in recent 5G milestones — including the world’s first successful 5G data session with Verizon and in building one of the largest Open RAN networks in the world with Vodafone.

The company has received industry recognition for its technology innovation and leadership, and for its workplace culture, including global Great Place to Work certification and being named a “Top Workplace” for ten consecutive years. If you want to be part of a unique culture where the lived experience is based on our cultural attributes of growth mindset, customer-focus, and diversity, equity, inclusion & belonging, come join us and help advance the future software defined world.

ABOUT THE OPPORTUNITY

Innovation

Are you a curious and collaborative engineer, someone that is excited about working on new and innovative solutions utilizing technology that is at the forefront of the industry? Do you want to be part of the Digital Transformation wave that is happening today? This is an exciting time to be at Wind River! You will have an opportunity to sharpen your skills in Linux and Kubernetes, while working with the leading companies in the industry.

Interface & Collaboration

Working with the leading provider of integrated embedded software solutions, you will work with some of the most talented engineers in the industry to draft technical solutions to challenging problems.

As our customers look to gain a competitive advantage in this digital first world, they are looking to companies like Wind River to partner with in their journey. Wind River is answering this call through our delivery of the world’s first Cloud Native Environment that enables developers of intelligent edge devices to transform and optimize their device life cycle from Development to Deployment, to Operations, and Servicing.

Your opportunity is to join as a key member of highly talented and motivated, customer facing field engineering team. You will be responsible for understanding our customers' business and technical needs and to work with them in the capacity of technical evangelist and trusted advisor in crafting the next generation Intelligent systems.

Responsibilities

Understand your customer’s technical requirements, design technical solutions, and showcase them through product presentations, discovery workshops, proof of concepts, and evaluations, to secure the technical sale.
Be the customer facing evangelist by guiding your customers through their Digital Transformation journey.
Partner closely with your Account Manager and be focused on hunting for new business.
Manage all aspects of the technical needs of the assigned territory utilizing all available resources.
Increase Wind River market share with your customers.
Manage Trade Shows and Seminars.

ABOUT YOU
Core Competencies & Demonstrated Success

The ideal candidate will have 10+ years of software development and solutions architecting, with experience in the following areas:
Direct, hands-on experience with Linux. Experience with Yocto and Debian is advantageous.
Experience with Cloud Native technologies including Kubernetes, containers, microservices, etc.
Programming skills in the C or C++ language is essential, and experience or interest in the following are desirable: Python, Rust, Java, etc.
Demo development and delivery experience (internal and/or external).
Experience with DevSecOps development methodologies including an understanding of tools such as Gitlab, Jenkins, Docker etc.
Experience working with the telecommunications industry.

Qualifications

BSCS or BSEE is required.
Software development experience.
Excellent communication skills exhibited through white boarding, technical presentations, white papers, and demonstrations.
Experience interfacing with internal and/or external customers.
Experience responding to customer RFPs is desirable.
Excellent time management skills and ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously.
Demonstrated self-starter and able to work independently in a fast-paced environment.
Ability to travel to customers and trade shows, when required, within EMEA.
Positive Attitude.
Strong growth mindset, continuous learner, and adaptive to the Wind River culture.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Backend Developer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

Our client is seeking an experienced and proactive Backend Developer with Java expertise to strengthen its IT team. The consultant will initially work on the Personuppgifter Från Skatteverket (PFS) project, scheduled for release in spring 2025. This role focuses on backend development with occasional frontend tasks, working closely within a Scrum team. Key responsibilities include building Java applications aligned with client's target architecture, integrating with third-party services, and modernizing legacy systems through microservices implemented in Spring Boot.

Key Technologies and Tools:

Deployment: Kubernetes/OpenShift, ArgoCD, Docker
Code Management: Bitbucket/Git
Documentation: Confluence
Monitoring & Analysis: Splunk, Grafana
Database Integration: JPA with IBM DB2
Inter-Service Communication: RabbitMQ, REST
Integrations: SFTP

The role also involves testing, system architecture planning, and requirements gathering in close collaboration with the team and stakeholders. Depending on client's needs, the consultant may contribute to other similar projects within the IT department during the contract.

Must-Have Requirements:

Fluency in Swedish, both spoken and written.
Demonstrated experience and capability to fulfill the role requirements.
7+ years of recent experience in Java development within a distributed, service-oriented architecture.
Proficiency in microservices architecture.
At least 5 years of system development experience within an IT organization with 100+ employees in the last 8 years.
Strong expertise in container technology (Kubernetes).
Experience with Java version 17 or higher.
Willingness to work onsite at client's job location in Sundsvall for a minimum of 3 days per week, with remote work possible for the remaining time.
Familiarity with agile methodologies.

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at priyanka@vipas.se &contact me at +46727749222

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

description:
Cloud Infrastructure Engineer – Shape the Future of Our AWS Infrastructure

At Paligo, we’re not just producing content—we’re redefining how the world’s leading companies create, manage, and deliver technical documentation. As a globally leading Component Content Management System (CCMS), Paligo is transforming traditional content management and the way technical information is crafted, organized, and accessed by major organizations like Bitdefender, Bluetooth, Mitsubishi, the European Commission, Wrike, Alteryx, and more.

As a Cloud Infrastructure Engineer, you’ll join our talented team at Paligo's headquarters in Solna, Stockholm, working alongside other tech leaders to drive the ongoing innovation of our cloud infrastructure. Our cloud team is small but agile, prioritizing collaboration and technical excellence. Here, you’ll have the chance to work closely with our engineering team and make a significant impact on our journey to becoming the #1 CCMS in the industry.

What You’ll Do:

- Design, implement, and maintain AWS cloud infrastructure, ensuring best practices and strategic alignment.

- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to drive cloud projects from inception to completion.

- Develop pipelines, scripts, and tools to streamline deployment, improve developer experience, and increase operational efficiency.

- Enhance the security, performance, and reliability of AWS cloud services through proactive monitoring and troubleshooting.

- Stay ahead of industry trends, evaluating new AWS services and technologies to improve our cloud environment.

- Partner with stakeholders to gather requirements, define architecture, and provide technical expertise.

What We’re Looking For:

- A Cloud Infrastructure Engineer with 5 years’ experience focused on AWS, with certifications like AWS Certified Solutions Architect or AWS Certified DevOps Engineer preferred.

- Solid knowledge of AWS services like ECS, S3, Lambda, SQS, RDS, CloudFormation, and CDK.

- Skilled in Go, Python, TypeScript, and automation tools for cloud provisioning and deployment.

- Expertise in cloud security, identity management, and data encryption.

- Excellent communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to guide and coach engineers new to AWS.

- A proactive approach to problem-solving with strong analytical skills.

Why You’ll Love Working at Paligo:

- You’ll be part of an industry-leading SaaS and CCMS innovator, helping drive the future of content management.

- A fast-growing, dynamic work environment with endless opportunities for growth.

- Newly upgraded, modern offices near transit and dining options.

- Great perks, including an annual wellness contribution, professional development budget, home office support, and parental pay.

Who We Are:

At Paligo, we’re disrupting the CCMS landscape with our cloud-based platform, trusted by major global brands to manage their technical documentation. We value open communication, collaboration, and a vibrant work culture celebrating diversity and inclusion.

Join Us in Shaping the Future of Cloud Infrastructure!

If you’re passionate about AWS and ready to contribute to our mission, we’d love to hear from you! Ready to learn more? Explore our culture and values on our careers page and see what it’s like to be part of the Paligo community.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Sr. Developer-IAM

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Sr. Developer.

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

We are seeking a skilled Senior Developer with experience in working as a provider of Identity and Access Management (IAM) services to join a dynamic team. This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a collaborative environment, values knowledge sharing, and is eager to contribute to the growth and success of both the team and the solutions they deliver.

Key Responsibilities:

Implement and manage IAM solutions using OpenID Connect, OAuth2, Keycloak, and EntraID.
Develop and maintain applications using Java, Python and React.
Build, deploy, and maintain services in AWS environments.
Collaborate closely with team members and stakeholders to drive technical solutions forward, ensuring high quality and efficient delivery.

Must-Have Skills:

Strong experience delivering IAM services, using for example OpenID Connect, OAuth2, Keycloak, EntraID.
Knowledge about API Security and Authorization Mechanisms.
Solid knowledge of Java for back-end development.
More than basic understanding of REST and Web APIs
Devops mindset and experience.
Experience working with AWS cloud services.
Familiarity with Python.

Nice-to-Have Skills:

Proficiency in React for front-end development.

What we are looking For:

A collaborative team player, passionate about knowledge sharing and supporting teammates.
Motivated to take ownership and drive solution development.
Willing to advocate for IAM initiatives and support strategic transformation.
Open to being in the office at least two days per week.
Curious and eager to learn new skills, including programming languages, technologies, and services.

Required skills-

AWS Cloud Services
OAuth2
Java
Identity and Access Management (IAM)
Python
Amazon Web Services (AWS)
OpenIDConnect
keycloak
React Frontend
EntraID

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at aniket@vipas.se & contact me at +91-7894195216

description:
Location: Remote in CET Time Zone

Job Description:

As a Senior 3D Designer, you will play a pivotal role in our creative team, leading the design and execution of high-quality 3D production and motion graphics. You will collaborate with cross-functional teams to deliver visually stunning and technically sound projects that align with our client's visions and brand identities.

Key Responsibilities:

Lead the conceptualization and creation of 3D models, animations, and motion graphics for various projects.
Collaborate with creative directors, designers, and other stakeholders to understand project requirements and deliver innovative solutions.
Develop and refine 3D assets, ensuring they meet the highest standards of quality and creativity.
Stay updated with the latest trends and technologies in 3D design and motion graphics to continuously improve our offerings.
Mentor and guide junior designers, providing feedback and fostering a collaborative team environment.
Manage multiple projects simultaneously, ensuring timely delivery and adherence to project goals and budgets.
Understanding in 3D with Ai a plus.

Qualifications:

Bachelor’s degree in Graphic Design, Animation, Fine Arts, or a related field valuable.
Minimum of 8 years of professional experience in 3D design and motion graphics.
Proficiency in industry-standard 3D software such as Autodesk Maya, Blender, Cinema 4D, or equivalent.
Strong portfolio showcasing a range of 3D production and motion graphics projects.
Excellent understanding of lighting, texturing, and rendering techniques.
Strong problem-solving skills and the ability to work independently and collaboratively.
Excellent communication skills and the ability to articulate design concepts to non-technical stakeholders.

Preferred Skills:

Experience with virtual reality (VR) and augmented reality (AR) projects.
Knowledge of programming languages such as Python or C++ for 3D applications.
Familiarity with video editing software like Adobe Premiere Pro and After Effects.

Application Process:
Interested candidates are invited to submit their resume, cover letter, and a portfolio of relevant work as part of the application. Please share your resume in English.

If you have not heard from us in 2 weeks, please consider your application as unsuccessful.

______

Why join Klingit?

Here at Klingit, we believe that good quality design and development is the key to success in any business and we are driven by creating more equal opportunities for creatives all over the world. By joining Klingit, you will be part of the journey to create something new in the agency world and to be able to make an impact.

We can offer you:

Being part of a fun, supportive and close-knit team.

Being part of our talented creative team with top developers and designers all over the world.

Be involved in key client projects from day one.

A steep learning curve and opportunities for development and growth.

Klingits recruitment process:

If this is a match, please share your CV/Portfolio or the link to your LinkedIn profile and a short cover letter.

If you move on to the next stage, we have a short call and use a test to ensure a fair selection based on your readiness for the role and your potential to grow with us.

Next up: you get a chance to get to know us and we want to get to know you! In the first interview, we will focus on your personality, motivation for this role and your team fit. In the second interview, we want to go deeper into your technical skills and what you can add to the team. Before we move on to an offer, we will ask for references from previous work experience. Let's do this!

We move fast, so please send your application today!

description:
The role of the Senior Java Software Developer is to design, develop and maintain a Java-based network controller, used by our network management system – the SoSmart software suite.

Introduction

Smartoptics provides innovative optical networking solutions for a new era of open networking. We focus on solving network challenges and increasing the competitiveness of our customers. Our customer base includes cable and telecom operators, cloud providers, Internet exchanges, governments and thousands of enterprises.

The candidate will be part of the R&D team. The R&D team develops complete systems including both hardware and software.

Position summary

We are looking for a senior developer for the SoSmart software suite, https://smartoptics.com/products/sosmart/. The team is multinational, but this position is seated in our Stockholm office. We are working agile according to the SAFe methodology. Some possibility for work from home, but most days we try to meet in our office in Kista, Stockholm.

Required skills
Experience of Java 17+
Development experience on Linux
Experience of Test-Driven Development, for example Unit test with Mockito
Based in the Stockholm area
Exam within relevant field, e.g. MSc in Electrical Engineering or Computer Science
Good communication skills in English, preferably also in Swedish
Considered beneficial
Experience from work with larger module-based Java projects together with Karaf and Maven
Micro-service architectures and containerization (e.g. Docker)
Experience with REST APIs
End-to-end testing with Python
Experience of Git and Gerrit
Experience with network technologies (IP, Ethernet, DWDM)
Experience with SDN (software-defined network) architectures and related protocols (e.g. RESTCONF, NETCONF and gNMI)
Knowledge of agile development

Smartoptics R&D team is located in Kista with head office in Oslo, Norway. Benefits include pension, health insurance, bonus scheme, 6 weeks’ vacation and flexible working hours. For more information about Smartoptics, please see smartoptics.com/about.

Furthermore, note that you must have a Swedish/EU work permit. No relocation assistance or visa support provided. No recruiters or agencies, please.

About Smartoptics

Smartoptics is a Scandinavian company founded in 2006. We provide innovative optical networking solutions for the new era of open networking. Our focus is on solving network challenges and enhancing the competitiveness of our customers. Our clientele includes cable and telecom operators, cloud providers, Internet exchanges, governments, and thousands of enterprises.

At Smartoptics, we value inclusivity and prioritize the well-being of our employees. We foster a positive company culture and provide a supportive work environment.

description:
Odevo is a group of exciting brands with a shared vision of challenging status quo in the property management industry. We are committed to revolutionizing the industry with innovative software solutions that make managing properties easier, more efficient, and more effective. Our rapidly growing product and engineering organization is approaching 100 highly skilled professionals.

Our cloud-based platform is unique, and in a brief time, we have proven ourselves as a leading and innovative player on the market. Our product development department acts as a SaaS supplier to all the companies in the Odevo group and several other players in the industry. Together, we will continue to challenge and change this industry. To continue our ambitious growth journey, we seek more great people to join us to build market-leading property management software products. Are you one of them?

The role:
As a Fullstack Developer, you will be part of a team that is responsible for our organization's AI-focused initiatives, creating transformative solutions for our business opportunities. With your expertise as a developer, you and your team will lead the charge in building end-to-end solutions that help us deliver efficiency gains to our customers.

You will be pivotal in defining how we apply AI solutions to business problems. We want to deeply integrate AI across our organization, drive innovation and ensure that AI is a clear part of our business strategy.

For this role, deep AI expertise is not a requirement, we already have AI expertise in the team. Instead, we are looking for experienced Fullstack Developers that can craft systems directly from customer requirements, spanning design, frontend, backend, databases, all the way to deployments and infrastructure.

You will be reporting to our AI Engineering Manager and working closely with our Head of AI Product.

Who You Are:
You are an experienced and driven software engineer who has shipped applications to real users. Complex challenges do not deter you; they intrigue you. You tackle them methodically, finding practical solutions that truly make a difference.

You prefer working in a team with developers, designers and product managers and deeply collaborate with your team rather than working from specifications. You communicate effectively and can discuss the pros and cons of different options in constructive ways.

You find AI developments interesting, and have experimented with them, and are eager to learn more.

Responsibilities

Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including engineers, and product managers, to define requirements and deliver AI solutions that meet business needs.
Interested in learning more about the latest developments in generative AI, reading up on open-source projects and exploring AI technologies that can benefit the organization.
Create prototypes and proof-of-concepts to demonstrate the feasibility and potential of solutions to stakeholders.
Document architecture designs, algorithms, and best practices for knowledge sharing within the organization.

Qualifications

Bachelor's or Master's degree in computer science, Machine Learning, or a related field.
Experience in backend development using Python and FastAPI, and React for frontend development
Proven experience with building applications for real users, spanning design, frontend, backend, databases and infrastructure. We don’t require deep experience in all areas.
You will be asked to demo your experience in the interview process
Proficiency in Swedish

What we offer

Hybrid/remote work environment - you will be part of a team based in and around Stockholm that values collaboration and communication, regardless of location.
Professional growth - to work with the most talented developers in the industry.
Modern technology - we invest in the latest technologies and tools, we sign agreements with the largest players, and we encourage our team members to share their ideas and take ownership of their work to form a collaborative environment where AI is used throughout the group.
Innovation - to work on exciting projects that push the boundaries of our industry and make a real impact.
Commitment to quality - a dynamic and forward-thinking company that values profitable and long-term product development.

Location
We find great value in being able to work closely with our Stockholm-based team in person. At the same time, we understand the need to focus deeply without interruptions. Therefore, the team works according to a hybrid setup with 3 days at the Stockholm office, and 2 days remotely from home, combining the best of both worlds.

Excited?
If you are excited about being part of a successful team, we encourage you to apply for this position.

Why we formed Odevo
About Odevo
Our Software
descriptionHTML:
Odevo is a group of exciting brands with a shared vision of challenging status quo in the property management industry. We are committed to revolutionizing the industry with innovative software solutions that make managing properties easier, more efficient, and more effective. Our rapidly growing product and engineering organization is approaching 100 highly skilled professionals.

Our cloud-based platform is unique, and in a brief time, we have proven ourselves as a leading and innovative player on the market. Our product development department acts as a SaaS supplier to all the companies in the Odevo group and several other players in the industry. Together, we will continue to challenge and change this industry. To continue our ambitious growth journey, we seek more great people to join us to build market-leading property management software products. Are you one of them?

The role:
As a Fullstack Developer, you will be part of a team that is responsible for our organization's AI-focused initiatives, creating transformative solutions for our business opportunities. With your expertise as a developer, you and your team will lead the charge in building end-to-end solutions that help us deliver efficiency gains to our customers.

You will be pivotal in defining how we apply AI solutions to business problems. We want to deeply integrate AI across our organization, drive innovation and ensure that AI is a clear part of our business strategy.

For this role, deep AI expertise is not a requirement, we already have AI expertise in the team. Instead, we are looking for experienced Fullstack Developers that can craft systems directly from customer requirements, spanning design, frontend, backend, databases, all the way to deployments and infrastructure.

You will be reporting to our AI Engineering Manager and working closely with our Head of AI Product.

Who You Are:
You are an experienced and driven software engineer who has shipped applications to real users. Complex challenges do not deter you; they intrigue you. You tackle them methodically, finding practical solutions that truly make a difference.

You prefer working in a team with developers, designers and product managers and deeply collaborate with your team rather than working from specifications. You communicate effectively and can discuss the pros and cons of different options in constructive ways.

You find AI developments interesting, and have experimented with them, and are eager to learn more.

Responsibilities

  • Collaborate closely with cross-functional teams, including engineers, and product managers, to define requirements and deliver AI solutions that meet business needs.
  • Interested in learning more about the latest developments in generative AI, reading up on open-source projects and exploring AI technologies that can benefit the organization.
  • Create prototypes and proof-of-concepts to demonstrate the feasibility and potential of solutions to stakeholders.
  • Document architecture designs, algorithms, and best practices for knowledge sharing within the organization.

Qualifications

  • Bachelor's or Master's degree in computer science, Machine Learning, or a related field.
  • Experience in backend development using Python and FastAPI, and React for frontend development
  • Proven experience with building applications for real users, spanning design, frontend, backend, databases and infrastructure. We don’t require deep experience in all areas.
  • You will be asked to demo your experience in the interview process
  • Proficiency in Swedish

What we offer

  • Hybrid/remote work environment - you will be part of a team based in and around Stockholm that values collaboration and communication, regardless of location.
  • Professional growth - to work with the most talented developers in the industry.
  • Modern technology - we invest in the latest technologies and tools, we sign agreements with the largest players, and we encourage our team members to share their ideas and take ownership of their work to form a collaborative environment where AI is used throughout the group.
  • Innovation - to work on exciting projects that push the boundaries of our industry and make a real impact.
  • Commitment to quality - a dynamic and forward-thinking company that values profitable and long-term product development.

Location
We find great value in being able to work closely with our Stockholm-based team in person. At the same time, we understand the need to focus deeply without interruptions. Therefore, the team works according to a hybrid setup with 3 days at the Stockholm office, and 2 days remotely from home, combining the best of both worlds.

Excited?
If you are excited about being part of a successful team, we encourage you to apply for this position.

Why we formed Odevo
About Odevo
Our Software

description:
Who we are ‍️
Welcome to Findity, the tech provider fueling Europe’s leading edge in expense management solutions! We empower over 30,000 corporate entities and more than 290,000 employees to conquer their financial challenges with ease. Join us in revolutionizing how businesses thrive in the digital age!

What we do
At Findity, we constantly strive to eliminate expense management for every individual and business so they can focus on what matters. Expense management is for many a must and not a want, that is why we partner with the leading software and financial institutes to eliminate the pain of dealing with expenses.

The role

We are now looking for a skilled, driven and experienced Backend Developer to join our team of creators, constantly raising the benchmark on expense management. Though working behind the scenes, our backend developer will have a great effect not only on our business success but also on the success of our partners. Simply put, our ideal candidate should have a blend of technical expertise, insatiable curiosity, and an analytical mindset.

What you will do

Participate and take ownership in the day to day work in the scrum team.
Design and implement robust APIs to support different clients, internal and external.
Regularly communicate with project managers, stakeholders, quality assurance teams, and other developers regarding advancements on the technology roadmap.
Collaborate with the front-end developers and other team members.
Develop ideas for new products, programs, or features by following industry developments, emerging technologies, and trends.

Who you are

Great understanding in the development process and design patterns
A minimum of three years of experience in Java or other similar languages
An academic background in a relevant field
Good knowledge of relational databases
Experience with Git-based version control
Experience in using postman or other API tools
A drive and doer attitude that is not afraid to take on challenging tasks
A curiosity to learn and grow professionally
Ability to work independently as well as in a team
Great attention to detail as well as good problem solving and communication skill

Bonus for Us if you have worked with some of below tech:
Grails, MariaDB/ MySQL, Docker/ Kubernetes, GitLab, Python, Javascript Angular/ Typescript, Jira, Kafka and/or Ubuntu

Apply Now!
Excited about embarking on your new career journey? Fantastic! Send us your application in English as soon as possible!

description:
Karo Healthcare, a dynamic and growing company, is all about making smart choices for everyday healthcare. With a wide-ranging portfolio across seven categories including medical products, we own and sell over 100 brands in about 90 countries. Our portfolio includes such brands as E45, Pevaryl, Lamisil, Nutravita, Decubal and many others. Our core belief in empowering people to make intelligent health decisions drives our growth strategy, blending organic expansion and M&A.

Are you ready to join a fast-moving, empowered team where your contributions are valued, and you can make a significant impact on an entire organization? We are looking for a motivated Data Engineer with hands-on experience using the Databricks platform to join our collaborative team of six, led by the Head of Data & Analytics. If you are passionate about creating high-quality data solutions, thrive in a high-tempo environment, and are excited about the potential to expand your skills in AI and ML, we would love to hear from you!

About the Role

As a Data Engineer on our team, you’ll work hands-on across all parts of the data engineering lifecycle, from data ingestion to transformation and optimization. You’ll have the freedom to explore and optimize all areas of our data pipeline, ensuring end-to-end quality, efficiency, and innovation in everything we deliver.

In this role, you will:

Design, develop, and optimize data pipelines on the Databricks platform.
Collaborate closely with team members and stakeholders to deliver high-quality data solutions that meet our business’s needs.
Be empowered to proactively address technical challenges and help us stay on the cutting edge of data engineering best practices.
Have the opportunity to dive into AI/ML projects, with mentoring and support available to expand your expertise.

Requirements

What You Will Need

We’re looking for a data engineer who brings:

Experience working with Databricks and a strong understanding of lakehouse architecture
Proficiency in SQL, Python, and Spark, with a strong ability to write efficient, clean, and optimized code.
A collaborative spirit and the drive to work in a high-tempo, agile team where adaptability is key.
Curiosity and a desire to grow in the data engineering field; experience or interest in AI/ML is a big plus.
Technical Competencies:
Education: Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Data Science, or a related field.
Experience: Minimum of 3 years of relevant experience in data engineering or data science.
Core Skills:

- Advanced proficiency in SQL and intermediate knowledge of Python.

- At least 2 years of hands-on experience with Databricks.

- Familiarity with Medallion architecture.

- Experience building and managing CI/CD pipelines.

- Proficient in Git version control and data modeling techniques (e.g., Kimball/Star schema).

- Strong understanding of ETL/ELT processing.

Certifications (optional but desirable):

- Databricks Certified Data Engineer Professional/Associate.

- Databricks Certified Associate Developer for Apache Spark.

- Databricks Certified Machine Learning Associate/Professional.

Nice-to-Have Skills and Tools:
Experience with PySpark for advanced data processing.
Familiarity with machine learning concepts.
Knowledge of Delta Live Tables and Workflows for managing data pipelines.
Azure DevOps and Azure Cloud Services experience.
Hands-on experience with REST APIs for integration.
Personal Characteristics:
Creative and analytical mindset to identify innovative solutions and troubleshoot issues effectively.
Curiosity and commitment to continuous learning to stay updated with industry trends.
Strong problem-solving skills to troubleshoot errors and optimize performance.
Adaptability to embrace changing requirements and new technologies.
Strong communication skills to convey complex technical concepts to non-technical stakeholders.
Time management abilities to prioritize tasks and meet deadlines.
Collaboration and teamwork skills to work effectively with diverse teams.
Attention to detail to ensure data accuracy and quality.
Critical thinking to make informed decisions about data engineering strategies and architectures.

Why Join Us?
Small Team, Big Impact: With a team of six, each person plays an integral role in every project, from start to finish.
Skill Development: As part of our team, you’ll be exposed to diverse projects and have plenty of opportunities to develop your skills across all areas of data engineering.
Growth in AI/ML: For those interested, there’s potential to work on AI/ML initiatives that push the boundaries of what’s possible in data.

Benefits

Opportunity to create, grow, and encourage
Apart from a competitive salary pack, there are lots of growth opportunities to meet your personal ambitions
Flexible schedule and life work balance
Responsibility for exciting and challenging projects that have a direct, visible impact on our customers and the industry
Very positive work environment in a dynamic, international, and motivated team
Start-up spirit while being a part of the large international organization with strong values

Karo Healthcare has a Diverse & Inclusive environment. We are looking for qualified candidates irrespective of gender, gender identity, sexual orientation, ethnicity, race, religion, national origin, disability or age.

description:
Overview

The System and Database Administrator is responsible for the effective operation, maintenance, and security of the organization's business intelligence (BI), customer relationship management (CRM), and enterprise resource planning (ERP) systems. This role requires a strong understanding of database administration, system architecture, and data management principles.

The work is carried out in our modern and welcoming office located in the vibrant neighborhood of Vasastan in Stockholm. The office provides a comfortable and inspiring environment for our employees to thrive. You have the option to work hybrid (office first policy).

Responsibilities

Database Administration:

Manage and maintain databases used by BI, CRM, and ERP systems, including database design, optimization, and performance tuning.
Implement data security measures to protect sensitive information.
Perform regular backup and disaster recovery planning.
Design database architectures to accommodate business growth
Plans for increased data volumes and user loads
Troubleshoot database-related issues and resolve problems promptly.

System Administration:

Install, configure, and maintain BI, CRM, and ERP.
Monitor system performance and identify potential bottlenecks.
Ensure system security and compliance with relevant regulations.
Manage user accounts and permissions.
Provide technical support to users and resolve system-related issues.

Data Integration:

Develop and maintain data integration processes to extract, transform, and load data from various sources into BI, CRM, and ERP systems.
Ensure data quality and consistency across systems.

Database development support:

Collaborates with developers to optimize database designs
Ensures best practices for database coding and stored procedures are implemented

Performance and Data Optimization:

Identify and address performance issues in BI, CRM, and ERP systems.
Implement strategies to improve system efficiency, data quality and responsiveness.
Implements solutions for high availability and load balancing
Ensures efficient query performance and data access patterns

Project Management:

Participate in IT projects related to BI, CRM, and ERP systems, including system upgrades, implementations, and migrations.
Assist in project planning, execution, and monitoring.

Cost optimization:

Optimizes database licenses and hardware resources
Implements efficient storage solutions
Reduces operational costs through automation and best practices

Strategic planning:

Aligns database and system architectures with business objectives
Provides technical expertise for decision-making on database technologies
Plans for future technology adoptions and upgrades

Qualifications

Bachelor’s degree in computer science, Information Technology, or a related field.
3+ years of experience in system and database administration, with a focus on BI, CRM, and ERP systems.
Strong knowledge of database management systems (e.g., SQL Server, PostgreSQL, MySQL).
Experience with data warehousing and data integration tools.
Familiarity with BI, CRM, and ERP software (e.g., Qlik sense, Salesforce, Jeeves).
Proficient in SQL query writing, database design, indexing, stored procedure creation and performance tuning.
Excellent problem-solving and troubleshooting skills.
Strong communication and interpersonal skills.

Preferred Skills

Certification in database administration or a relevant IT field.
Experience with scripting languages (e.g., VBA, Python, PowerShell).
Knowledge of cloud computing platforms (e.g., AWS, Azure, GCP).

Experience with data analytics and reporting tools.

Interested?

If you liked what you just read, and believe you are the person that will make us better, do not hesitate to apply.

Please contact recruitment consultant Johan Pfeifer at johan.pfeifer@pfvconsulting.se or call +46 739-230 786 with any questions regarding the position. We are looking forward to hearing from you!

When applying, make it easy for yourself. Add a resume and fill out the required fields, no need to add anything else at this point. We accept applications in both English and Swedish.

description:
Analytics & Data Science

Stockholm, Sweden · Helsinki, Finland

Full-time

Hey, you look like you might be our new People Analytics Manager(SQL)

Analytics & Data Science

Stockholm, Sweden · Helsinki, Finland

Full-time

Together with our amazing People Analytics teammates from DoorDash, we’re looking for an Analytics Manager to lead our small but mighty team of analysts responsible for self-service reporting and deep dives across the People space. The ideal candidate will excel as a “player - coach”, excited to provide functional leadership to the team, provide thought partnership to their stakeholders, and roll up their sleeves to dive into the data themselves.

The role can be based in Finland (preferred), or Sweden. You can work onsite, hybrid, or fully remote from one of the mentioned locations - the work format is up to you

You will work directly with stakeholders across the Wolt people team (as well as the rest of the Wolt business), serving as their thought partner to solve problems and prioritize solutions to big, thorny questions. You will report directly to the US-based Sr. Manager of People Analytics at DoorDash, and will partner closely with them and your US-based peers in Recruiting Analytics and Data Science to lead People Analytics across the globe.

Your daily work will include

• Supervising the day-to-day work of your team of analysts responsible for people analytics, recruiting analytics, and similar.
• Serving as the trusted advisor, thought leader, and representative of the global People Analytics team to your stakeholders across Wolt.
• Leading the development of metrics, reports, dashboards and analyses, putting high-quality insights directly into the hands of your stakeholders.
• Developing a cohesive vision and roadmap together with your peers and partner teams across the globe, including US-based Data Science, People Analytics, Recruiting Analytics, Data Engineering, and People Applications teams.
• Dive into the data, diagnosing data and reporting needs, building new solutions, and providing answers to big, ambiguous, critical problems.

Our humble expectations

• Education: Degree in a quantitatively focused discipline, e.g., experimental psychology, economics, computer science, physics, or similar.
• Strong experience working as an Analyst, BI Developer, Analytics Engineer, Data Scientist, or techy Data Analyst. People/HR Analytics experience is strongly preferred.
• Experience leading small teams with outsized impact.
• Demonstrated experience working with and influencing technical and nontechnical cross-functional peers and stakeholders. This will be a highly visible role within the People Team, and building trust with your colleagues will be critical.
• Tech skills: Python, SQL, R, AWS, and one of the modern BI tools (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, Sigma, or similar). Advanced SQL skills, and ability to write optimized queries for large data sets.
• Subject Matter Expertise: Deep expertise in data visualization and analysis. Some expertise in statistics is preferred (regressions, t-tests). Nice to have: Experience analyzing survey data.
• Since you’ll be taking care of our internal stakeholders, we’re looking for someone who truly enjoys interacting with people on a daily basis. The ability to search for information and ask relevant questions from various teams will be crucial.

Next steps

Why you'll love working with us

The position will be filled as soon as we find the right person, so make sure to apply as soon as you realize you really, really want to join us!

Complex environment with tons of data just waiting to be utilized — you’ll get hands-on experience in working on various TA metrics and topics.

You can choose the ways of working - work onsite, hybrid, or fully remote from one of the locations mentioned above.

You would get to work in a company culture where we take ownership beyond the obvious, do common things uncommonly well, think big but stay humble, do right by people, treat others kindly and justly, and recognize that if we don’t learn, we won’t stay still but fall behind and keep in mind that Luke was Yoda’s greatest achievement. Read more about how we work.

If you are excited about working in a high-growth environment, taking ownership, and being part of an extremely ambitious team, then click below to apply and get the conversation going!

If you have any further questions about the position, you can turn to:

Orsi Kocsis, Senior Talent Acquisition Partner - orsolya.kocsis@wolt.com

Please note that we do not accept applications sent by mail. You should submit your application through our careers website!

  • Tech skills: Python, SQL, R, AWS, and one of the modern BI tools (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, Sigma, or similar). Advanced SQL skills, and ability to write optimized queries for large data sets.
  • Subject Matter Expertise: Deep expertise in data visualization and analysis. Some expertise in statistics is preferred (regressions, t-tests). Nice to have: Experience analyzing survey data.
  • Since you’ll be taking care of our internal stakeholders, we’re looking for someone who truly enjoys interacting with people on a daily basis. The ability to search for information and ask relevant questions from various teams will be crucial.

Next steps

Why you'll love working with us

The position will be filled as soon as we find the right person, so make sure to apply as soon as you realize you really, really want to join us!

  • Complex environment with tons of data just waiting to be utilized — you’ll get hands-on experience in working on various TA metrics and topics.

  • You can choose the ways of working - work onsite, hybrid, or fully remote from one of the locations mentioned above.

  • You would get to work in a company culture where we take ownership beyond the obvious, do common things uncommonly well, think big but stay humble, do right by people, treat others kindly and justly, and recognize that if we don’t learn, we won’t stay still but fall behind and keep in mind that Luke was Yoda’s greatest achievement. Read more about how we work.

If you are excited about working in a high-growth environment, taking ownership, and being part of an extremely ambitious team, then click below to apply and get the conversation going!

If you have any further questions about the position, you can turn to:

Orsi Kocsis, Senior Talent Acquisition Partner - orsolya.kocsis@wolt.com

Please note that we do not accept applications sent by mail. You should submit your application through our careers website!

description:
10% of Europe’s CO₂ emissions are caused by residential heating and energy bills are out of control. Aira is here to change that.

With our intelligent Aira Heat Pump at the heart, we’re making the switch to clean energy-tech easier and more affordable. Helping Europe turn off gas and slashing energy costs one home at a time.

Founded in 2022, and with 800+ employees and counting, Aira is driving the clean energy revolution by providing homes with modern clean energy-tech solutions such as solar power, battery storage solutions and heat pumps. With a state-of-the-art production facility in Poland, an HQ in Stockholm, Sweden, and hubs across the UK, Germany and Italy, Aira is well on track to install clean energy-tech into 5 million homes by 2034.

About the role

We're on the lookout for a Tech Lead / Rust developer to join our team and play a pivotal role in bridging the gap between our low-level code and cloud infrastructure. As part of our dynamic Engagement team, you'll be at the forefront of shaping the customer journey post-purchase, ensuring that our clients receive the best possible experience with our products.

You'll be working at the intersection of embedded systems and cloud computing, driving the design and development of software that facilitates seamless communication and data transfer between our devices and cloud-based applications. Collaborating closely with your colleagues, you'll define software requirements, craft design specifications, and lead the charge in Rust development within our organization.

What sets this role apart is the opportunity to make a significant impact on our development processes and product offerings. You'll have the autonomy to set the framework for Rust development activities and provide guidance to fellow developers, empowering them to excel in their operational tasks.

What you’ll be doing

Design and develop embedded systems software using Rust and related tools, including pipelines, testing, and automation.
Collaborate with other developers, including hardware engineers, software developers, and cloud engineers, to ensure seamless integration between different layers of the system.

What you bring to the team

Solid background in software development, ideally acquired within a product-focused company or scale-up environment
Commercial experience with Rust and Linux
Understanding of how IoT and wireless devices can be connected

Nice to have

Experience working with IoT, Bluetooth, and wireless devices
Experience with Kotlin and Python
Knowledge of databases (Redis, MongoDB)
DevOps understanding; maintaining own code (AWS)
MQTT experience

What is in it for you?

Gain hands-on experience in a fast-growing scale-up, with a supportive and inclusive culture, and career advancement opportunities.
Collaborate with diverse teams across international markets and launch products globally.
Develop and grow personally and professionally in an entrepreneurial-minded environment.
Thrive in a dynamic, solution-oriented culture, tackling challenges and driving meaningful solutions that make a positive impact on the world.
Influence the company's success, with a visible impact on product development and market growth.
Enjoy the flexibility of our hybrid work model and discover our brand-new office at Norra Stationsgatan 93 in Stockholm. Conveniently located near public transport, with Sankt Eriksplan and Odenplan stations just a few minutes walk away

At Aira, we champion next-generation energy as well as diversity and inclusion. We firmly believe that a diverse workforce fosters innovation and creativity, enhancing our ability to serve customers and communities effectively. We welcome individuals from all backgrounds, cultures and perspectives to join our team. Our commitment is to uphold equality and inclusivity, fostering a collaborative environment where everyone can thrive and contribute to a better future for our people and the planet.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Jira Developer / Atlassian Engineer

Location: Stockholm (Remote-Friendly)
Start Date: ASAP

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Jira Developer / Atlassian Engineer

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

As a Jira Developer / Atlassian Engineer, you’ll work closely with stakeholders to develop, streamline, and maintain custom Jira solutions. Your expertise in ScriptRunner and Jira Query Language (JQL) will be essential as you support our client’s mission-critical project management environment. Experience with Jira Software Cloud, Jira Service Management, and Confluence is required, while OpsGenie experience is a valuable plus.

Key Responsibilities:

If you’re ready to leverage your ScriptRunner and JQL expertise on impactful projects, we’d love to connect with you!

Custom Development: Design and configure custom workflows, fields, screens, permissions, and notifications within Jira, focusing on ScriptRunner.
Automation & Efficiency: Use ScriptRunner and JQL to automate processes, build custom reports, and create tailored dashboards to optimize performance.
Collaborative Problem Solving: Engage with teams to understand requirements, troubleshoot issues, and implement scalable solutions that support dynamic projects.
Documentation & Training: Develop comprehensive documentation and deliver training sessions to foster efficient tool usage and adoption.
Integration Management: Integrate Jira with Confluence, OpsGenie, and other tools to support seamless cross-functional collaboration.

Requirements:

Experience: 5+ years as a Jira Developer or Atlassian Engineer, with a strong focus on ScriptRunner and JQL.
Technical Skills: Extensive knowledge of Jira Software Cloud, Jira Service Management, Confluence, and (ideally) OpsGenie.
Analytical Mindset: Strong problem-solving skills and a keen eye for detail in optimizing workflows and processes.
Communication: Ability to work effectively with diverse teams and simplify complex technical concepts for non-technical stakeholders.

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at sandhya@vipas.se

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

description:
Ready to Lead the Future of Content Management?

At Paligo, we’re not just producing content—we’re redefining how the world’s leading companies create, manage, and deliver technical documentation. As a globally leading Component Content Management System (CCMS), Paligo is transforming traditional Content Management and the way technical information is crafted, organized, and accessed by major organizations like Bitdefender, Bluetooth, Mitsubishi, the European Commission, Wrike, Alteryx, and many more.

As a Team Lead for one of our engineering team consisting of 5-6 developers, you’ll be part of our engineering organisation at our headquarters in Solna, Stockholm, reporting directly to the VP of Engineering. Paligo is a global company with clients and teams spread across different locations, but our engineering team is primarily based in Solna, where we prioritize in-office collaboration. We embrace a hybrid working model, allowing for regular in-office meetings while offering flexibility for remote work when needed. However, the heart of our teamwork happens in Stockholm.

We’re on a mission to become the #1 solution in our industry, and we’re looking for a dynamic Team Manager who’s ready to help us scale to new heights. If you love leading top-notch engineering teams, solving complex challenges, and setting trends in the world of SaaS, this role is for you!

What You’ll Do:

- Lead and inspire a team of engineers to follow best-in-class development practices.

- Work closely with the code through hands-on coding, code review and design discussions.

- Partner with the Product Owner and stakeholders to launch stable, high-quality releases that keep Paligo ahead of the curve.

- Bridge the gap between teams, ensuring seamless communication and a united focus on our goals.

- Prioritize technical and customer needs to keep us laser-focused on delivering exceptional value.

- Cultivate a learning environment where knowledge is shared, collaboration thrives, and the team grows stronger together.

- Shape the future of your team by driving personalized growth plans, setting meaningful goals, and leading engaging 1-1s and dev talks.

- Own the Scrum process and guide the team through successful sprints, making every review count.

- Attract and retain top engineering talent, keeping Paligo at the forefront of innovation.

What We’re Looking For:

- An enthusiastic leader who thrives in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.

- Someone passionate about pushing boundaries and keeping the customer at the heart of every decision.

- An expert communicator who can seamlessly collaborate across teams and departments.

- 5 years hands-on web development experience.

- Experience with technologies like PHP, TypeScript, Python, Vue, AWS, Docker.

- A natural mentor with a knack for developing and inspiring high-performing teams.

- Experience in agile software development environments.

- Background in improving best practices and processes across development teams on a continuing basis.

- Bachelor’s or Master's degree in Computer Science, related technical field, or equivalent practical experience.

- Experience managing both onsite and remote engineers.

Why You’ll Love Working at Paligo:

- You’ll be at the cutting edge of SaaS and CCMS innovation, working alongside industry leaders and trendsetters.

- We’re transitioning from a startup to a scale-up, and your contributions will shape the future of our company.

- A customer-first mindset drives everything we do—so you’ll directly impact the success of our global clients.

- We believe in open communication, collaboration, and a fun, healthy work culture that celebrates diversity and inclusion.

- Our fast-growing, dynamic environment offers endless opportunities for growth and development.

- We recently moved into brand new modern offices within walking distance of transit and lunch destinations.

- We have great employee perks, including an annual Wellness contribution, Professional Development budget, Home office contribution, and Parental pay.

Who We Are:

At Paligo, we’re disrupting the CCMS landscape with our cloud-based platform that helps the world’s biggest brands manage technical, knowledge, and product documentation like never before. Our clients span industries and geographies, but they all have one thing in common: they trust Paligo to deliver the future of content management.

Join Us in Making History

If you’re ready to lead a talented team of engineers and contribute to something truly game-changing, we’d love to hear from you! Curious about our culture and values? Check out our careers page here and get a feel for what it’s like to be part of the Paligo community.
