description:
Job Description

Embedded SW Tester within R&D - Stockholm

Your Role as an Embedded Tester/Test Developer:
You will work on assignments with our market-leading, mainly but not exclusively within the Automotive Industry, and be at the forefront of embedded testing, verification and validation.

Main responsibilities can include the following tasks:
• Review system or functional requirements
• Receive and test different SW release candidates
• Construct and run different test cases (PyTest, Python, C/C++ or MATLAB Simulink)
• Perform embedded testing, verification and validation in workbench or in HIL rigs
• Write and run different unit tests or other testcases (Python for scripting, automation, and testing to streamline development processes).
• Previously worked with both manual and automated testing, with e.g. GitLab’s, Jenkins or Selenium.
• Write documentations.

Your Profile
You have a Bachelor’s or Master of Science in Electronics, Mechatronics or Software, and have worked your way up in testing and verification of embedded systems for several years. You understand electronics, HIL rigs, and embedded development.
This allows you to communicate with parallel teams unhindered.
If you currently work as a senior tester, you enjoy working hands-on with verification and are used to training and supporting colleagues with new tools and applications.

To be successful in this role, we are looking for an individual who has:
• At least 4 years of proven experience in testing embedded domains.
• Experienced with constructing test cases.
• Experience with hardware-related programming and debugging, including JTAG and other debugging tools.
• You have experience in test framework development with PyTest
• Experience with version control systems such as Git and continuous integration/continuous delivery (CI/CD) pipelines.
• Excellent writing and verbal English skills
• Bachelor’s degree in relevant field

Strongly Meritorious:
• MATLAB and Simulink Experience
• ISTQB Certification
• Proven Test leader

Meritorious:
• Testing on a System Level.
• Basic understanding of C, C++
• Experience in DSPACE, JTAG
• Understanding of ASPICE or ISO 26262.
• Experience from Electrical Vehicles
• Familiarity with Automotive communication protocols such as CAN, LIN, and Ethernet.
• Experience of the consultant role in a European country
• Spoken and written Swedish

Application and Contact
Selection and interviews are running continuously. Apply now to join our team and make a meaningful impact in the automotive industry.
For questions and for more information contact Jan Hansson, Talent Acquisition Partner, 0725-616900

Kindly note that due to GDPR, we will not accept applications via mail. Please use our career site.

We kindly but firmly refrain from direct contact with staffing, brokerage, and recruitment companies as well as other external actors and sellers of additional job advertisements.

description:
Do you want to be at the forefront of protecting our society against cyber threats? We are looking for an Application Security Engineer to team up with a passionate team of cyber specialists in our Secure Development domain.

Secure Development

Applications and custom solutions are currently popular targets for threat actors. In modern application development, security must be present throughout all aspects of the development process. Our engagements span from AppSec-related security workshops, educating organizations in secure coding and DevSecOps, to longer assignments where we write code responsibly as integrated team members. We are a cyber tech company with our own custom software and services that we leverage both during assignments and with our clients.

The Role

At Truesec, you'll have the opportunity to work with a variety of customers and their development organizations, providing technical solutions to help them improve their security, based on their needs and current circumstances. Your tasks may include assessing proposed or existing systems for security vulnerabilities, conducting code reviews to identify potential issues, and helping clients develop more secure development processes. A big part in what you will do is advising and educating customers on risk.

You'll also have the chance to engage in threat modeling exercises, which involve analyzing systems to identify potential security threats and developing strategies to mitigate them. In addition, you may participate in workshops and training sessions to help clients improve their security posture and ensure they are up-to-date on the latest techniques and best practices.

To ensure that you are well-equipped to handle these challenges, we provide ongoing training and support, including opportunities for continuous learning during work hours and attendance at industry conferences. Whether you are working independently or in a team, you'll have the technical expertise and resources necessary to help our clients develop more secure and resilient systems.

Your Potential Background

Application security is a broad area that encompasses a range of skills and expertise, and the right candidate for us could come from a variety of different backgrounds. If you are an application security engineer, you may have experience in threat modelling, vulnerability assessment, code review, or secure software development. You likely understand the importance of building security into the software development life cycle and are well-versed in industry-standard methodologies.

On the other hand, if you are a a developer with a keen interest in security, you might have experience implementing secure coding practices such as input validation, access control, and cryptography. You could also have experience with web application firewalls or other security technologies.

If you are a penetration tester, you probably have a talent for finding weaknesses in systems and exploiting them to show their impact on business operations. You might also be interested in vulnerabilities and vulnerability research.

Finally, if you are an information security professional with an interest in the secure software development life cycle (SSDLC), you may have experience designing and implementing security policies, procedures, and controls that support the development of secure software.

In short, we believe your previous experience could include:
• DevSecOps and secure coding practices.
• Software architecture and design.
• Programming skills in one or more languages, preferably within either Java, C#, C/C++, Python, JavaScript, or Go.

If you have experience in any of the following, we will consider it a bonus:
• Cryptography/Authentication/Authorization.
• OAuth 2/OpenID Connect/JWT.
• Distributed systems/Docker/Kubernetes.
• AWS, Azure, or GCP.
• Threat modeling and security assessments of code.
• Penetration testing.
• SAST/DAST tools.
• Vulnerability management.

Application security is a broad area and we know that even if you have a different background than the ones mentioned you could fit right in, so don't hesitate to apply.

About Truesec – A Leading Cybersecurity Company

Since 2005, Truesec has been a native cybersecurity company, driven by one single purpose: Creating safety and sustainability in a digital world by preventing cyber breach and minimizing impact.

Over the years, we’ve earned the trust of organizations worldwide and gained a strong reputation internationally. Our team consists of dedicated specialists covering the entire spectrum of cybersecurity – with capabilities in Predict, Prevent, Protect, Respond, and Recover.

Today, we employ around 350 employees – and as cybercrime grows, we need to grow. To support that goal, we are now looking for a Security Application Engineer who wants to make a difference.

Join Our Mission Toward a Safe Digital Future

If you truly want to make a difference and make our world a little bit safer, this is the place for you. At Truesec, you'll get to be at the forefront of fighting cybercrime instead of reading about it in the news. This is your chance to be part of an exciting journey in a leading cybersecurity company - and learn from some of the best in their field.

Our assignments involve handling sensitive information, which is why we're looking for candidates who either hold Swedish citizenship or have a valid Swedish work permit

So, are you ready to team up with the most dedicated team of experts and be part of a meaningful mission? Then we are excited to get to know you!
descriptionHTML:
Do you want to be at the forefront of protecting our society against cyber threats? We are looking for an Application Security Engineer to team up with a passionate team of cyber specialists in our Secure Development domain.


Secure Development

Applications and custom solutions are currently popular targets for threat actors. In modern application development, security must be present throughout all aspects of the development process. Our engagements span from AppSec-related security workshops, educating organizations in secure coding and DevSecOps, to longer assignments where we write code responsibly as integrated team members. We are a cyber tech company with our own custom software and services that we leverage both during assignments and with our clients.

The Role

At Truesec, you'll have the opportunity to work with a variety of customers and their development organizations, providing technical solutions to help them improve their security, based on their needs and current circumstances. Your tasks may include assessing proposed or existing systems for security vulnerabilities, conducting code reviews to identify potential issues, and helping clients develop more secure development processes. A big part in what you will do is advising and educating customers on risk.

You'll also have the chance to engage in threat modeling exercises, which involve analyzing systems to identify potential security threats and developing strategies to mitigate them. In addition, you may participate in workshops and training sessions to help clients improve their security posture and ensure they are up-to-date on the latest techniques and best practices.

To ensure that you are well-equipped to handle these challenges, we provide ongoing training and support, including opportunities for continuous learning during work hours and attendance at industry conferences. Whether you are working independently or in a team, you'll have the technical expertise and resources necessary to help our clients develop more secure and resilient systems.


Your Potential Background

Application security is a broad area that encompasses a range of skills and expertise, and the right candidate for us could come from a variety of different backgrounds. If you are an application security engineer, you may have experience in threat modelling, vulnerability assessment, code review, or secure software development. You likely understand the importance of building security into the software development life cycle and are well-versed in industry-standard methodologies.

On the other hand, if you are a a developer with a keen interest in security, you might have experience implementing secure coding practices such as input validation, access control, and cryptography. You could also have experience with web application firewalls or other security technologies.

If you are a penetration tester, you probably have a talent for finding weaknesses in systems and exploiting them to show their impact on business operations. You might also be interested in vulnerabilities and vulnerability research.

Finally, if you are an information security professional with an interest in the secure software development life cycle (SSDLC), you may have experience designing and implementing security policies, procedures, and controls that support the development of secure software.

In short, we believe your previous experience could include:
  • DevSecOps and secure coding practices.
  • Software architecture and design.
  • Programming skills in one or more languages, preferably within either Java, C#, C/C++, Python, JavaScript, or Go.

If you have experience in any of the following, we will consider it a bonus:
  • Cryptography/Authentication/Authorization.
  • OAuth 2/OpenID Connect/JWT.
  • Distributed systems/Docker/Kubernetes.
  • AWS, Azure, or GCP.
  • Threat modeling and security assessments of code.
  • Penetration testing.
  • SAST/DAST tools.
  • Vulnerability management.

Application security is a broad area and we know that even if you have a different background than the ones mentioned you could fit right in, so don't hesitate to apply.

description:
Welcome to Homevolt – a cutting-edge joint venture between Tibber and Polarium, dedicated to revolutionizing the energy storage landscape. At Polarium, we're renowned for disrupting the energy storage industry, setting the gold standard in quality engineering, efficiency, security, and circular manufacturing of energy storage hardware. Meanwhile, Tibber is leading the charge in transforming consumer energy usage with top-notch user control, transparency, and smart software solutions. We've excelled in driving the market toward a more sustainable and intelligent future.

In this era of transformative change, the energy market is undergoing a seismic shift, presenting challenges and opportunities. As the world adapts to soaring energy prices and uncertain times, the public and the market are poised to invest in a brighter future.

Enter Homevolt – our answer to a new era of home energy storage. A groundbreaking consumer battery developed in collaboration with Polarium and Tibber, Homevolt brings energy storage to the masses, offering unprecedented flexibility for the entire grid. This marks the next significant step in our shared journey towards electrification. By seamlessly integrating cutting-edge battery technology with state-of-the-art energy-managing software, Homevolt is not just a battery; it's a system that truly understands and adapts to your home's energy needs.

Join Us on this Exciting Journey!

As a Backend Developer in the Homevolt Team, you'll be at the forefront of driving change and innovation.

Your mission includes:

Building and maintaining device integrations. This will be for our own and our partner's hardware.

Implementing backend logic. This is to be done for Homevolt and it’s integrations with app and firmware.

Collaboration and improving ways of working. Contributing to general architecture, best practices, and engineering culture at Homevolt.

Qualifications and Experiences:

Tech expertise. Comfortable designing and maintaining software in technologies like .NET (8.0) and Python (These are the technologies you will be working with).

Microservices experience. Knowledgeable with microservices architecture in high throughput cloud environments. Preferably AWS.

Meritorious experience. Knowing some of these technologies is useful in this role. Microsoft Orleans, REST, GraphQL, Terraform, Docker, AMQP, Kubernetes, Typescript, Javascript or Flutter.

Relevant experience. Experience with IoT or any device integration is a huge plus for this role.

Industry expertise. Understanding of the energy or battery industry is a bonus.

Culturally in sync. Curious and collaborative mindset with a bold yet humble approach to engineering.

Get Ready For:

Be a part of a European high-performing team from scratch that can become a leading player in Europe innovation. A way to change the landscape of one of the most important industries on the planet

Growth. A possibility to learn a lot and push the barriers of what you think is possible, with the possibility to grow personally and professionally

Autonomy. An autonomous and humble culture in a scale-up adventure

Empowerment. Your voice matters, we are a place to work where laughter and support amongst diverse and inclusive colleagues are guaranteed

Flexible benefits. Whether this is towards health, wellness, equipment, or other allowances important to you, we will do our best to accommodate your needs

At Tibber, we are committed to hiring, developing, and retaining exceptional people regardless of race, color, religion, sex, sexual orientation, age, marital status, disability, neurodiversity, or gender identity. We strongly encourage people from underrepresented groups to apply.

description:
Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Embedded Software Developer.

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

We are seeking an experienced Embedded Software Developer (Level 3) to join our dynamic team of 7-8 developers. In this role, you will be responsible for developing and maintaining embedded systems software using C and C++. You will work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure the delivery of high-quality solutions within tight deadlines. Your ability to communicate effectively and collaborate in a group setting is essential, as is your fluency in Swedish.

Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and maintain embedded software using C/C++ for embedded systems.
Collaborate with the team to define requirements and ensure robust software solutions.
Participate in code reviews, debugging, and testing to ensure the highest level of quality and performance.
Use development tools such as Git and Artifactory to manage version control and artifacts.
Troubleshoot and resolve issues in embedded software in a timely manner.
Adhere to project timelines and milestones while maintaining clear communication with team members.

Required Qualifications:

3-5 years of experience in embedded software development, specifically using C/C++.
Experience working with tools such as Git and Artifactory for version control and artifact management.
Proven ability to work effectively in a collaborative team environment.
Fluent in Swedish, both written and verbal.
Swedish citizenship, as the assignment may be covered by defense secrecy and require security clearance.

Meritorious Qualifications:

Experience with VxWorks or other real-time operating systems (RTOS).
Previous experience in radio systems, the defense industry, or working within our company.

Additional Information:

The assignment is subject to approval of a security clearance by the appropriate authority, and only candidates with Swedish citizenship can be considered.

If you are a proactive, skilled developer with a passion for embedded systems and enjoy working in a team-oriented environment, we encourage you to apply for this exciting opportunity.

#CProgramming #C++ #EmbeddedSystems #RealTimeOperatingSystems #TechJobs #SwedishJobs #StockholmJobs #SecurityClearance #DefenseIndustry #TechCareers

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at swathi.hr@vipas.se &contact me at +46764341371/+46 739803973

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

description:
Job Description

Embedded SW Developer within R&D - Stockholm

Are you a skilled embedded software developer or proven tester with a passion, mainly but not exclusively, within the Automotive Industry?
Then, join our dynamic team and become a driving force behind cutting-edge automotive technology!

Here you can find:
• Innovative Projects: Dive into exciting projects at the forefront of Automotive development, shaping the future of mobility.
• Top-Notch Tools : Access the latest tools and technologies, empowering you to excel in your craft.
• Collaborative Environment: Work alongside a talented team of professionals, collaborating seamlessly to conquer challenges and achieve excellence.
• Continuous Growth: Fuel your passion for learning with ongoing training and development opportunities.
• Impactful Work: Make a meaningful impact by contributing to the creation of safe, reliable, and innovative automotive solutions that touch lives globally.

Your Role as an Embedded Software Developer :
You will focus on developing embedded software, mainly but not exclusively within the Automotive Industry.

Main responsibilities can include the following tasks :
• Developing software using C and C++ programming languages.
• Use MATLAB and Simulink for modeling and potentially generate C code.
• Write unit tests or other testcases (Python)
• Working with real-time operating systems (RTOS) and embedded Linux or other embedded operating systems.
• Debugging hardware-related programming issues using tools such as JTAG.
• Utilizing version control systems such as Git and CI/CD pipelines.

Your Profile
To be successful in this role, we are looking for an individual who has:
• At least 5 years of experience with embedded programming in C/C++.
• Experienced in MATLAB and Simulink
• Experience with hardware-related programming and debugging, including JTAG and other debugging tools.
• Knowledge of real-time operating systems (RTOS) and experience with embedded Linux or other embedded operating systems.
• Experience with version control systems such as Git and continuous integration/continuous delivery (CI/CD) pipelines.
• Excellent writing and verbal English skills
• Bachelor’s or Master degree in relevant field

Meritorious:
• Experience from Electrical Vehicles
• Experience from Driveline Control Systems
• Experience from Engine Control Modules and Combustion Engines
• Experience from Powertrains
• Understanding of Automotive software development processes, such as Automotive SPICE or ISO 26262.
• Familiarity with Automotive communication protocols such as CAN, LIN, and Ethernet.
• Experience of the consultant role in a European country
• Spoken and written Swedish is meritorious.

Application and Contact
Selection and interviews are running continuously. Apply now to join our team and make a meaningful impact in the automotive industry.
For questions and for more information contact Jan Hansson, Talent Acquisition Partner, 0725-616900

Kindly note that due to GDPR, we will not accept applications via mail. Please use our career site.

We kindly but firmly refrain from direct contact with staffing, brokerage, and recruitment companies as well as other external actors and sellers of additional job advertisements.

#LI-JH6

positionName: Embedded SW Developer within R&D - Stockholm

description:
Minimum qualifications:

• Bachelor’s degree or equivalent practical experience.
• 1 year of experience with software development in one or more programming languages (e.g., Python, C, C++, Java, JavaScript).
• 1 year of experience with data structures or algorithms.

Preferred qualifications:

• Experience working with web/mobile application development, Unix/Linux environments, distributed and parallel systems, machine learning, information retrieval, natural language processing, networking, or similar.
• Experience developing accessible technologies.
• Excellent problem solving skills.

About the job

Google's software engineers develop the next-generation technologies that change how billions of users connect, explore, and interact with information and one another. Our products need to handle information at massive scale, and extend well beyond web search. We're looking for engineers who bring fresh ideas from all areas, including information retrieval, distributed computing, large-scale system design, networking and data storage, security, artificial intelligence, natural language processing, UI design and mobile; the list goes on and is growing every day. As a software engineer, you will work on a specific project critical to Google’s needs with opportunities to switch teams and projects as you and our fast-paced business grow and evolve. We need our engineers to be versatile, display leadership qualities and be enthusiastic to take on new problems across the full-stack as we continue to push technology forward.
Google Cloud accelerates every organization’s ability to digitally transform its business and industry. We deliver enterprise-grade solutions that leverage Google’s cutting-edge technology, and tools that help developers build more sustainably. Customers in more than 200 countries and territories turn to Google Cloud as their trusted partner to enable growth and solve their most critical business problems.

Responsibilities

• Write product or system development code.
• Review code developed by other developers and provide feedback to ensure best practices (e.g., style guidelines, checking code in, accuracy, testability, and efficiency).
• Contribute to existing documentation or educational content and adapt content based on product/program updates and user feedback.
• Triage product or system issues and debug/track/resolve by analyzing the sources of issues and the impact on hardware, network, or service operations and quality.
• Develop infrastructure that supports Meet's need for cloud-side audio and video processing.

Google is proud to be an equal opportunity workplace and is an affirmative action employer. We are committed to equal employment opportunity regardless of race, color, ancestry, religion, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, age, citizenship, marital status, disability, gender identity or Veteran status. We also consider qualified applicants regardless of criminal histories, consistent with legal requirements. See alsoGoogle's EEO Policy andEEO is the Law. If you have a disability or special need that requires accommodation, please let us know by completing ourAccommodations for Applicants form.

positionName: Software Engineer II, Backend, Meet Media

description:
Grow with us

About this opportunity:

Hardware Engineering strives to be the most competitive Radio Network R&D unit in the industry. We work in an agile set-up to develop and maintain competitive, high-quality Radio products which give our customer solutions securing future growth.

Control Software is part of the Hardware Engineering (EU HW) Radio within Business Area Networks (BNEW). We are based in Kista, Stockholm. We also have a close corporation with development of PEU Radio products in Ottawa, Beijing, Nanjing, Chengdu, Lund and Zagreb.

Control Software provides possibility to work with the latest technology within telecommunication development. We can offer a rich number of opportunities in an everyday learning, creative and challenging atmosphere where Kista, Stockholm, is our base but the world is our arena.

We provide the SW platform for radio products also known as the auxiliary control system (XCS). We organize in cross functional development teams, and we are involved in several activities at the same time. We are in an intense phase, due to 5G development, with many new products in the pipeline. There is a high pressure on quality, flexibility and understanding of HW and SW. It also means working with skilled colleagues in an inspiring environment.

We are now looking for a Developer to develop the auxiliary control system (XCS) for radio. Your role will include system design, SW design, trouble shooting in target environment and product documentation. Knowledge about Linux and SW close to HW is of high value.

Team has the end-to-end responsibility for developing and maintaining our Production System loops which are used for quality assurance, building, and delivering XCS products.

What you will do:

You will drive strategic technical leadership
 Develop and test high quality products
 Perform trouble shooting internally and on customer networks as well as handling customer support in general
 Drive continuous improvements of products and processes
 Develop competence in technical domain
 Execute continuous improvements of products and processes, bring up new SW platforms
You will be given a more specific area of responsibility after becoming productive, and depending of interest

The skills you bring:

Education: MSc in engineering or similar
 Min years of experience: 5 years of relevant experience

descriptionHTML:
Grow with us

About this opportunity:


Hardware Engineering strives to be the most competitive Radio Network R&D unit in the industry. We work in an agile set-up to develop and maintain competitive, high-quality Radio products which give our customer solutions securing future growth.

Control Software is part of the Hardware Engineering (EU HW) Radio within Business Area Networks (BNEW). We are based in Kista, Stockholm. We also have a close corporation with development of PEU Radio products in Ottawa, Beijing, Nanjing, Chengdu, Lund and Zagreb.

Control Software provides possibility to work with the latest technology within telecommunication development. We can offer a rich number of opportunities in an everyday learning, creative and challenging atmosphere where Kista, Stockholm, is our base but the world is our arena.

We provide the SW platform for radio products also known as the auxiliary control system (XCS). We organize in cross functional development teams, and we are involved in several activities at the same time. We are in an intense phase, due to 5G development, with many new products in the pipeline. There is a high pressure on quality, flexibility and understanding of HW and SW. It also means working with skilled colleagues in an inspiring environment.

We are now looking for a Developer to develop the auxiliary control system (XCS) for radio. Your role will include system design, SW design, trouble shooting in target environment and product documentation. Knowledge about Linux and SW close to HW is of high value.

Team has the end-to-end responsibility for developing and maintaining our Production System loops which are used for quality assurance, building, and delivering XCS products.


What you will do:


  • You will drive strategic technical leadership
  • Develop and test high quality products
  • Perform trouble shooting internally and on customer networks as well as handling customer support in general
  • Drive continuous improvements of products and processes
  • Develop competence in technical domain
  • Execute continuous improvements of products and processes, bring up new SW platforms
  • You will be given a more specific area of responsibility after becoming productive, and depending of interest


The skills you bring:


  • Education: MSc in engineering or similar
  • Min years of experience: 5 years of relevant experience
  • Domain experience: Linux and SW close to HW, systemization and trouble shooting, ASIC knowledge is benificial
  • Experience from SW development in a Linux environment using e.g. GIT, Gerrit, Junit, Jenkins, Nexus, Bash/Shell, Artifactory
  • Several years of experience working with C/C++ in an embedded environment
  • Experience from designing and executing automated test scripts in Java, Python or similar.

description:
Why VNTRS?

By joining VNTRS, you'll be part of an environment that values innovation, partnership, and shared success. We offer significant growth opportunities and the chance to be at the forefront of technological advancements in a collaborative and dynamic setting.

Our mission is to transform innovative ideas into successful companies. Unlike typical consultants, we are hands-on partners sharing both risks and successes with our clients. With a dedicated team of over 40 experts in Stockholm, Tallinn, and Helsinki, we are looking to expand our technical prowess by adding a skilled ML Backend developer to spearhead our development projects and contribute to our technological strategy.

About the Role:

We are looking for a senior Backend developer with experience in Machine learning and DevOps practices.

As our ML/AI Backend Developer, you'll play a crucial role in guiding our organization through the fast-changing AI landscape. Working within our Tech Forum, you will collaborate with a dynamic group of more than 20 professionals, including full-stack developers, DevOps engineers, and architects.

Location:

Stockholm - Hybrid/on-site, not fully remote.

Key Responsibilities:

- Design, develop, and implement backend solutions that leverage existing ML/AI technologies to address business problems and enhance product capabilities.

- Actively contribute to the VNTRS Tech Forum by sharing ML/AI insights, setting technical standards, and participating in strategic planning

- Work closely with the Head of Tech to align AI initiatives with company objectives

- Lead software development projects, integrating and utilizing existing ML/AI technologies.

- Collaborate with cross-functional teams to integrate AI solutions into existing products and workflows

- Represent VNTRS at industry events, showcasing our AI capabilities and fostering connections in the ML community

Qualifications:

- Minimum 5 years of professional experience within software development

- Fluent in Swedish and English

- Excellent problem-solving skills

- Strong technical background with some knowledge in machine learning, deep learning, and AI technologies

- Strong proficiency in backend development, specifically in Python (Django)

- Experience with DevOps practices

- Experience working with end-to-end solutions

- Experience working with databases such as SQL, NoSQL or Vector DBs

- Previous experience in a technical consulting role

- Familiarity with big data technologies

- Familiarity with cloud-based ML services such as AWS, Azure or GCP

- Strong communication skills

- Ability to work in a fast-paced, innovative environment

- Ability to explain and reason ML concepts to both technical and non-technical stakeholders

Meritorious:

- Experience with ML frameworks such as TensorFlow, PyTorch, or Scikit-learn

- Familiarity with MLOps tools for model deployment and monitoring

- Previous experience in a senior position within a tech startup or scaleup

Application:

If you're ready to play a key role in VNTRS's tech revolution, we want to hear from you. Apply now to contribute to the future success of VNTRS and our clients.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Senior C++ Server Developer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Senior C++ Server Developer

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

On behalf of one of our customers, we are looking for a Senior C++ Server Developer to join their organization.

This assignment is on-site in Lund and will start as soon as possible with long-term potential. We are reviewing candidates continuously.

Key Responsibilities:

• Participate in requirements analysis.

• Design, build, and maintain efficient, secure, reusable, and reliable code.

• Ensure the best possible performance, quality, and responsiveness of applications.

• Identify bottlenecks and bugs and devise solutions to mitigate and address these issues.

• Help maintain code quality, organization, and automation.

Requirements:

-Min 5 years of C++ server-side development experience.
-Solid understanding of object-oriented Design & Analysis.
-Solid experience of writing modular code that is clear, testable and maintainable.
-Familiar with various design and architectural patterns.
-Familiar with Test Driven Development, continuous integration and agile software best practices.
-Strong experience in debugging, profiling and optimizing code.
-Strong analytic capabilities.
-Experience in algorithms and time complexity.
-Bachelor’s degree or higher in software engineering.
-Good verbal and written English communication skills.
-Strong team player and a good communicator.

Desired skills and experiences:

-Operating systems in general, Linux in particular.
-SQL and databases.
-Python.
-Network and communication (TCP/IP)
-Open source usage.
-Cyber security.
-Container technologies (Kubernetes, Docker).

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at- sandhya@vipas.se

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

positionName: Dotnet Backend Developer with Azure DevOps

description:
OFFER

Net Insight offers the possibility to work hands-on with cutting-edge technology and products used by millions. Together in a close-knit team with colleagues who share a passion for delivering top-quality products, you have the chance to enable reliable live experiences for a global and diverse audience.

You will be part of an international and friendly working environment. The teams are cross-functional and individuals as well as teams are encouraged to have open communication and collaboration across their functions - creating the best possible result.

Some of the benefits of working at Net Insight:

Net Insight is a world leader in media networks and resource optimization with a strong focus on innovation
Flexibility to impact the development environment and use the latest tools.
Open and flat organization and good culture with a lot of teamwork
Unusually low turnover - High employee satisfaction!
Run a very technologically advanced environment
An open culture where everyone can drive changes and influence how we work.
Family-friendly company and a great understanding of pick-up/drop-off
Flexible working hours. You mainly report to your team.

About the role:
You will be part of a team focusing on their algorithm for time synchronization. It is about using different time sources (atomic clock, PPS, GNSS, PPT, measurement of round trip times in the network) to be able to calculate the time at the nanosecond level in their nodes.

Some short notes from the team:

We work with precise networked time synchronization. Think NTP, but four orders of magnitude better.
We use C++ 20 and Python for various tasks like test execution and glue scripts.
We take code review very seriously, not only to catch bugs but most importantly to share knowledge within the team. We sometimes do pair programming.
Interacting with other teams and team members is crucial for success.

Net Insight’s initiates a large development project within their new business area, 5G Synchronization. In this role, you will work in a team with other senior developers to further develop and improve our unique solution for transporting time with extremely high precision over IP infrastructure.

Together with people who are passionate about technology, you will work in an environment that spans the entire range, from hardware development to cloud applications - and everything in between.

YOUR PROFILE
The team structure demands a more flexible/entrepreneurial way of working. Thus, a high degree of independence and initiative is required for the role.

Net Insight wishes to work with skilled engineers who are open to learning new things, and value working in a team to achieve a common goal. Therefore it is also good if you have great communication and organizational skills.

We think you are an experienced and socially driven person who is used to working in close collaboration with other developers in agile teams; from system architecture, specification, and implementation of algorithms and functions to testing and verification.

Seen to the technical elements of the role, you need to have:

Good knowledge of modern C++ (14/17/20
Experience with network communication and protocols
RAII and other best practices
Comfortable with driving design and technology
Good knowledge of Linux and systems with real-time requirement
Git, Jira, Jenkins, GitLab, CI or Linux
Agile working methods such as scrum, TDD, and continuous integration

It is an advantage if you have experience in some of the following:

Automatic control (PI/PID, MPC, Kalman filter)

Graph theory
Signal processing
Statistics
Optimization (in the mathematical sense)
Automatic control
Basic cryptography (TLS certs, AES)

ABOUT NET INSIGHT
Net Insight is a global leader in media networks, resource optimization, and streaming solutions. With more than 20 years of experience, Net Insight is a trusted and important partner and a leading force in the media tech industry in creating a better media experience.

More than 500 world-class customers run mission-critical media services using Net Insight’s solutions in more than 60 countries worldwide. Net Insight is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm.

Net Insight is powering the evolving media business in a connected world where technology enables seamless meetings between producers, distributors, and consumers of content – regardless of geographical location, technical resources, or distribution network. With its deep market knowledge and insight, genuine customer focus, and world-leading innovative technology, Net Insight makes it easier to create and deliver better content more reliably and effectively. Net Insight is driven by the idea that everything can always be done smarter, for both for customers and consumers.

For more info, visit https://netinsight.net/

ABOUT PINETREE

At Pinetree, we have a vision and mission to differentiate ourselves from the crowd and are Sweden's contenders in talent search and matching.

By working as an agency, the value to you as an employee is that we have a very wide network of partner companies that we continuously ensure high-quality standards.

This recruitment is direct employment at Net Insight AB and all applications, questions, administration and recruitment process is managed by Pinetree AB.

Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Senior Fullstack Engineer

We are seeking a talented Senior Fullstack Engineer with a strong focus on backend engineering to join our team dedicated to developing and implementing genre taxonomies in a multilingual, multicultural environment. In this role, you will play a key part in ensuring that our content is organized and discoverable across different markets.

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Key Responsibilities:

Design and implement solutions within existing services and data pipelines.
Develop enhancements to complex systems, ensuring scalability and performance.
Collaborate across the tech stack, working on both backend services (primarily in Java) and frontend applications using React and Next.js.

Mandatory Skills required:

Java, React, Next.js, Taxonomies

Requirements:

A skilled backend engineer with proven experience in building and scaling services using Java.
Familiar with data pipelines and mapping services.

Excellent problem-solver with strong decision-making skills and a proactive approach.
Effective communicator with strong writing skills; able to lead engineering deep dives, workshops, and stakeholder demos.
Self-driven and capable of working independently as well as part of a collaborative team.
Experience with taxonomies is a plus.

Join us in shaping the future of content discoverability!

positionName: Senior Fullstack Developer with Backend focus - Stockholm

description:
At Anyfin HQ, nestled in the vibrant heart of Stockholm, we’re on a mission to transform the financial world. By equipping people with smart, innovative tools, we’re changing how individuals manage their financial well-being on an international scale. Our vision is clear and powerful: to improve the financial health of every individual, one debt at a time.

About Us: Since our inception in 2017, we’ve helped thousands of Swedes, Finns, Germans, and Norwegians take back control of their finances, saving millions by refinancing costly consumer credit. But this is just the beginning. With new markets to conquer, cutting-edge tools, and ambitious products on the horizon, we are constantly seeking new ways to elevate people’s financial situations. And to reach these bold goals, we need passionate and talented individuals like you.

What You Will Be Doing:
As a Senior Node.js Developer at Anyfin, you’ll dive deep into building and optimizing complex financial backend systems. You’ll be part of a fast-paced startup environment, collaborating with driven colleagues who thrive on innovation. Our team values growth, diversity, and adaptability, and you’ll have the chance to contribute to impactful projects from your very first day.

Your Responsibilities:

Specialize in backend development, utilizing Node.js and SQL to build robust and scalable financial systems.

Tackle complex coding challenges, crafting new backend solutions, and refining existing ones.

Work with TypeScript, GraphQL, Postgres, and occasionally touch on React, but the backend will be your primary focus.

Contribute to the design and architecture of financial platforms, ensuring the scalability and reliability of our systems.

Collaborate with cross-functional teams to shape both product and business strategies.

Share your backend expertise with the team, championing best practices and continuous learning.

Who You Are:

Proficient in Node.js and backend in general. Experience with SQL databases (preferably Postgres) is essential.

You have a passion for solving intricate backend problems, especially in high-stakes environments like finance.

At least 5 years of professional experience in software development. Experience with financial systems is a huge plus.

A good understanding of system design, clean code, and pragmatic problem-solving.

Bonus points if you’re familiar with React, Python, Go, GraphQL,Kubernetes, Google Cloud/AWS or DevOps with Github Actions but your backend experience will take center stage here.

Why Join Us? We promise you’ll be challenged and pushed to develop your skill set, all while working alongside a talented and ambitious team. Though we’ve made significant strides, the most exciting part of our journey is just beginning. Plus, we offer competitive compensation, a cozy centrally-located office, extra time off on your birthday, and many other benefits we’ll tell you about when we meet.

Are you ready to be a key player in revolutionizing financial well-being? We can’t wait to receive your application!

We believe that innovation thrives in person, so we work from the office four days a week to foster collaboration and creativity.

Please note that we are not offering relocation support for this position.

description:
Job Overview:

We are looking for a Software Developer with documented expertise in C++ and preferably at least one other programming language to work with our client in the defense industry. You will be involved in developing innovative and high-tech projects, where your technical skills will contribute to creating advanced solutions.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop and optimize software for real-time applications.
Work on graphics programming, including GPU programming, graphics APIs, and pipelines.
Participate in projects using Unreal Engine 5 to create advanced gaming and simulation solutions.
Collaborate with teams to implement continuous integration.

Mandatory Qualifications:

Strong experience in C++ programming.
Experience in game development.
Knowledge of graphics programming (GPU programming, graphics APIs, pipelines).
Experience in developing real-time applications.

Swedish citizenship and approved security clearance (RK).

description:
About the role

As a Build Engineer you will be critical in ensuring that our development teams can work efficiently with quick access to feedback and information, collaborating with many parts of the organization. Together with your team, you will also support bringing our in-house titles to hundreds of thousands of gamers in a fun and engaging work environment that is always looking to build and improve.

Responsibilities include the administration of source control and continuous integration servers. Management of services and processes for deployment of internal builds and public game releases. Development of systems that provide timely feedback and analytics to developers and service users as well as the investigation and promotion of new technologies and better testing procedures.

Required Qualifications

Experience of Linux / macOS server administration.

Experience managing continuous integration systems such as Gitlab CI or Jenkins.

Experience managing version control systems such as Git and Subversion.

Good verbal and written communication skills.

Service minded approach with a passion for providing and improving critical development services.

Experience in the following will be considered a plus

Experience with Bash scripting or Python.

Experience of working with and maintaining provisioning systems such as Terraform.

Experience of working with configuration management systems such as Ansible or Chef.

Experience building and configuring networks and server installation or maintenance.

The right candidate is passionate about our games and believes that developer efficiency is key to making great experiences. As a key member of the PDS Tech team many developers will rely on your expertise and the services you maintain so you should be both service minded and confident in accepting responsibility. At Paradox, we pride ourselves in providing opportunities to develop and learn new skills so we are looking for candidates who are interested in expanding their talents and working with new technologies.

Practical Information

Scope: Full-time and permanent

Location: Stockholm

Reports To: PDS Tech Lead

We will only recruit locally for this position

If you think that this description matches your background, we highly encourage you to apply as soon as possible as we will interview candidates continuously for this position. In your application, please show us why your previous experiences and skills would work for this role and why you are interested in working at Paradox. If you don't match all the requirements, please demonstrate how your passion, attitude and interest in Paradox might compensate for this.

Since we strive for a more even gender distribution we highly encourage women to apply to this role.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Qt/QML Developer - Automotive GUI

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Qt/QML Developer - Automotive GUI

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

We are looking for a driver display GUI developer for the Automotive industry.
We are looking for a developer to join the team in ensuring a premium quality driver interface by utilizing the full potential of ECU system and development tools.
As a developer, you will play a key role in developing user interfaces for the applications. You will work closely with designers, developers, and product managers to implement high-quality, performance-optimized, and visually appealing UIs using Qt Quick/QML.

Key Responsibilities:

Develop and implement high-quality user interfaces for automotive applications using Qt Quick/QML.

Collaborate closely with designers and product teams to ensure intuitive and user-centric UI/UX design.

Integrate QML with C++ backends for optimized performance and smooth functionality.

Maintain and improve existing GUI systems while ensuring code quality and performance.

Utilize version control systems like Git for collaborative development and continuous integration.

Troubleshoot and resolve issues related to GUI functionality, ensuring a premium user experience.

Work with agile development methodologies and contribute to continuous improvement of processes.

Requirements:

Bachelor’s or Master’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field.

Proven experience as a QML Developer or in a similar role.

Proficiency in QML and Qt Quick, with a strong understanding of UI/UX principles.

Solid experience in C++ programming and integration with QML.

Familiarity with version control tools like Git.

Strong analytical skills, attention to detail, and problem-solving abilities.

Excellent communication skills with the ability to work independently and within cross-functional teams.

Experience with agile methodologies is a plus.

Knowledge of Swedish is meritorious, but English fluency is required (verbal and written).

Work Setup:Hybrid work environment: 3 days in-office, the remainder from home.

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

description:
VIPAS is Hiring: FPGA Developer

Join VIPAS AB and unlock new opportunities as an FPGA Developer in the thrilling world of IT consulting!

About VIPAS:

At VIPAS AB, we harness the power of technology to transform business processes. Our mission is to align advanced technologies with your business goals for creating scalable and efficient solutions. Whether it's FPGA development, Java, or Python, our team is committed to guiding organizations through the latest tech innovations with confidence and a forward-thinking approach.

Role Overview: FPGA Developer Responsibilities

As an FPGA Developer at VIPAS AB, you will play a crucial role in our engineering team, focusing on the design, development, and optimization of FPGA-based solutions. Your collaboration with cross-functional teams will be key in delivering cutting-edge technology solutions that meet diverse client needs.

Design and implement digital circuits using FPGA technology.
Develop and optimize VHDL/Verilog code for various applications.
Perform simulation and testing to ensure system functionality and performance.
Work closely with hardware and software teams for seamless integration.
Troubleshoot and resolve any technical issues as they arise.
Essential Qualifications and Skills for FPGA Developers
Expertise in VHDL for FPGA design.
Proficiency with GIT for version control and Jenkins for continuous integration.
Hands-on experience with Matlab for simulations and modeling.
Linux proficiency for development and deployment.
Familiarity with tools like Quartus, Vivado, and Radiant.
Experience with project management tools like Confluence and Jira.

Requirements:

Location: Must be able to work on-site in Stockholm, 5 days a week.
Language: English proficiency is required.

If you're ready to take your FPGA skills to the next level, apply now and be a key player in our team!

description:
About ROYC
ROYC, founded in early 2022 by former Blackstone and Nordea executives, is a private markets investment platform, purpose built for the complex European market, focusing on streamlining and optimizing private equity fund life cycle management. ROYCs enterprise solutions is tailored to private equity General Partners, banks, wealth managers, and Multi Family Offices, allowing them to efficiently manage and sell private market investments.

Our team is composed of a diverse and international group of individuals who bring creativity, energy and excellence to every situation. We offer a fun and dynamic scale-up atmosphere, paired with the resources and stability of a mature organization, allowing for a rapid path from concept to implementation.

Why you are a fit for ROYC

Minimum of 4 years of relevant experience

Experience with JavaScript, React, Node.js and Python
Experience with Agile development methodologies

Experience making decisions and leading junior developers

Technical Skills

Strong knowledge of JavaScript, Python, React, and Node.js

Experience with SQL and AWS
Experience with Git and version control

Strong understanding of software development principles
Experience with cloud architecture
Experience with CI/CD pipeline and automation tools
Understanding of networking protocols and concepts

What you will do at ROYC

Be a senior member of our Tech team
Collaborate within our product development teams to deliver cutting edge product features
Stay up-to-date with new technologies and industry trends
Participate and drive code reviews and ensure adherence to development best practices
Take the lead on technical solutions and providers
Shape the future of private market investing

Benefits

Competitive compensation structure.
Options available for right level of seniority and experience.
Health benefits including fitness allowance.
Bonus scheme.
Hybrid working environment.
Work with the best in the industry.

What's ROYCs Culture

We have a flexible working environment where you would work closely with people pushing the boundaries of the wealth-tech space . If you like to innovate and use modern technology and want to avoid slow decisions, you would fit well here. We have a unique decision making process built by some of Europe's best investors from the last decade and aim to have fun whilst expanding the capabilities of the business.

Why ROYC is a fit for You!

We are a diverse multi-disciplinary and international team of people who bring creativity, energy, and excellence to every situation. It's a fun start-up atmosphere in a scale-up environment with a short path from idea to action. We offer flexibility, lovely breakfasts, fun team activities and after works, the maximum legal wellness allowance and actively support work-life balance.

Interested?

The ideal candidate will ideally have a track record and passion for creating innovative technology solutions. They should be comfortable working in a fast-paced scale-up environment and be able to adapt to changing requirements as the company grows.

This is a full-time, permanent position based either in central Stockholm, London, Copenhagen or Oslo. We are reviewing applications on a rolling basis. While the start date is flexible, the right candidate can join us immediately.

ROYC celebrates diversity and does not discriminate based on ethnicity, religion, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, age, disability status, or any other applicable characteristics protected by law.

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a 3D Frontend Developer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:

We are looking for an experienced Senior Frontend Developer who possesses extensive knowledge in React, TypeScript, and native JavaScript. The ideal candidate will be proficient in using Docker containers to streamline development processes and have familiarity with CI/CD deployments and GitHub for efficient project management. Knowledge of 3D skills, or game development skills, along with knowledge of Three.js, will be considered a strong advantage. We would love to have a optimistic high drive developer to follow our very active 3D team.

Key Responsibilities:

Design, develop, and maintain responsive and high-performance web applications using React and TypeScript.
Utilize Docker to create, deploy, and manage containerized applications, ensuring consistency across various environments.
Implement CI/CD pipelines for automated build, test, and deployment processes, improving development efficiency and product quality.
Collaborate with DevOps teams to deploy and manage applications within OpenShift clusters, ensuring scalable and reliable infrastructure.
Utilize Three.js for developing and integrating advanced 3D graphics into web applications (if applicable).
Work closely with cross-functional teams, including pipeline developers, backend developers, 3D designers, and project managers, to deliver high-quality solutions on time.

Requirements:

Extensive knowledge and hands-on experience with React, TypeScript, and native JavaScript (Node/Express)
Familiarity with Docker containers, including creating, deploying, and managing containerized applications using Docker CLI and Docker Compose.
Familiarity with CI/CD tools and processes, such as Jenkins, GitHub Actions, or similar platforms.
Experience with GitHub for version control and collaboration.
Familiarity with Azure stack, Azure functions, CosmosDB, Azure Busses, etc.

Education and Experience:

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related field.
4+ years of professional experience in frontend development.

Required skills

React
Docker
Azure Stack
Docker Compose
Jenkins
Docker CLI
Javascript
Azure Functions
EXPRESS
Github
Typescript
Node
CosmosDB
CI/CD

Preferred skills

3D graphics
game development
3D Modelling
Web Applications
3d Rendering

Languages

English (Proficient)

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

Apply Now & Please feel free to reach me at shrini@vipas.se

Note: Please do apply if you have Sweden PR/ citizenship OR a Sweden work permit.

How to Apply:

Interested candidates are encouraged to apply by submitting their resume and cover letter. Join us in driving innovation in the VIPAS AB!

Please note! We offer continuously. That means that we sometimes remove the assignments before the deadline. If you are interested we recommend that you apply immediately.

Job Description:

We are looking for several Test developers. You will be a part of a test developer team that will implement and maintain test cases and test frameworks for customers in the heavy vehicle domain.The customer uses the Danfoss Plus+1 system in their software development that will be under test.The customer will be represented by the product owner and architects who work in tight collaboration with the team when prioritizing and refining a development backlog using an agile development process.

Key Responsibilities:

• Test control systems and software for heavy vehicles.
• Develop and maintain test plans and test cases.
• Automate test processes where possible.
• Report bugs and work with the development team to resolve them.
• Participate in agile team ceremonies and streamline development processes.

Requirements:

• Experience in software testing.
• Experience in test automation.
• Good communication skills in Swedish and English.
Preferred:
• Experience in software testing within automotive/heavy vehicles.
• Knowledge of Danfoss systems.
• Proficiency in C, C++, Python and Simulink.

Location:
Linköping, Gothenburg and Jönköping.

The initial knowledge transfer will take place at costumer location

Do you have a passion for improving people's life? Are you fascinated by new technology with the challenge to create the next generation access control solutions? Join our Development Team in Stockholm, Sweden and enjoy a collaborative culture that empowers you to build a career you can be proud of.

What you would do as our Backend Developer
You will work in a cross functional team of five people, developing a safety solution for hotels and their employees. This is the opportunity to create a future for an innovative product and change the market for access systems all over the world.

You would also:
• apply the principles of Pair/Mob programming to ensure that we always deliver high quality software
• support our Microservice architecture and implement it with modern tools
• apply the principles of DevOps and Continuous Delivery to deliver our products to customers as soon as possible in the cloud (AWS)

Requirements:

Proven experience in developing and creating new solutions in Java, with experience in Java 17, with cloud deployment
Experienced in creating new solutions, not just maintain existing ones
A team player is core, the target team consists of total 5 people, in true DevOps setup, meaning no one else is there to handle bugs, infrastructure, development and maintenance.
In addition to being a team player, we’re looking for someone who is used to and appreciates working with pair- and mob-programming
Is fluent in English

Why Join Us?

Vipas AB offers attractive employment packages for IT consultants, aligned with the Teknikföretagen (Almega) collective agreement. Clients Working with us provides opportunities in diverse industries, allowing you flexibility and growth. If you’re driven and eager to face new challenges, join the VIPAS family.

You'll be part of an innovative team driving the future of telecom, Automotive, Retail, and Banking. If you're ready to take on challenging projects and grow your career in a cutting-edge environment, this is the opportunity for you!

description:
Company Description

As a pioneering Google Cloud partner, we pride ourselves on our collaborative, innovative culture that fosters learning and growth. With a team of over 600 Google Cloud experts and 1000+ certifications, we deliver cutting-edge solutions to over 2600 customers across 18 countries.

Job Description

Dive into the world of cloud computing with Devoteam G Cloud, the leading experts in Google Cloud solutions across the Nordics! We're offering exciting unpaid internship opportunities from January to May 2025 for driven individuals with a passion for development. Gain hands-on experience working with Python and/or TypeScript/JavaScript and become a part of our Digital Lab!

This internship offers you the chance to actively contribute to real-world projects within our Digital Lab, a fast-paced, agile environment. You'll collaborate with experienced developers, learn best practices, and contribute to the development of innovative solutions using cutting-edge technologies within the Google Cloud ecosystem.

Qualifications

Your Profile

Currently pursuing or recently completed a degree in computer science, software engineering, or a related field.
Solid understanding of Python and/or TypeScript/JavaScript.
Familiarity with Git and version control.
Eagerness to learn and contribute to a team.
Interest in cloud computing and Google Cloud Platform (GCP) is a plus.

What You Gain

Practical experience in software development using Python and/or TypeScript/JavaScript.
Exposure to Google Cloud Platform and its various services.
Mentorship from experienced developers and industry experts.
Opportunity to build your professional network in the cloud computing field.
Dynamic environment that encourages creativity and personal development.

Additional Information

"The Devoteam G Cloud internship provided me with invaluable hands-on experience in a real-world development environment. The supportive team and collaborative culture allowed me to grow both personally and professionally." - Julien Gumy, former Devoteam Intern

Apply Now!
Ready to launch your development career at the forefront of cloud computing? Submit your CV and a motivational letter highlighting your relevant skills and why you're the ideal candidate for this internship. We celebrate diversity and are an equal opportunities employer.

description:
We are seeking someone who:

Represents ambition and strength as a valuable team member in a dynamic workplace.
Demonstrates a self-driven spirit, recognizing the importance of adaptability in ever-changing environments.
Understands that success is a collective effort, placing a strong emphasis on genuine teamwork.
Exhibits high levels of drive, determination, and commitment.

About the Job:
We are looking for a proficient Automation Engineer to join our team. You will automate lab processes, enhancing operational efficiency and driving innovation across our projects.

Responsibilities:

Develop and implement automation scripts to optimize lab processes.
Collaborate with team members to identify and automate repetitive tasks.
Maintain and enhance existing automation frameworks.
Explore and integrate machine learning techniques to improve automation efficiency.
Work closely with cross-functional teams to ensure seamless integration of automated processes.

Mandatory Requirements:

Proficiency in Python programming.
Experience in automating processes, particularly in lab environments.
Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.

Desirable Skills:

Interest or experience in machine learning.
Familiarity with other programming languages.

WHY K TWO?
At K Two, our consultants are renowned for their high technical and social competence, extensive experience, responsiveness, and winning demeanor. We value not only skilled developers, technicians, and project managers but also effective consultants. We're in the business of assembling winners. Join us, where working for and with K Two is more than just a job; it's a rewarding experience!

Sounds interesting?

We hope so! Throughout the selection process, we will place significant emphasis on personal qualities and your commitment. If you believe you align with the above profile and wish to be part of our successful team, we eagerly await receiving your application!

description:
About the role

Do you have a passion for making things tick? Do you take pride in creating well-structured and functional code? If so, you might just be our new Embedded Engineer. Here at X Shore, we are developing the future of smart boating, and to do that we need the best and brightest developers.

As an Embedded Engineer at X Shore, you will have a crucial role in the development process for our boats. The work will consist of hardware integration in software, functional development, performance analysis, and much more. You will of course also have the benefit of testing your implementations out on the water. You will join a small, high-paced team of very talented individuals, and as a part of that team you will get to grow and develop alongside your colleagues.

Responsibilities include, but are not limited to:

Integrate new hardware components with software.
Develop new customer features.
Test and verify functionality.
Design and review electronics
Verify and solve bugs found in the field.
Continuously find ways to improve the efficiency of both yourself and the whole team.

You'd be based in Stockholm with occasional trips to our factory in Nyköping.

Your profile

We believe that you are a hands-on communicative person with a hunger to learn and develop. You have at least 5 years' experience working with embedded systems and you take ownership of the tasks that you work on.

We're looking for the following skills:

Strong C programing skills
Solid understanding of embedded electrical systems
Communication protocols used in Automotive/Marine systems such as CAN and Ethernet
Git, Bitbucket, Jira

It would also be a plus if you have experience within the following areas

Battery Management Systems (BMS), including design, optimization and safety management.
Electronics PCB design
IoT platforms
System design and/or test frameworks within the Automotive/Marine segment
Python
DevOps, HIL or CI/CD

... and of course you share our passion for contributing to a more sustainable way of living.

About X Shore

The Swedish climate technology and electric boat company X Shore was founded in 2016 in Stockholm. Made in Sweden, X Shore has become the world's leading supplier of electric boats with customers in markets such as North America and Europe. X Shore’s boats use no fossil fuels and have minimal impact on marine wildlife. X Shore boats have received numerous design awards and have won European Powerboat of the Year, Best of Boats and Design awards globally.

X Shore creates 100% electric boats for a fossil free tomorrow. By combining Swedish maritime craftsmanship with technology, innovation and sustainability, we are changing and charging the future of the boat industry. Sustainability is at the heart of everything X Shore does and the company was found by an independent auditor, Cicero Shades of Green AS, to be one of the most sustainable manufacturers in the world. For more information visit: www.xshore.com

description:
We are looking for you who wants to work with system development and also has expertise in testing at a company where there are opportunities to develop in other business areas as well. We are also looking for you who works as a developer and want to learn more about testing.

You have an interest in technology and understand logical connections between IT systems and have the ability to look at the business benefits for our customers. As a consultant at our clients, it's important that you are a "doer" who ensures that things get done.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Engage in agile system development for IT or Embedded systems at our clients' sites.
Collaborate in teams where developers write product code, unit tests, and automate integration and regression tests.
Assist teams in taking collective responsibility for the quality of their deliverables.
Contribute to discussions on system architecture, quality assurance, and agile methodologies.
Play a role in driving product development forward and ensuring future-proofing at both strategic and operational levels.
Participate in shaping our internal culture and fostering team development.

QUALIFICATIONS

Experience requirements

You have at least 5 years of experience as a developer.
You have worked with testing or automation.
You have a good command of at least one programming language, eg. Python, C#, C++, Javascript or Java.
You have experience in databases and Rest API.
You speak and write Swedish and English fluently.

As a person

Are a social team player.
Are meticulous and eager to live up to quality standards.
Are curious and have a willingness to keep up to date.
Takes initiative and are structured.

Meritorious experience and knowledge

Experience with Azure Devops, Jenkins, GIT, JIRA or similar.
Experience with Continuous Integration/Deployment and DevOps.
Experience with AWS, GCP or Azure Cloud.
Knowledge of agile methods.
ISTQB certification.

We highly value personal qualities such as collaboration skills, initiative, and a strong sense of responsibility. It is also crucial for our consultants to maintain a professional approach with clients.

WE OFFER YOU

We offer a collaborative and open environment with streamlined decision-making processes and colleagues who share common values of curiosity, creativity, and commitment. Our work culture empowers you to influence and make independent decisions. We provide the necessary tools to create an optimal setting for your personal and professional growth, contributing to the company’s long-term success. We trust in the abilities of our employees and appreciate the value of leveraging each individual's unique strengths.

Manage your own development plan.
Market salary.
Ability to customize part of your salary according to your own priorities.
Flexible working environment.
Full-time

 Stockholm
 Full-time permanent position
