description:
Learnster is a cutting-edge learning management system committed to revolutionizing how organizations approach employee development. Our human-centered approach blends innovative technology and AI with a dedication to empowering individuals and fostering learning cultures. Learnster comprises 45 engaged individuals, 200+ customers, and users across 30+ countries.

Join us on our trailblazing journey to reshape the future of workplace individual learning!

Job description

Are you a senior back-end developer with a devops mindset? Do you enjoy building scalable SaaS-products using Python and AWS? If so, you might be exactly the one we're looking for!

We're on the hunt for a senior back-end developer who wants to join us on our quest to help employees of our customers in their individual learning and growth journeys! We believe that you're a skilled engineer with a passion for technology and a drive to solve customer problems. We believe that you have a DevOps mindset where you care about the entire lifecycle of a solution, from ideation to development and deployment, and that you do that with open eyes and a learning mindset.

Your role will include

As a back-end developer at Learnster, you’ll be involved in the whole development lifecycle, where you contribute with everything from ideation and solution design to development, testing and deployment.

You'll do this in close collaboration with other developers, designers and product managers since we believe that the best solutions come when people with different skills and background work together finding the best solutions.

To thrive in this role you'll have the following skills and experience

Back-end development experience: Experience as a back-end developer, with a strong portfolio of solutions developed using Python and AWS.

Python Development: Solid experience in Python development, specifically with the Django framework.

Database design and development: Experience using both relational and non-relational databases and experience writing SQL code to retrieve and modify data.

AWS Solution Development: Experience in designing and implementing solutions on AWS, leveraging both AWS managed services and cloud-agnostic technologies.

DevOps Mindset: A strong understanding of DevOps principles, with a focus on the entire lifecycle of a software solution. This includes a keen interest in why we build solutions, how we build them, and ensuring they perform optimally once deployed.

What We Offer

An exciting journey in a scale-up with strong investors

Flexible work arrangements (remote/on-site)

Health and wellness benefits

Continuous learning opportunities within a vibrant, innovative team

Six weeks of paid vacation plus 3 extra free days per year

A culture that values diversity and promotes personal development

We look forward to meeting you!

Join a fast-growing and awarded SaaS company, where you will play a key role in shaping Learnster’s future.

At Learnster, you will work with passionate and ambitious colleagues, ready to take ourselves, our team, and the company to the next level!

Please send your application in if you think that you would be a good fit for this position and if you think that Learnster might be a place for you!

We look forward to meeting you!

Join us on our trailblazing journey to reshape the future of workplace individual learning!


Job description


Are you a senior back-end developer with a devops mindset? Do you enjoy building scalable SaaS-products using Python and AWS? If so, you might be exactly the one we're looking for!


We're on the hunt for a senior back-end developer who wants to join us on our quest to help employees of our customers in their individual learning and growth journeys! We believe that you're a skilled engineer with a passion for technology and a drive to solve customer problems. We believe that you have a DevOps mindset where you care about the entire lifecycle of a solution, from ideation to development and deployment, and that you do that with open eyes and a learning mindset.


Your role will include

As a back-end developer at Learnster, you’ll be involved in the whole development lifecycle, where you contribute with everything from ideation and solution design to development, testing and deployment.

You'll do this in close collaboration with other developers, designers and product managers since we believe that the best solutions come when people with different skills and background work together finding the best solutions.


To thrive in this role you'll have the following skills and experience

  • Back-end development experience: Experience as a back-end developer, with a strong portfolio of solutions developed using Python and AWS.

  • Python Development: Solid experience in Python development, specifically with the Django framework.

  • Database design and development: Experience using both relational and non-relational databases and experience writing SQL code to retrieve and modify data.

  • AWS Solution Development: Experience in designing and implementing solutions on AWS, leveraging both AWS managed services and cloud-agnostic technologies.

  • DevOps Mindset: A strong understanding of DevOps principles, with a focus on the entire lifecycle of a software solution. This includes a keen interest in why we build solutions, how we build them, and ensuring they perform optimally once deployed.

What We Offer

  • An exciting journey in a scale-up with strong investors

  • Flexible work arrangements (remote/on-site)

  • Health and wellness benefits

  • Continuous learning opportunities within a vibrant, innovative team

  • Six weeks of paid vacation plus 3 extra free days per year

  • A culture that values diversity and promotes personal development

We look forward to meeting you!


Join a fast-growing and awarded SaaS company, where you will play a key role in shaping Learnster’s future.


At Learnster, you will work with passionate and ambitious colleagues, ready to take ourselves, our team, and the company to the next level!


Please send your application in if you think that you would be a good fit for this position and if you think that Learnster might be a place for you!

We look forward to meeting you!

description:
Job Vacancy: DevOps Engineer

Location: Sweden - remote / hybrid / office

Contract: B2B, Full-Time

Company Overview:

Kolomolo is a globally recognized tech enterprise dedicated to delivering state-of-the-art digital solutions. As we expand our operations, we are on the lookout for seasoned DevOps Engineers.

Role:

Seeking a DevOps professional for a Platform Observability role. Individual will contribute to supporting application teams' observability stack. Team follows agile methodologies.

Join a team focused on enhancing developer productivity through platform solutions. The goal is to understand and address the needs of internal software engineers to improve their efficiency and performance.

Responsibilities:
Collaborate with application groups to optimize system dependability and speed.
Advocate for advanced operational approaches.
Manage enterprise-wide operational tool sets.
Contribute to both development and operational tasks.
Participate in rotating on-call responsibilities.

Qualifications and skills:

Necessary:

Proven experience in integrating and supporting cloud-native observability solutions such as ElasticSearch/OpenSearch, InfluxData, and Azure Monitor.
Expertise in CI/CD tools like Jenkins, Azure Devops, Gitlab or alternatives.
Demonstrated ability to thrive in a product-focused environment aligned with Team Objectives and OKRs.
Bachelor's degree in computer science or a comparable field.Minimum of 3 years of practical experience as a DevOps Engineer.

Proficient in Git version control.Fluent in English with excellent written and verbal communication skills.
Deep expertise in monitoring and alerting systems leveraging ElasticStack, InfluxData, and Grafana.
Strong scripting and automation capabilities with hands-on experience in Kubernetes, Terraform, and Python.

Desired:

Results-oriented and technologically adept individual with a passion for automation and code-based solutions.
Possessing a strategic mindset, able to tackle complex challenges within large-scale environments.
Proven ability to enhance developer productivity through the integration of observability tools into the software development lifecycle.
Demonstrates exceptional problem-solving and troubleshooting abilities.
A strong collaborator with effective communication and teamwork skills.

WHAT WE OFFER:

Competitive salary and benefits
A dynamic, collaborative, and growth-oriented work environment
Opportunities for career advancement and continuous learning
Flat management structure
B2B contract
A chance to be part of something bigger where what you say matters

Agile ways of working
Fun and relaxed working environment where work-life balance is important
Regular company events (time for fun)
Office in Krakow (High quality coffee / Tea / Fruits / Sweets)
Ability to work alongside young, motivated, eager to learn and talented team

ABOUT US:

Kolomolo, a global supplier of software engineering and IT outsourcing services, is looking for a DevOps.

While Kolomolo is a pillar of strength, we shatter the corporate mold. Think agile teams, generous autonomy, and a remote & asynchronous ethos.

We're also big on work-life harmony, inspired by Scandinavian values.

Curious?

Dive deeper into Kolomolo's Career Portal.

WHAT MAKES USE DIFFERENT?

We prioritize learning and development, and we recognize and reward hard work and intelligence. We treat our staff with respect and trust, giving them responsibilities and seldom checking up on them. We prefer agile ways of working, minimizing unnecessary management and bureaucracy.

Our team is made up of passionate and knowledgeable individuals who love what they do and are always eager to help each other. But it's not all work and no play at our company!

We believe in a healthy work-life balance and foster a fun and inclusive culture.

Join us and be part of a dynamic team that encourages continuous learning, rewards hard work, and values a fun and inclusive work culture. Take your career to new heights with us as, where you'll have the opportunity to work with cutting-edge technologies, align your work with your passions, and be part of a team that truly values your contributions.

Apply now and let's embark on an exciting journey of learning, achievements, and camaraderie together!

Cheers to a fulfilling and rewarding career with us!

description:
Job Description:

Role: Senior AWS Cloud Architect

Experience: 8-10 years

Location: Stockholm, Sweden

Role Description:

We are seeking an AWS Cloud Architect who will play a crucial role in executing our Cloud strategy and achieving roadmap milestones in collaboration with our team. As an AWS Cloud expert, you will provide technical leadership, support cross-functional initiatives, and drive automation in cloud operations.

Key Responsibilities:

Serve as a Subject Matter Expert (SME) on the AWS cloud platform, providing guidance on best practices, security, and compliance standards.
Stay updated with the latest AWS cloud services, features, and capabilities; evaluate their applicability to meet evolving business needs.
Collaborate with cross-functional teams, stakeholders, and business units to gather requirements, prioritize initiatives, and align cloud strategies with business objectives.
Lead efforts to automate processes related to cloud operations, security configurations, account management, and cost optimization.
Promote the Public Cloud offering internally, acting as an ambassador and point of contact for AWS cloud solutions.
Provide technical leadership, mentorship, and guidance to junior architects, engineers, and developers, fostering a culture of innovation, learning, and continuous improvement.

Competencies Required:

Digital Expertise: Amazon Web Services (AWS) Cloud Computing

Experience:

8-10 years of experience in AWS Cloud Computing, with deep knowledge of platform services, features, and best practices.

Essential Skills:

Proven ability to build scalable, resilient, and cost-effective cloud platform solutions based on business requirements and industry standards.
Experience with AWS Cloud Foundations constructs for Enterprises, such as AWS Control Tower and the AWS Cloud Adoption Framework.
Familiarity with containerization technologies like Docker and orchestration platforms like Kubernetes.
Expertise in infrastructure automation tools such as Terraform and AWS CloudFormation for provisioning and managing cloud resources programmatically.
Experience with Continuous Integration and Continuous Delivery (CI/CD) pipelines at scale, with a passion for automation.
Proficient in programming languages, particularly Go and Python, used extensively for serverless integrations and APIs.
Strong understanding of practical security, networking, and cloud economics, including cost optimization and visualization (FinOps).
Other cloud knowledge (e.g., GCP/Azure) is a plus.
Excellent communication skills in English, with the ability to articulate complex cloud strategies to stakeholders.
Ability to translate strategic plans into technical deliverables, ensuring operational readiness and stability.

Why Join Us?

Be part of a forward-thinking team that values innovation and continuous learning. If you are passionate about leveraging AWS to drive business outcomes and thrive in a dynamic environment, we encourage you to apply!

We would love to hear from you if you are interested in joining our team and contributing to our mission of innovation and excellence. Please send your resume and cover letter for consideration to anu@beyondtech.se.

description:
What We Are Looking For:

We are seeking passionate and skilled Senior C++ Software Engineers to join our team and drive our strategic vision to transform trading for our clients globally. As part of our dynamic team, you will embrace change and excel in a fast-paced, global environment.

Responsibilities:

Participate in the design, development, and testing of financial markets software products.
Develop and integrate various methods of information visualization.
Evolve technically while working on data-intensive and latency-sensitive products.
Engage in code-review practices to provide and receive constant technical feedback.
Ensure internal quality standards are met through automated testing, including unit, integration, performance, and throughput tests.
Continuously learn and enhance expertise in financial assets, investment banking, and financial technology.
Contribute and promote best practices during development cycles using continuous integration.

Profile Needed:

Mandatory:

Bachelor’s degree in STEM fields such as math, physics, computer science, engineering, etc.
Over 5 years of experience in C++ development.
Solid knowledge of C++ features and programming techniques.
Comprehensive knowledge of basic algorithms and data structures.
Good understanding of modern C++ standards (C++ 17/20).
Proficiency in debugging and troubleshooting.
Ability to work independently and as part of a global team.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills with attention to detail.
Familiarity with applying OOP concepts in performance-demanding environments.
Good communication skills with proficient English proficiency.

Beneficial:

Knowledge of financial markets and financial technologies.
Linux/Unix experience at an advanced user or admin level.
Experience in multi-threaded programming.
Experience in low-latency software design, performance profiling, and optimization.
Knowledge of the Internet protocol suite and network programming.
Familiarity with the LLVM toolchain.
Understanding of functional programming concepts.
Experience in other programming languages (Java, Python, Shell scripting, Rust, Haskell, etc.).

Hybrid Flexible at Broadridge

We are made up of high-performing teams that meet in person to learn and collaborate as needed. This role is considered hybrid, which means you’ll be assigned to a Broadridge office and given the flexibility to work remote

#LI-Hybrid

description:
Hej, Truecaller is calling you from Stockholm, Sweden! Ready to pick up?

Our goal is to make communication smarter, safer, and more efficient, all while building trust everywhere. We're all about bringing you smart services with a big social impact, keeping you safe from fraud, harassment, scam calls, or messages, so you can focus on the conversations that matter.

Top 20 most downloaded apps globally, and world’s #1 caller ID and spam-blocking service for Android and iOS, with extensive AI capabilities, with more than 400 million active users per month.
Founded in 2009 with an impressive year-on-year growth with high profitability, listed on Nasdaq OMX Stockholm, Large Cap.
Founded in 2009, listed on Nasdaq OMX Stockholm and is categorized as a Large Cap. Our focus on innovation, operational excellence, sustainable growth, and collaboration has resulted in consistently high profitability and strong EBITDA margins.
A team of 400 people from ~35 different nationalities spread across our headquarters in Stockholm and offices in Bangalore, Mumbai, Gurgaon, and Tel Aviv with high ambitions.

We, at the Data Science and Analytics Products team, build centralized data products that serve the business and our customers. We collaborate across all of Truecaller, delivering products that require centralized ownership or where the competence to build the products is not present in the wider product organization.

As a Senior MLOps Engineer, you will lead the transformation of our MLOps platform and will be responsible for reimagining and rebuilding it to enable fast, scalable, and cost-effective machine learning model development and deployment. You will also help set the best ways of working to make the best use of the platform and increase developer productivity. This role is critical to our mission of accelerating model training, deployment, and experimentation. Your work will directly impact our ability to deploy models within hours, support automated machine learning (AutoML), and enable teams across the organization to experiment with and deploy generative AI models.

The impact you will create:

Lead the MLOps transformation in Truecaller by designing and building the infrastructure needed to enable our teams.
Understand the current and future needs of developers and the organization, and create a roadmap with your manager for meeting those needs.
Collaborate closely and support developers throughout the organization to make model training, development, and monitoring fast, scalable, and cost-efficient.
Stay up to date with the latest trends and technologies in MLOps, AI, and cloud computing, and drive continuous innovation throughout Truecaller.

What you bring in:

5+ years of experience building and maintaining tools and platforms for feature engineering, model training, model deployment, model monitoring, and A/B testing model performance.
Strong programming skills in Python and shell scripting.
A strong understanding of CI/CD pipelines and automation tools.
Expertise in infrastructure as code (for example, Terraform).
Strong understanding of machine learning frameworks (TensorFlow, PyTorch, ONNX).
Strong experience in cloud platforms (we use GCP) and cloud-native tools.
Strong communication and collaboration skills, with the ability to work effectively across different teams and disciplines.
A customer-focused mindset.

It would be great if you also have:

Experience with AutoML tools (for example H2O.ai or Auto-Keras).
Experience enabling generative AI experimentation, fine-tuning, and deployment.
Experience with Go.

It would be great if you also have:

Experience with AutoML tools (for example H2O.ai or Auto-Keras).
Experience enabling generative AI experimentation, fine-tuning, and deployment.

Sounds like your dream job?

We will fill the position as soon as we find the right candidate, so please send your application as soon as possible. As part of the recruitment process, we will conduct a background check.

 This position is based in Stockholm, Sweden.

We only accept applications in English.

What we offer:

A smart, talented, and agile team: An international team where ~35 nationalities are working together in several locations and time zones with a learning, sharing, and fun environment.
A great compensation package: Competitive salary, 30 days of paid vacation, flexible working hours, private health insurance, parental leave top-up, pension contribution, Udemy membership to keep learning and improving, and free gym membership.
Great tech tools: Pick the computer and phone you most fancy within our budget ranges.
Office life: We strongly believe in in-person collaboration and follow an office-first approach while offering some flexibility. Enjoy your days with great colleagues with loads of good stuff to learn from, and a wide range of yummy snacks and beverages. In addition, now and then check out the playroom for a fun break or join our exciting parties and or team activities such as Lab days, Running team, movie nights in our cinema, or a Geek lunch. There is something for everyone!

Come as you are:
Truecaller is diverse, equal, and inclusive. We need a variety of backgrounds, perspectives, beliefs, and experiences to keep building our great products. No matter where you are based, which language you speak, your accent, race, religion, color, nationality, gender, sexual orientation, age, marital status, etc. All those things make you who you are, and that’s why we would love to meet you

description:
Are you as inspired as we are by the combination of multiphysics simulation, product design, and programming? Do you want to work in a team of driven and talented colleagues? Would you like to develop functionality for products used worldwide by tens of thousands of engineers? If so, read on.

Who We Are

COMSOL is the leading innovator of multiphysics simulation software for research and product development. The COMSOL product suite enables our users to solve challenging science and engineering problems, thanks to our intuitive and flexible user interface. We create the tools that drive new breakthroughs in science and engineering, and we love what we do. Founded in Sweden in 1986, the COMSOL organization boasts 16 offices and a distributor network throughout the world with more than 500 employees.

What You'll Do

In our newly renovated Stockholm office, we develop the core functionality of our multiphysics product family, used worldwide in research and development (R&D) and computer-aided engineering (CAE). We are now seeking a talented and motivated software developer to expand the team developing the COMSOL Model Manager — a version control system for managing simulation data. The Model Manager is fully integrated with our flagship product COMSOL Multiphysics® and enables our users to seamlessly store, search, organize, and share multiphysics simulations between colleagues and stakeholders within their respective organizations. Being a part of the COMSOL product suite, the functionality is shipped as an off-the-shelf software package that our users install onsite and manage themselves.

As a new hire, you will:

Work in a specific problem space, with the goal to gradually expand your knowledge within the many areas we're responsible for, with plenty of opportunities to learn and grow.
Take on an integral role in the full life-cycle of your code, from design to development, testing, feedback, improvement, and maintenance.
Help solve real problems for engineers worldwide.

The position involves both backend work on the storage and API layers, and some work on the desktop user interface. Most of the development is done in Java, some in SQL, and some in C# for desktop user interface components. Depending on your interests, the role can also cover frontend development in TypeScript and Vue for the web interface of the Model Manager server.

Your day-to-day work typically involves writing code, reviewing other team members’ code, being involved in specification- and design work, testing and giving feedback on the team’s projects, and otherwise contributing to the overall health of the codebase. The team organizes its work through a Kanban process that tracks a yearly release schedule for the product.

What We're Looking For

You are passionate about problem-solving and not afraid to dig into existing code and make it your own. You are open-minded, value teamwork, and understand the importance of putting users center stage. You also care about code quality and understand the need for comprehensive test coverage, sense of code ownership, modularity, adequate performance-tuning, and good documentation. Beyond that, we are looking for someone with the following background:

M.Sc. or equivalent degree in engineering, physics, mathematics, or computer science, or significant work experience in relevant programming positions spanning multiple years.
Excellent programming skills with proficiency in at least one object-oriented programming language, for example Java, C#, or Python.
Strong written and verbal communication skills.
Must be eligible to work in Sweden, but Swedish is not a requirement as long as you have good English skills.

Experience with the following will be valued when assessing candidates:

Larger software projects.
Design of user interfaces for desktop or web.
Design of APIs.
Mentorship of other developers.
Professional use of Java, SQL, Lucene, PostgreSQL (or some other relational database management system), Apache Solr (or some other search technology), Javascript, Typescript, Vue.

Knowledge of physics or simulation is not a requirement, but interest in these areas will help to better understand our product and market.

What We Offer

At COMSOL, you will quickly play a key role within your development projects, where you will have many opportunities to suggest ideas and improvements. As the company is growing continuously, we strive toward making you an expert within your development area within a few years. Along the way, you will be supported by experienced colleagues in a collaborative working environment. In addition to an exciting career working on a sophisticated software product, we also offer a competitive salary, individual pension plans, and sponsored gym membership. We respect your leisure time and need for a work-life balance. We expect you to be onsite during the initial onboarding period. After that, we apply a hybrid approach that enables you to work from home a few days a week on average.

Our corporate culture is innovative, vibrant, and cutting-edge. We are committed to encouraging creativity through an exciting and challenging environment in which individuals excel and grow. We believe that our talented employees and an active learning environment are the keys to our success.

descriptionHTML:
Are you as inspired as we are by the combination of multiphysics simulation, product design, and programming? Do you want to work in a team of driven and talented colleagues? Would you like to develop functionality for products used worldwide by tens of thousands of engineers? If so, read on.

Who We Are

COMSOL is the leading innovator of multiphysics simulation software for research and product development. The COMSOL product suite enables our users to solve challenging science and engineering problems, thanks to our intuitive and flexible user interface. We create the tools that drive new breakthroughs in science and engineering, and we love what we do. Founded in Sweden in 1986, the COMSOL organization boasts 16 offices and a distributor network throughout the world with more than 500 employees.

What You'll Do

In our newly renovated Stockholm office, we develop the core functionality of our multiphysics product family, used worldwide in research and development (R&D) and computer-aided engineering (CAE). We are now seeking a talented and motivated software developer to expand the team developing the COMSOL Model Manager — a version control system for managing simulation data. The Model Manager is fully integrated with our flagship product COMSOL Multiphysics® and enables our users to seamlessly store, search, organize, and share multiphysics simulations between colleagues and stakeholders within their respective organizations. Being a part of the COMSOL product suite, the functionality is shipped as an off-the-shelf software package that our users install onsite and manage themselves.

As a new hire, you will:
Work in a specific problem space, with the goal to gradually expand your knowledge within the many areas we're responsible for, with plenty of opportunities to learn and grow.
Take on an integral role in the full life-cycle of your code, from design to development, testing, feedback, improvement, and maintenance.
Help solve real problems for engineers worldwide.

The position involves both backend work on the storage and API layers, and some work on the desktop user interface. Most of the development is done in Java, some in SQL, and some in C# for desktop user interface components. Depending on your interests, the role can also cover frontend development in TypeScript and Vue for the web interface of the Model Manager server.

Your day-to-day work typically involves writing code, reviewing other team members’ code, being involved in specification- and design work, testing and giving feedback on the team’s projects, and otherwise contributing to the overall health of the codebase. The team organizes its work through a Kanban process that tracks a yearly release schedule for the product.

Larger software projects.
Design of user interfaces for desktop or web.
Design of APIs.
Mentorship of other developers.

Knowledge of physics or simulation is not a requirement, but interest in these areas will help to better understand our product and market.

description:
We are looking for a dynamic and innovative Machine Learning Engineer to join our team. This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a startup environment and is passionate about developing cutting-edge AI solutions. As a Machine Learning Engineer, you will work collaboratively with cross-functional teams to drive our AI initiatives forward.

Company description

Hypertype is an AI-powered text based communication platform that finds the most relevant information and writes smarter customer emails & live chats, using real-time company data.

305 billion emails sent and received every single day. We live in an information overload era, with ever-changing customer scenarios to process and answer. Customer facing roles still spend 20-30 mins just to find the right answers and draft high quality email, connecting the dots from millions of data sitting inside their company. Our vision is to make the smartest experience for customer communications with data.

Only a single digit % of SMEs has adopted AI in their customer facing teams. We have over 200 paying companies including Mynt, Yazen, Remote and many more.

Our customers proudly recognize us for delivering the "highest quality answers in the market... outsmarting Gemini, Fin, Microsoft Copilot etc". —a testament to our unwavering commitment to excellence and precision in every interaction.

Join us on our mission to build the world’s smartest and most accurate AI brain across customer domains and beyond. If you're driven and ready to contribute to something groundbreaking, this is your chance to be part of a mission that is setting new industry standards.

The Position

The ML Engineer is responsible for developing Hyperbrain AI to build the world's smartest and accurate brain for CS and many more domains. Hyperbrain ingests and stores high quality data which is unique for each company. Company data is ingested from omni- data sources into Hyperbrain in one-click. Hyperbrain then automatically writes customer communications with the most relevant data in the reply interfaces e.g. Intercom, Gmail and Outlook, to answer trillions of customer scenarios that is beyond standard Chatbot conversations.

In the role, you will design, develop, and deploy machine learning models that directly impact Hypertype products. You will work closely with customer data, ensuring the models are not only accurate and efficient but also compliant with data privacy regulations.

Developing new product experiences using NLP & LLMs and working closely with customers to understand their needs and ensure successful implementation.
Implementing and shipping state-of-the-art information retrieval systems and search algorithms, with high impact metrics
Improve the quality and accuracy of answers from omni- data sources and format, by incorporating the best data and features to improve AI suggested answers.
Prompt engineering and fine-tuning to improve the quality of customer communications for different scenarios.
Collaborating with cross-functional teams to align technical decisions with business goals and co-develop ML roadmap.
Designing, developing, and maintaining scalable APIs for integrating new data sources.
Collaborate with frontend developers to ensure APIs are efficient, well-documented, and deliver the necessary data for UI/UX components.
Troubleshooting and resolving data-related issues, ensuring continuous data flow and minimal downtime.
Identifying opportunities for performance improvements and proactively implementing solutions to improve the data architecture.
Rapidly integrating new data sources to support POCs and MVPs, working closely with co-founders and the sales team to offer technical expertise throughout the sales process.
Qualification
You have ample experience in in building machine learning pipelines and / or information retrieval systems and are up to speed on latest in NLP & LLMs.
You have experience in developing POC and MVP to facilitate the successful establishment of customer partnerships and the closing of deals.
You have applied knowledge of A/B testing for model evaluation
Versatile Software Engineering Skills: A solid engineering background with a robust foundation in software engineering principles. You have written code for and supported production engineering systems.
Proficient in Python and experience with GCP: our AI stack uses Python, Hugging Face, PyTorch & Elasticsearch and is deployed on GKE.
You care about delivering true business value and solving RAG challenges at the same time.
A Solid Educational Foundation: Bachelor’s degree in Machine Learning, Computer Science or related field; Master’s degree is a plus.
Bonus points
Experience with ETL processes, data pipelines and large-scale data processing.
Familiar with tools like Airbyte, Apache Airflow, or similar.
Experience with Node and Typescript.
Familiar with data security and compliance (e.g., PII handling, ISO 27001, SOC 2, GDPR). Familiarity with the Vanta platform is a strong plus.
The Offer
Opportunity to be part in a generative AI startup before the next AI inflection point.
A role and position that enables you to be part of building and shaping the way how customer information is shared and communicated.
Take part of our journey as we grow to be at the forefront to solve AI challenges and work towards building Hyperbrain AI for every domain for a decision-making AI.
Salary + Equity + Opportunity to grow in the role

At Hypertype, we look for positive, 'always learning' and humble personalities. We welcome everyone to apply if you feel it suits you and let’s have a chat to see if you could be right for the role.

description:
At CatalystOne, we’re transforming the future through technology. As we expand our innovative integration services, we’re looking for an Integration Developer to join our dynamic team. If you’re passionate about building cutting-edge solutions and thrive in a collaborative environment, we want to hear from you!

Catalystone is on a mission to become the central system in our customers' IT landscapes for employment master data. Our Technical Consultation (TC) team has split into two specialized roles to better meet growing demands: Technical Consultants who advise and guide, and Integration Developers who build and maintain integrations. Together, we deliver seamless, high-quality solutions with a customer-focused approach.

What you'll do as Integration Developer
Building and Maintaining Integrations: Design, develop, and maintain customer integrations and standard integrations for partners.
Collaborative Problem Solving: Work closely with Technical Consultants to ensure integration solutions are effective and high-quality.
Platform Development: Update, develop, and maintain our integrations platform to enhance our service capabilities.
Customer-Focused Solutions: Engage in discussions with third parties and internal IT departments to build optimal solutions.
Documentation: Document integration processes, architecture, and code for future reference and maintenance.
Daily Operations: Handle error messages for current integrations, maintain and update existing ones, and participate in scrum activities like sprint planning and daily stand-ups.

Requirements

Educational Background: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent work experience.
Technical Experience: Proven experience as a senior developer or in a similar role, with proficiency in Python or C#.
Integration Expertise: Solid understanding of different types of APIs, Microsoft Azure integration services, and experience with Git (CI/CD).
Agile Methodology: Familiarity with Scrum and agile development processes.
Languages: Fluency in a Scandinavian language and English.

Benefits

As well as your salary, you’ll receive:

Financial and Health Security: Benefit from a comprehensive pension and insurance package, plus private healthcare.
Your Well-being, Your Way: Take advantage of our wellness contribution to stay on top of your health.
Tech Tools for Efficiency: Get the job done with a choice of laptop (mac / PC), mobile phone & subscription, and a home internet allowance.
Flexible Work Setup: Hybrid for your life-work balance.
And more country-specific benefits

CatalystOne does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firms/recruiters. CatalystOne will not pay any fees to search firms/recruiters if a candidate is submitted by a search firm/recruiter unless an agreement has been entered into with respect to the specific open position(s). Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to CatalystOne on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.

We would like to inform you that all candidates who receive a job offer will be subject to a background check.
Contact Mark Mc Daid Talent Acquisition Manager – People & Culture
About CatalystOne

CatalystOne is a Scandinavian leader of HCM-software with nearly 250 employees throughout Norway, Sweden, Denmark, and India. We have, since 2004, built a strong value-based company driven by our customers' success. Our culture is characterized by a unique combination of emphasis on results and on people. We have experienced high growth in recent years and have the ambition to continue this growth both in Scandinavia and in other North-European countries.

CatalystOne is an equal opportunity employer that is committed to diversity and inclusion in the workplace. We prohibit discrimination and harassment of any kind based on race, color, sex, religion, sexual orientation, national origin, disability, genetic information, pregnancy, or any other protected characteristic.

Founded in 2004
Co-workers 250+

Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

BSc or MSc level in Electrical Engineering, Computer Science, or other equivalent education.
At least 5 years of work experience.
Significant experience of EDA tools for Synthesis & Timing/Area/Power closure
Significant experience from Static Timing Analysis and timing sign off
Experience in low power and UPF

Knowledge in scripting languages (Python, Perl, TCL, Linux Shell scripting etc.)
Experience from UNIX/Linux

Experience from source code repositories such as Git

Knowledge about mobile communication standards is an advantage.

Telecom knowledge

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a DevOps CI Engineer with (Java & python )

Do you have the skills and passion to succeed in the dynamic world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a growing company, invites you to join us for your next impactful project , . Do you love being in the flow as a developer and want to enable that for everyone else? Do you believe the key to personal flow is making the local developer build experience fast, well-integrated, automated, and with meaningful insights? We are seeking a collaborative and curious Engineer to help drive and develop our CI infrastructure forward.

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description:
Continuous Integration (CI) is at the core of our developer experience. xx's growth and widespread presence have led us to require an ever wider and deeper range of target platforms to run CI against. In a context where early adoption and swift flexibility is at utmost importance we need to provide CI environments that enables us to deliver functionality to our customers with both speed and safety. This role will be part of a team collaboratively creating and owning our CI infrastructure for xx which aims to provide our developers with a streamlined, simple to use, and safe build experience at scale.
The role is located in the Platform Developer Experience (PDX) studio within the Platform Mission. The PDX Studio oversees and owns the infrastructure that cuts across all engineering disciplines at xx

What you’ll do

Execute on xx’s future CI infrastructure strategy that can serve 3000+ engineers doing 100’s thousands of builds daily and beyond

Support with Operational tasks keeping our systems healthy and up-to-date

Drive the automation and improvements of our CI system across our current technical stacks.

Help scale our CI infrastructure to support large-scale monorepos.

Collaborate with Infrastructure teams across the company to discover what a best-in-class CI infrastructure means.

Key Responsibilities:

You are an experienced engineer familiar with Linux, MacOS, and Windows as well as Networking fundamentals

You are an experienced Software Engineer with Java and Python

You have experience deploying and implementing solutions in GCP, Azure, and/or AWS.

You believe in iteration and know that finding the right solution is more important than the first.

You like to focus on standardization and automation; always looking for ways to improve the developer experience

You have 6+ years of experience in building and implementing large-scale systems across various projects and teams

You have familiarity with and enthusiasm for software engineering best practices such as testing, continuous integration, and continuous delivery

Requirements:

Linux, MacOS, and Windows system administration experience
HTTP / networking
Google Cloud (preferred) / Azure / AWS
TeamCity Integrations

description:
Company Description

Wolt is a Helsinki-based technology company that provides an online platform for consumers, merchants, and couriers. It connects people looking to order food and other goods with people interested in selling and delivering them. To enable this, Wolt develops a wide range of technologies from local logistics to retail software and financial solutions – as well as operating its own grocery stores under the Wolt Market brand. Wolt’s products include Wolt+ (subscription service for customers), Wolt for Work (meal benefits and office deliveries for companies), Wolt Drive (fast last-mile deliveries for merchants), and Wolt Self-Delivery (service for merchant partners with their own delivery staff). Wolt’s mission is to make cities better by empowering and growing local communities. Wolt was founded in 2014 and joined forces with DoorDash in 2022. DoorDash operates in 31 countries today, 27 of which are with the Wolt product and brand.

So, why work at Wolt?

At Wolt, We’re About Getting Things Done.
You’ll probably enjoy it here if you like taking ownership, developing yourself, and being around friendly, humble, and ambitious people.

We work hard to make cities into better places, and it’s pretty cool seeing us grow every week. If you’re passionate about building things that just… work, Wolt might be for you.

Our Commitment to Diversity, Equity & Inclusion
We want to have all sorts of people in our team – people like you and me, and people different from you and me. To be able to work with diverse teammates – when it comes to gender, age, ethnicity, life background, sexual orientation, political views, religion, or any other personal trait – we consciously aim to offer equal opportunity for everyone to work with us. This is because we believe diverse teams make the most thought-through decisions and build things in the most inclusive way.

Join us today to build Wolt together.

Job Description

Together with our amazing People Analytics teammates from DoorDash, we’re looking for an Analytics Manager to lead our small but mighty team of analysts responsible for self-service reporting and deep dives across the People space. The ideal candidate will excel as a “player - coach”, excited to provide functional leadership to the team, provide thought partnership to their stakeholders, and roll up their sleeves to dive into the data themselves.

The role can be based in Finland (preferred), or Sweden. You can work onsite, hybrid, or fully remote from one of the mentioned locations - the work format is up to you

You will work directly with stakeholders across the Wolt people team (as well as the rest of the Wolt business), serving as their thought partner to solve problems and prioritize solutions to big, thorny questions. You will report directly to the US-based Sr. Manager of People Analytics at DoorDash, and will partner closely with them and your US-based peers in Recruiting Analytics and Data Science to lead People Analytics across the globe.

Your daily work will include

• Supervising the day-to-day work of your team of analysts responsible for people analytics, recruiting analytics, and similar.
• Serving as the trusted advisor, thought leader, and representative of the global People Analytics team to your stakeholders across Wolt.
• Leading the development of metrics, reports, dashboards and analyses, putting high-quality insights directly into the hands of your stakeholders.
• Developing a cohesive vision and roadmap together with your peers and partner teams across the globe, including US-based Data Science, People Analytics, Recruiting Analytics, Data Engineering, and People Applications teams.
• Dive into the data, diagnosing data and reporting needs, building new solutions, and providing answers to big, ambiguous, critical problems.

Qualifications

• Education: Degree in a quantitatively focused discipline, e.g., experimental psychology, economics, computer science, physics, or similar.
• Strong experience working as an Analyst, BI Developer, Analytics Engineer, Data Scientist, or techy Data Analyst. People/HR Analytics experience is strongly preferred.
• Experience leading small teams with outsized impact.
• Demonstrated experience working with and influencing technical and nontechnical cross-functional peers and stakeholders. This will be a highly visible role within the People Team, and building trust with your colleagues will be critical.
• Tech skills: Python, SQL, R, AWS, and one of the modern BI tools (Tableau, Power BI, Looker, Sigma, or similar). Advanced SQL skills, and ability to write optimized queries for large data sets.
• Subject Matter Expertise: Deep expertise in data visualization and analysis. Some expertise in statistics is preferred (regressions, t-tests). Nice to have: Experience analyzing survey data.
• Since you’ll be taking care of our internal stakeholders, we’re looking for someone who truly enjoys interacting with people on a daily basis. The ability to search for information and ask relevant questions from various teams will be crucial.

Additional Information

Why you'll love working with us

The position will be filled as soon as we find the right person, so make sure to apply as soon as you realize you really, really want to join us!

Complex environment with tons of data just waiting to be utilized — you’ll get hands-on experience in working on various TA metrics and topics.

You can choose the ways of working - work onsite, hybrid, or fully remote from one of the locations mentioned above.

You would get to work in a company culture where we take ownership beyond the obvious, do common things uncommonly well, think big but stay humble, do right by people, treat others kindly and justly, and recognize that if we don’t learn, we won’t stay still but fall behind and keep in mind that Luke was Yoda’s greatest achievement. Read more about how we work.

If you are excited about working in a high-growth environment, taking ownership, and being part of an extremely ambitious team, then click below to apply and get the conversation going!

If you have any further questions about the position, you can turn to:

Orsi Kocsis, Senior Talent Acquisition Partner - orsolya.kocsis@wolt.com

Please note that we do not accept applications sent by mail. You should submit your application through our careers website!

description:
Join Our Team VIPAS AB as a Camunda Engineer

Do you have what it takes to thrive in the vibrant world of IT consulting? VIPAS AB, a burgeoning company, proudly invites you to embark on your next engaging project as our Camunda Engineer

About VIPAS :

Imagine a world where your business technology perfectly aligns with your goals—efficient, scalable, and innovative. At VIPAS AB, that’s exactly what we strive to create. As an IT consulting company, we don’t just offer services; we deliver tailored solutions using cutting-edge technologies like Java and Python. Our team is well-versed in software development, DevOps, and engineering, bringing years of experience and expertise. Think of us as your trusted guide, leading your organization through the landscape of modern tech adoption, ensuring every step is taken with confidence and foresight.

Job Description

We are seeking a skilled Camunda Engineer to help design, develop, and implement business process management solutions using Camunda BPM. In this role, you will collaborate with cross-functional teams to understand business requirements and translate them into effective workflow and process automation solutions. You will play a key role in optimizing business processes and integrating them with various systems to drive efficiency and performance.

Key Responsibilities:

Workflow Design and Implementation: Design, model, and implement complex workflows using Camunda, ensuring efficient automation of business processes.

Integration Expertise: Integrate Camunda with existing systems and applications to ensure seamless communication and data flow.

Customization and Configuration: Customize Camunda to meet specific business requirements, configuring processes and decision tables for optimal performance.

Technical Documentation: Create comprehensive technical documentation for implemented workflows, integrations, and configurations.

Collaboration: Work closely with cross-functional teams, including business analysts and developers, to understand business needs and translate them into effective Camunda solutions.

Requirements:

Experience Level: 8-10 years in IT with 4-5 years of relevant experience as a Camunda Developer.
Strong proficiency in Camunda BPM platform, including BPMN, DMN, and CMMN.
Proficient in Java or JavaScript for backend development and workflow customization.
Solid experience with REST APIs, microservices architecture, and integration techniques.
Familiarity with relational databases such as MySQL, PostgreSQL, or SQL Server.
Experience with DevOps practices and tools like Jenkins, CI/CD pipelines, and Docker.
Strong problem-solving and analytical skills, with the ability to troubleshoot and optimize processes.
Excellent communication skills and a collaborative mindset.
Fluent in English; Swedish is a plus.

Nice to Have:

Experience with cloud platforms like AWS, Azure, or Google Cloud.
Knowledge of additional programming languages like Python or Kotlin.
Familiarity with Kubernetes, Docker, and container orchestration.
Understanding of messaging systems like Kafka or RabbitMQ

description:
Join our global force of 500+ innovators, blending the latest in tech with the greatest in soundtracking, from our Stockholm HQ to offices in London, New York, Los Angeles, Berlin, Oslo, and Seoul. We’re an industry leader with a startup mentality. We take what we do seriously, but we don’t take ourselves too seriously. Creating and collaborating to transform the sound of streaming, content, and culture. Come join us—and let the world feel your work.

We are looking for Senior Backend Engineers

The Payments Team is focused on enhancing seamless payment experiences and subscription management while tackling the challenge of migrating from a legacy monolithic to an event-driven architecture. Through collaboration across engineering, product management, and stakeholders, we aim to optimize user journeys and drive Epidemic Sound’s growth.

As a team, we value open collaboration, tackling complex technical challenges together, and sharing knowledge through pair and mob programming as well as regular hack weeks. Your insights will shape and influence the team’s roadmap, so we're looking for someone who thrives in a dynamic environment and embraces uncertainty.

What You’ll Do

Develop and maintain high-performance backend systems with a focus on payment and subscription services
Design and implement REST APIs and microservices using Kotlin (Ktor) or Python (FastAPI), ensuring scalability and reliability
Collaborate with frontend engineers, product managers, and data teams to create cohesive, impactful solutions
Champion best practices in CI/CD, DevOps, and testing, leveraging tools like Kubernetes and Google Cloud Platform (GCP) for robust deployment pipelines
Drive experimentation through A/B testing and growth-focused methodologies to iteratively improve user engagement and experience

Who You Are

System Design Expertise: You have a solid understanding of system design principles and distributed architecture, enabling you to build scalable and reliable backend services
Experienced Developer: You bring 5+ years of experience in backend development with expertise in Java with Kotlin or Python
DevOps Knowledge: Familiarity with Docker, Kubernetes, Google Cloud Platform (GCP) or AWS

Nice to Have:

Go
Terraform

Soft Skills

Adaptability: Quickly adjust to changing priorities and evolving technologies in a fast-paced scaleup environment
Collaboration: Strong teamwork abilities for effective cross-functional engagement and knowledge sharing
Problem-Solving Mindset: Proactively identify challenges and devise innovative solutions to drive progress and improve processes

Equal Opportunity Employer:

We believe that bringing people together from different backgrounds, experiences and perspectives makes for a healthy workplace, a more successful business and a better world. We value diversity and encourage everyone to come and soundtrack the world with us.

Application
Do you want to be a part of our fantastic team? Please apply, in English, by clicking the link below.

description:
Are you enthusiastic about complex system development and financial products/services? If so, consider the opportunity to join AARO, a Swedish product company specializing in the development of a comprehensive system for group accounting, reporting, and analysis.

At AARO, you will have the opportunity to engage with the dynamic reality of the largest business groups in the country, offering a stimulating, challenging, and global work environment. Intrigued?

Explore further and submit your application today!

Role Description

As System Developer you will be a part of an agile development team that delivers new features, upgrades and customizations to the "AARO platform". This platform is an adaptable system utilized by 30% of the groups listed on the OMX Large- and Mid-cap list.

You, together with your team will take ownership of the development process and play a vital role in realizing the technical vision. You will analyze requirements, design and develop new features as well as fixing bugs and improving the current code base.

The tech stack consists out of Java, Wildfly/Jboss, MS SQL, GWT, React, Bootstrap, TypeScript, Scala, Azure (cloud hosting) and Python. They also use tools such as Jira, Git and Jenkins. Your contribution and insights will impact future choices of technology and tools.

To work at AARO gives you both freedom and a high level of involvement. The organization has short decision paths and the step from idea to action is short. They also have lots of fun together!

The placement is situated in one of AARO's offices, either in Stockholm, Malmö, or Gothenburg.

Is this you?
We welcome applications from both Senior Backend Developers with expertise in Java, and highly driven junior candidates aspiring to enhance their skills in complex system development. Previous experience of implementing new technologies and knowledge of architectural concepts will be considered a significant advantage.

In terms of personality, we are seeking individuals with outstanding problem-solving abilities who find satisfaction in analyzing and resolving complex issues, ranging from code-related challenges to interpreting industry-relevant legislation. Collaboration is a highly valued, and we appreciate candidates who enjoy working with others, exploring innovative technologies, and sharing their discoveries. Additionally, effective communication skills, both in writing and verbally in English, are essential attributes.

A background check is a mandatory requirement for the last step of the recruitment process.

Interested to know more?

In this recruitment AARO is collaborating with IDG Recruitment. If you are interested or have any questions contact recruitment consultant Moa Eriksson at 070 828 36 65 or moa.eriksson@idg.se. Please apply with your CV or LinkedIn profile and we will get back to you as soon as possible. Selection and interviews are ongoing.

We are looking forward to hearing from you!

About AARO

AARO has a vision to make group consolidation simpler, quicker, and more transparent. Having developed and refined our product for over 30 years, we are able today to offer a complete system that meets the needs for reporting, consolidation, group accounting, operational follow-up, and analysis – for both large and small business groups.

At AARO we have 150 specialists in group reporting, consolidation, system development, IT operations, sales, project management, and product management. Our offices are in Stockholm, Malmö, Gothenburg, Kalix, Helsinki, Riga, Dubai, and Nairobi. Since the company started, it has grown strongly. Of the groups listed on the Stockholm OMX Large Cap list, 30% use AARO.
descriptionHTML:
Are you enthusiastic about complex system development and financial products/services? If so, consider the opportunity to join AARO, a Swedish product company specializing in the development of a comprehensive system for group accounting, reporting, and analysis.

At AARO, you will have the opportunity to engage with the dynamic reality of the largest business groups in the country, offering a stimulating, challenging, and global work environment. Intrigued?

Explore further and submit your application today!


Role Description

As System Developer you will be a part of an agile development team that delivers new features, upgrades and customizations to the "AARO platform". This platform is an adaptable system utilized by 30% of the groups listed on the OMX Large- and Mid-cap list.

You, together with your team will take ownership of the development process and play a vital role in realizing the technical vision. You will analyze requirements, design and develop new features as well as fixing bugs and improving the current code base.


The tech stack consists out of Java, Wildfly/Jboss, MS SQL, GWT, React, Bootstrap, TypeScript, Scala, Azure (cloud hosting) and Python. They also use tools such as Jira, Git and Jenkins. Your contribution and insights will impact future choices of technology and tools.

To work at AARO gives you both freedom and a high level of involvement. The organization has short decision paths and the step from idea to action is short. They also have lots of fun together!


The placement is situated in one of AARO's offices, either in Stockholm, Malmö, or Gothenburg.


Is this you?
We welcome applications from both Senior Backend Developers with expertise in Java, and highly driven junior candidates aspiring to enhance their skills in complex system development. Previous experience of implementing new technologies and knowledge of architectural concepts will be considered a significant advantage.


In terms of personality, we are seeking individuals with outstanding problem-solving abilities who find satisfaction in analyzing and resolving complex issues, ranging from code-related challenges to interpreting industry-relevant legislation. Collaboration is a highly valued, and we appreciate candidates who enjoy working with others, exploring innovative technologies, and sharing their discoveries. Additionally, effective communication skills, both in writing and verbally in English, are essential attributes.


A background check is a mandatory requirement for the last step of the recruitment process.


Interested to know more?

In this recruitment AARO is collaborating with IDG Recruitment. If you are interested or have any questions contact recruitment consultant Moa Eriksson at 070 828 36 65 or moa.eriksson@idg.se. Please apply with your CV or LinkedIn profile and we will get back to you as soon as possible. Selection and interviews are ongoing.

We are looking forward to hearing from you!


About AARO

AARO has a vision to make group consolidation simpler, quicker, and more transparent. Having developed and refined our product for over 30 years, we are able today to offer a complete system that meets the needs for reporting, consolidation, group accounting, operational follow-up, and analysis – for both large and small business groups.

At AARO we have 150 specialists in group reporting, consolidation, system development, IT operations, sales, project management, and product management. Our offices are in Stockholm, Malmö, Gothenburg, Kalix, Helsinki, Riga, Dubai, and Nairobi. Since the company started, it has grown strongly. Of the groups listed on the Stockholm OMX Large Cap list, 30% use AARO.

description:
We are looking for full-stack developers with focus on front-End who want to work as a consultant in a smaller company with growth ambitions. You work individually, are innovative and have the ability to develop useful solutions that contribute to business benefit. You are used to teamwork and familiar with agile development.

About the role

As a system developer, you understand solutions in an overall perspective. Your specialty is to see and create solutions that meet customer needs. You can effectively structure code and have a good understanding of how to create good user experience. You have experience of the software development process, code standard and version control.

To fit in with us you have:

At least 8 years of experience in modern software development
At least 4 years of documented experience in web development.
At least 5 years of experience in Javascript/TypeScript, Node.js, CSS, HTML, Razor,
Proficiency in front-end frameworks like React, Blazor or Angular
In-depth knowledge of automated build and deployment environments
Solid knowledge of deploying cloud services in like AWS, Azure & GCP
General understanding of REST APIs
Understanding of container technology, for example Docker and Kubernetes.
Worked with version control systems like Git.

It would be a plus if you have:

Experience using automated unit tests in development.
Experience in Microservice architecture.
Experience in other languages like Java, Go, SQL, Python, Django, Spark, Scala.
Infrastructure as Code (for example Bicep, Pulumi, or Terraform)
Experience in Adobe AEM

Above all, you are curious, responsible, flexible, and aspiring to develop innovative products and services.

About Recommit:

We have three key words - Care, Share and Commit - something that defines how we are in our daily work, in the meeting with our customers and towards each other

Recommit offers a foundation for our co-workers to enhance their technical skills within IT. We strongly believe in knowledge sharing and are always passionate to learn from each other

Our employees consist of senior technology developers as well as young talents that disrupt with new ideas for innovations and opportunities. We know that the best teams consist of a mixed group of individuals

We endorse cultural diversity and have long experience in relocating new coworkers to our company and country. Recommit is certified by the Swedish Migration Agency and we can in short period of time handle the process of a valid work permit. We also try to help as much as possible in all aspects when in come to integrate to Sweden and the Swedish society .

Recommit AB was founded in 2010 and our office is located in central Stockholm

Application:

Does this sound like something for you? Apply today and meet us for a first Teams meeting. If you have any questions, please contact Jonas Falkowski Källman at jonas.kallman@recommit.se, or +46733113114

We are looking forward to your application!

description:
Company Description

Forloop.ai is a Swedish-Czech startup founded on the ambition to solve the problem that most (87%) of machine-learning projects never make it to production. Largely due to time, effort and complexity to handle data and data pipelines for ML.

To solve that - Forloop.ai provides an easy-to-use data pipeline and preparation tool, with personalised intelligent recommendations. Forloop.ai is a tool for Data Scientists to accelerate the mundane, yet critical tasks, of turning source data into model ready data.

Ultimately, Forloop.ai enables Data Scientists to focus on the creative aspects of data that drive the business forward.

Job Description

Forloop.ai is looking for a Lead Front‌ End‌ developer. You will get an unique opportunity to play a key role from an early-stage in forming the product, the chosen tech stack, its roadmap, and help shape the team behind it. You will partner with the Founding team to help develop the product from beta stage through public launch and beyond. Your main focus will be on building of our unique drag-and-drop application.

We see that you excel in taking responsibility both from a technical and team aspect, and thrive in seeing the results. This is a key role for the company - you should enjoy the thrill of taking initiatives that drive forward the product, the team, and the company as a whole.

We do not value experience over talent and drive to develop. So even if it is a senior lead position, we are open for other applicants as well that can see this as a way to take the next step.

Qualifications

OUR PREFERRED STACK

Tech stack:

Javascript, React.js framework, CSS, HTML, Typescript (nice to have)

Libraries:

React, Redux, React-router, Reselect, Redux-saga, Styled-components, Material UI, Ant Design, i18next, Webpack, Redux Form, Axios

Drag-and-drop libraries (nice to have):

React-dnd, React-draggable, React-digraph, or something better :)

Testing:

Cypress.io

Error tracking, monitoring:

Sentry.io

Backend (will not be your responsibility but if you know some of these it‘s a plus)

Python, Flask, Python ML Libraries, ETLs, SQL

UI/UX/Product (nice to have):

Figma, Adobe Xd, Material design, Bootstrap

Additional Information

WHAT ELSE SHOULD YOU HAVE?

University degree (or any comparable past experience)
Extended experience with front end technologies
Version control – Git
Interest in new front end trends and technologies
Experience with REST API
Clean code best practices
Analytical mind, Be a team player
Reliability and enthusiasm towards new challenges
English language at a sufficient level – we are international team
Startup environment experience. (nice to have)
Understanding of data problems or data science domain (nice to have)
Awareness of Data Science products. (nice to have)

WHY US?

We are quite a new startup (started at the end of 2020) with a potential and global ambition to change the way data science is currently done and you can be the part of the mission. We are based in Stockholm and Prague and we build a company based on values like being remote friendly, inclusive, and international. We have also secured a fresh funding from a Berlin-based investor fund. Come and help us changing the data science world.

OTHER PERKS:

Have a key role and impact the direction of the company.
Personal and career development with having a leadership role in a heavily technical product, with a talented and ambitious team, in a dynamic and fast growing market.
Chance to manage and lead an engineering team.
A fun, friendly, and collaborative environment
A competitive salary and a possibility to participate in our attractive stock options plan
Work from anywhere.

description:
We're a group of engineers hailing from leading innovators like Spotify, King, Anyfin, Sinch, and Einride. We've joined forces with some of the brightest minds in banking to assist entrepreneurs in growing their businesses smarter and faster.

Traditionally, founders have been left to navigate the fundraising journey alone. Today, the industry is evolving towards data-driven investment decisions, where investors crave numbers and data-backed pitches. We think this shift is great since it fosters a less biased and more diverse innovation ecosystem. Gilion's mission is clear: develop tools and improved funding options to simplify the lives of innovative founders.

By connecting to the Gilion platform, founders gain access to a comprehensive analytics tech stack right off the bat. Our platform provides stunning visualizations that narrate the story of their company, without the need for a single line of SQL or CSS. Historical data, coupled with Gilion's advanced forecasting capabilities, simulates future scenarios, offering a unique understanding of performance compared to relevant peers. Check out this video to delve deeper into what we're all about.

“I’ve never seen my company like this. We use Gilion to make strategic decisions and also to pitch our growth journey to investors.”

- Founder of a tech company based in Denmark

What you’ll do at Gilion

The tech team iterates fast. Being data nerds, we measure user behavior and verify our bets through user testing. We balance rapid iteration experiments with long-term strategic bets and continuous improvements to our infrastructure.

As a senior backend engineer at Gilion, you will be part of a cross functional product team working alongside other developers, designers and machine learning specialists.

You’ll contribute to architectural decisions as part of a functional team working across the product teams.

Working hands on, developing micro services in Go or Python on our infrastructure built with Kubernetes, Docker, Github and GCP.

Experiment with new technologies, especially utilizing the latest machine learning applications, both to improve developer experience but also our products.

Take part in a low overhead, product development process where ideas go to production in days and deployments to production happen multiple times a day.

We’d love to hear from you if you have:

5+ years of working as a professional software engineer

Experience of working in a cross functional team

An openness to learn and thrive in tackling a variety of problems that you might not have seen before.

A collaborative mindset where you leverage your colleagues expertise for coming up with a better solution together.

A leadership mindset or experience from leading initiatives or teams

While it’s not required, it’s an added plus if you also have:

A DevOps mindset and understanding of infrastructure and tooling

Experience with security, architecture and/or cloud technologies

At Gilion, we’re all about Growth. We believe in hiring great people with the right values and giving them a platform to grow with. Our unique combination of startup mentality, experienced team and ambitious vision make room for endless possibilities.

Does this sound interesting? We look forward to your application!

description:
About Brite

Brite Payments is a leading Open Banking-powered Account to Account (A2A) payment provider of Instant Payments and Instant Payouts. We provide a convenient transaction experience for consumers and reduce the risk in the payment process for merchants. Founded in Stockholm in 2019, Brite is committed to providing the best possible payment solution for everyone involved in a transaction.

The team behind Brite has worked with launching the first-generation of fintech companies before founding Brite. We know the market landscape, technologies, opportunities, and challenges. Now we channel all those experiences into developing modern solutions that will benefit both merchants and end-users.

Want to join us on our journey? The future is Brite!

What you will do

At Brite you will be part of our highly skilled QA team where we take accountability for the QA and Test strategy, toolset, and processes. We also work across the Engineering teams to support them in their quality and test work as well as assisting them with deploying high quality solutions.

Your responsibilities will include

Work on a daily basis with the QA and Test domains at the company. Together with your fellow QA team mates you take accountability for our QA and Test Strategies, the test management and the testing tools and frameworks we need to deliver quality products.
Supporting one or multiple Engineering teams as they mature in writing and executing tests and other quality verification tools. Your focus is on improving how the team works.
In this senior role you are also expected to be a mentor for other QA engineers as they grow their skill sets over time.
Reporting and Monitoring tools are a vital part of improving our work, both in engineering and in QA. You are going to share responsibility with other engineers in improving our tools.

With that said, you will be a vital part of the next fintech unicorn!

Are you a brite mind?

You are a leader with a solid technical background in modern development. You have experience from managing or facilitating technical collaborations between teams and departments. In the past you have had formal leadership roles such as Tech Lead, Development Manager or as an Architect. You have experience collaborating in creating Architectural visions and how to communicate them to the relevant stakeholders. You are a developer at heart! The ideal candidate has:

Experience in Test Automation and manual software testing.
Experience from working in a micro service architecture
Knowledge of Quality Assurance principles, methods and techniques
5+ year of professional work experience
Having mentored other QA engineers, for example in a formal or informal leadership role.

Good to have experience:

Experience with Selenium, Cypress or any other relevant modern automation tool
Experience with Postman, Charles
Experience with Javascript/Typescript, Python
Knowledge of Gherkin or another BDD tool.

What we offer

An optimistic, caring, and inclusive culture where we want you to be yourself
A dynamic, fast-paced, and innovative environment where you will have the possibility to make an impact from your first day onwards
A flat organization, friendly colleagues, and fast decision-making
An environment where we start small and learn fast to do big things
A team that cares about sharing, collaborative work, and prestigelessness
... and you will be part of a growing team of fun and skilled people

Do you want to learn more about our recruitment process? Here you can read about the hiring flow and find answers to the most frequently asked questions.

Please apply with your CV or your LinkedIn profile. We use screening questions to streamline this recruitment process, so a personal letter is not needed.
