description:
Technology | DataScientist | Stockholm, Sweden

Who we are

We are ferritico, a Swedish software company disrupting the global steel industry. Based on more than 10 years of world leading KTH research we are developing a machine learning tool provided to our customers as a SaaS. The ferritico service digitalizes the processes of developing, manufacturing and implementing steel, helping our customers to significantly cut time and costs.

We aggregate large sets of steel properties and process data and apply machine learning models enabling our customers to predict and view correlations in data when optimizing materials, products and processes. Ferritico is well funded through support from i.a. EIT and Vinnova although already generating revenues. Ferritico is used in production by two global steel companies and ferritico is currently strengthening the team with a Data Scientist as a consequence of increased service demand.

The Opportunity

This employment constitutes a unique opportunity to join the ferritico team in central Stockholm. As a Data Scientist you will be given a lot of responsibility and autonomy in developing our models and machine learning software. As we are still a small team, you will be given a unique opportunity to shape the digitalization of the steel industry by:

Managing and organizing the aggregation and cleaning of databases in collaboration with our materials engineers

Developing machine learning models and implement these with our software developers to optimize for our customers

Validating previously developed models as well as future models

Maintaining and monitoring models in production and support customers in performing model simulations

You are passionate

about developing result-focused and innovative machine learning solutions. You embrace new technology and the opportunity to contributeto and learn from related competence fields while taking responsibility for your deliverables.

Requirements:

Masters, PhD, or equivalent experience in a quantitative field (Computer Science, Mathematics, Engineering, Artificial Intelligence, etc.)

Experience with at least one programming language, preferably Python, and SQL databases.

Machine learning in R, scikit-learn and pandas libraries

Rigorous attention to detail and focus on quality of deliverables

Ambitious and independent self-learner with genuine interest for data, statistical modeling and machine learning software

Meriting skills:

Interest in or experience from materials engineering and especially the steel industry.

Basic understanding of front-end development frameworks, e.g. React and bootstrap.

Happy to communicate with customers, outline their processes and propose machine learning solutions

Git for version management.

Experience from using AWS hosting solutions.

Apply now

by sending us your resume to contact@ferritico.com. Add subject line “Data Scientist”.

Please contact Claes Holmström if you have any questions: +46 (0)8 121 530 05

Apply now

description:
We seek a highly skilled and experienced Telecom Software Developer to join our dynamic team. The ideal candidate will have a strong background in telecom, particularly in baseband ULPHY development.

Responsibilities:

Collaborate with the team to design and implement L1 solutions.
Develop telecom software modules utilizing Python and C languages.
Participate in the development of test tools for telecom software validation.
Conduct troubleshooting and problem-solving for baseband ULPHY issues.
Work independently and in a team environment to meet project deadlines.
Communicate effectively with team members and stakeholders.

Requirements:

Bachelor's degree in Telecommunications, Electrical Engineering, or a related field.
Proven experience working as a Telecom Software Developer or in a similar role.
Proficiency in Python and C programming languages.
Strong understanding of L1 basics, particularly in baseband ULPHY.
Excellent troubleshooting and problem-solving skills.
Ability to work independently and in a team environment.
Excellent communication and interpersonal skills.

Advantages:

Certification in Telecommunications or related field.
Familiarity with test tool development technologies.

WHY K TWO?

Our consultants are renowned for their high technical expertise, interpersonal skills, experience, responsiveness, and winning demeanor. You should have strong technical skills, good values, and be a great team player. We're assembling winners!

Sounds interesting?

We hope so! We place significant emphasis on personal qualities and your commitment. If you share our values and want growth, please get in touch!

description:
About Us

With over 85 million global active users and 2,5 million transactions per day, Klarna is on the way to becoming the world’s favorite way to shop. To help us get there, we’re assembling an unparalleled global talent team—accelerating individual careers, and disrupting entire industries. We’re looking for people ready to achieve the extraordinary and embrace our bold ambitions as we shape the future of payments and fintech. Will you join us?

What You Will Do

As a Senior Offensive Security Engineer at Klarna, you will be at the forefront of safeguarding our digital infrastructure and customer data. This position demands a blend of hacking skills, creativity, and a deep understanding of cyber threats. You will simulate sophisticated cyber attacks to identify vulnerabilities, ensuring Klarna's resilience against real-world threats. Collaborating with cross-functional teams, you will provide actionable insights to fortify our security posture.

Conduct white-box and black-box penetration testing against internal and public-facing applications and assets
Manage, triage, and investigate Bug Bounty submissions and external pentest findings
Perform variant analysis on issues discovered through all channels
Research and perform security analyses on Klarna’s 3rd-party solutions
Develop tooling to support reconnaissance, automation, and metrics collection
Provide expert guidance to developers, other product security teams, and the SOC in investigating issues
Spread awareness of offensive security practices via demos, workshops, and training
Assess the security of our tech stack through whatever means are best suited
Define what we focus on to provide the most value
Help further mature Klarna’s security program

Who You Are

Strong experience with penetration testing and other technical security assessments
Experience identifying security issues in code, particularly within Java and Node.js
Experience with cloud environments, particularly AWS and modern micro-service design principles
Comfortable communicating findings clearly and effectively, with concrete remediation recommendations beyond simple issue reporting
Comfortable scripting and contributing to larger projects in Python
Able to take the initiative and be comfortable taking on projects that contribute to the larger security culture and posture at Klarna
Industry recognized certifications, e.g., OSCP, OSWE, CREST, GIAC, AWS, et. al
CTF Participation and active contributions to the cybersecurity community

What We Offer

Collaboration within a diverse team that values innovation and creativity.
Culture - You'll have an opportunity to work with people from 90+ different countries in our English-speaking offices in Milan city center
A challenging scope with the opportunity to work with latest technologies

Klarna's Compensation model and Equity Offering
At Klarna, our compensation package includes a base salary and Restricted Stock Units (RSUs). To ensure fairness and maintain global market competitiveness, each role in a specific location has a set base salary. During the recruitment process, we will assess your skills and experience to determine which role is the best fit for you.
Our RSU program features a 4-year vesting schedule, allowing you to gradually become a shareholder in Klarna. Additionally, you may qualify for our Contribution-Based Reward (CBR) program, which recognizes and rewards significant contributions to our success.

Total Compensation
745 360 - 834 803 SEK

Closing
Please include a CV in English.

description:
Join our global force of 500+ innovators, blending the latest in tech with the greatest in soundtracking, from our Stockholm HQ to offices in London, New York, Los Angeles, Berlin, Oslo, and Seoul. We’re an industry leader with a startup mentality. We take what we do seriously, but we don’t take ourselves too seriously. Creating and collaborating to transform the sound of streaming, content, and culture. Come join us—and let the world feel your work.

We are looking for a Senior Growth Engineer to help us take our platform to the next level! The position is full-time and based in Stockholm.

How you will make an impact

Acquisition is seeking an experienced Growth Engineer with a strong focus on frontend development and user acquisition/growth to join our team. You’ll play a vital role in optimizing our conversion rate and shaping the first impression of visitors' interaction with Epidemicsound.com. You’ll work on public pages, signup flows, and the necessary tools and infrastructure required for user acquisition.

What you’ll do

Collaborate closely with product teams, SEO team, and Performance Marketing team to drive growth and conversion rate optimization
Conduct A/B tests and analyze data to improve user experience
Act as an architect, taking ownership of complex technical projects, including planning, cross-team collaboration, and impact evaluation
Utilize your expertise in frontend web development technologies such as Typescript, React, Next.js, HTML, and CSS
Leverage your experience in backend development, particularly in Python and/or frameworks like Django
Fostering an inclusive and collaborative culture
Embrace agile development processes, including pair and mob programming, to share knowledge

What you’ll bring

Experience from working as a fullstack developer, with focus on frontend development
Strong knowledge using Typescript, React, HTML and CSS
Experience from working with full stack frameworks like Django or Ruby on Rails.
Strong interest in user growth, A/B testing, and interest and knowledge in experimentation and product analytics
Experience working with web application performance, reliability, monitoring, and CI/CD

It would also be music to our ears if you have/are:

Familiar with SEO practices
Knowledge of CMS systems

Most importantly

If you possess strong communication skills, a collaborative spirit, and a passion for personal and professional development, this is the opportunity you’ve been looking for. Join our team to work in an environment that fosters innovation and embraces diversity.

description:
At CatalystOne, we’re transforming the future through technology. As we expand our innovative integration services, we’re looking for an Integration Developer to join our dynamic team. If you’re passionate about building cutting-edge solutions and thrive in a collaborative environment, we want to hear from you!

Catalystone is on a mission to become the central system in our customers' IT landscapes for employment master data. Our Technical Consultation (TC) team has split into two specialized roles to better meet growing demands: Technical Consultants who advise and guide, and Integration Developers who build and maintain integrations. Together, we deliver seamless, high-quality solutions with a customer-focused approach.

What you'll do as Integration Developer
Building and Maintaining Integrations: Design, develop, and maintain customer integrations and standard integrations for partners.
Collaborative Problem Solving: Work closely with Technical Consultants to ensure integration solutions are effective and high-quality.
Platform Development: Update, develop, and maintain our integrations platform to enhance our service capabilities.
Customer-Focused Solutions: Engage in discussions with third parties and internal IT departments to build optimal solutions.
Documentation: Document integration processes, architecture, and code for future reference and maintenance.
Daily Operations: Handle error messages for current integrations, maintain and update existing ones, and participate in scrum activities like sprint planning and daily stand-ups.

Requirements

Educational Background: Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Software Engineering, or a related field, or equivalent work experience.
Technical Experience: Proven experience as a senior developer or in a similar role, with proficiency in Python or C#.
Integration Expertise: Solid understanding of different types of APIs, Microsoft Azure integration services, and experience with Git (CI/CD).
Agile Methodology: Familiarity with Scrum and agile development processes.
Languages: Fluency in a Scandinavian language and English.

Benefits

As well as your salary, you’ll receive:

Financial and Health Security: Benefit from a comprehensive pension and insurance package, plus private healthcare.
Your Well-being, Your Way: Take advantage of our wellness contribution to stay on top of your health.
Tech Tools for Efficiency: Get the job done with a choice of laptop (mac / PC), mobile phone & subscription, and a home internet allowance.
Flexible Work Setup: Hybrid for your life-work balance.
And more country-specific benefits

CatalystOne does not accept unsolicited resumes from search firms/recruiters. CatalystOne will not pay any fees to search firms/recruiters if a candidate is submitted by a search firm/recruiter unless an agreement has been entered into with respect to the specific open position(s). Search firms/recruiters submitting resumes to CatalystOne on an unsolicited basis shall be deemed to accept this condition, regardless of any other provision to the contrary.

We would like to inform you that all candidates who receive a job offer will be subject to a background check.

description:
We are looking for a Technical Designer to join one of the game teams here at Embark, a team that is currently numbering around ~100 developers.

In this role you will be responsible for the technical design work on a project by creating, implementing and maintaining tools, systems and other workflows as a bridge between design and code.

You will collaborate closely with the Design Director and other Designers of the project, as well as Production leadership helping in articulating and establishing estimates, project scope and timelines.

Example of responsibilities

Help design and prove new features by developing prototypes for the design team to experiment with
Help identify technical pitfalls and challenges in our designs, offering possible solutions or alternatives
Contribute tool and workflow improvement ideas, especially design tools
Help design, balance and tweak our more technical gameplay systems, for example environmental destruction
Work with other disciplines to help align design intent with non-design pipelines and tech

We would love if you have

3+ years of experience within technical design making games
A good grasp of AAA PvP gameplay and systems design, including player psychology, UX design and gameplay mechanics and dynamics
Proficiency with the Unreal Engine and experience in scripting and blueprints
Knowledge of the UnrealEngine-Angelscript plugin is a big plus, but not required
Knowledge of programming languages such as C#, Lua, Python
A creative and curious mind
A good knowledge or familiarity with other game making disciplines such as animation, game physics, 3D Art, etc.
A great creative collaborator in cross disciplinary groups
Professional English communication skills

At Embark we offer competitive salaries, passionate colleagues to share knowledge with and much more, but most of all we invite you to take part of a journey into the unknown, to build creative, surprising and beautiful experiences together.

We welcome game makers of all sex, class, colour, age, gender identity, education, religion, opinion, culture, nation of origin, language, sexual orientation, shape, size, and ability.

Did we leave anyone out? Well, we welcome you, too! We think that the gaming industry is made better when everyone has a seat at the table.

Be yourself at Embark and make games while doing so. Please apply with confidence. We can’t wait to hear from you (in English)!

If this role doesn't quite match what you're looking for, feel free to apply to us via our "Open Application."

description:
About Brite

Founded in 2019, Brite Payments is a leading open banking-powered account-to-account (A2A) payment provider of instant payments, payouts, and other financial services in Europe. Brite is committed to creating fast, secure, and transparent payment solutions that reduce risk for businesses and provide consumers with the best possible payment experience.

At the heart of Brite is our proprietary instant payments network, Brite IPN, which enables real-time, 24/7 transaction processing with no delays, sign-ups, or card details required. Today, Brite connects with over 3,800 banks in 27 European markets and is committed to delivering cutting-edge, next-generation payment solutions that meet the market’s evolving needs.

Headquartered in Stockholm, Brite has offices in London and Malaga and now numbers over 150 colleagues.

Want to join us on our journey? The future is Brite!

What you will do

As a Senior Software Engineer at Brite you will work with our core team of highly skilled developers. Your tasks will be to develop and build a scalable and future-proof framework. You will work on building components to bridge between us and the banks across Europe, in order to deliver authentication (AIS) and payment initiation (PIS). As a Developer at Brite, you will have a major impact on building the foundation of our core platform. With that said, you will be a vital part of the next fintech unicorn!

Are you a brite mind?

Experience in systems development in Python
Experience with Cloud Computing (Google cloud)
At least 3 years of developer work experience

Meriting experience:

AWS, Azure
Kubernetes
Microservice architecture
GO or React

Preferred skills:

A degree in Computer Science or related technical field, or equivalent practical experience
Experience from building scalable, service-oriented architectures
Experience from working with transaction-intensive systems
Experience with Docker
Experience with Javascript/Typescript
Experience with information security from a systems development perspective (OWASP, encryption, etc.)

What we offer

An optimistic, caring, and inclusive culture where we want you to be yourself
A dynamic, fast-paced, and innovative environment where you will have the possibility to make an impact from your first day onwards.
A flat organization, friendly colleagues, and fast decision-making
An environment where we start small and learn fast to do big things
A team that cares about sharing, collaborative work, and prestigeless approach
A yearly wellness allowance and Tuesday breakfasts at the office
... and you will be part of a growing team of fun and skilled people

description:
We are seeking someone who:

- Represents ambition and strength as a valuable team member in a dynamic workplace.

- Demonstrates a self-driven spirit, recognizing the importance of adaptability in ever-changing environments.

- Understands that success is a collective effort, placing a strong emphasis on genuine teamwork.

- Exhibits high levels of drive, determination, and commitment.

About the Job:

We're actively seeking skilled Software Engineers to join our company and contribute to the essential aspects of enhancing Developer Experience (DX) and optimizing CI/CD pipelines and monitoring systems. In this role, you'll have the opportunity to apply your expertise to develop and maintain innovative tools and infrastructure that empower our development teams and ensure seamless integration and deployment processes.

Requirements:

- Bachelor's Degree in a related discipline or equivalent years of experience

- Extensive experience with Developer Experience tools, including https://backstage.io/

- Proficiency in DevOps practices and AI tools for developers (e.g., Codeium)

- Experience as a VS Code plugin developer

- Strong knowledge of CI/CD pipelines and monitoring systems

- Expertise in Linux, Nephio, Spinnaker, Jenkins, GitLab, Grafana, Kibana

- Proficiency in Kubernetes, Docker, Git

- Strong programming skills in GoLang, Python, Groovy (scripting/glue code), and Java

- Excellent communication skills

Advantages:

- Experience with cutting-edge technologies and tools

- Opportunities for professional growth and skill development

- A collaborative and innovative work environment

- Competitive salary and benefits package

Job Location: Bangalore, India

WHY K TWO?

At K Two, our consultants are renowned for their high technical and social competence, extensive experience, responsiveness, and winning demeanor. We value not only skilled developers, technicians, and project managers but also effective consultants. We're in the business of assembling winners. Join us, where working for and with K Two is more than just a job; it's a rewarding experience!

Sounds interesting?

We hope so! Throughout the selection process, we will place significant emphasis on personal qualities and your commitment. If you believe you align with the above profile and wish to be part of our successful team, we eagerly await receiving your application!

  • Proficiency in DevOps practices and AI tools for developers (e.g., Codeium)
  • Experience as a VS Code plugin developer
  • Strong knowledge of CI/CD pipelines and monitoring systems
  • Expertise in Linux, Nephio, Spinnaker, Jenkins, GitLab, Grafana, Kibana
  • Proficiency in Kubernetes, Docker, Git
  • Strong programming skills in GoLang, Python, Groovy (scripting/glue code), and Java
  • Excellent communication skills

Advantages:

  • Experience with cutting-edge technologies and tools
  • Opportunities for professional growth and skill development
  • A collaborative and innovative work environment
  • Competitive salary and benefits package

Job Location: Bangalore, India

WHY K TWO?

At K Two, our consultants are renowned for their high technical and social competence, extensive experience, responsiveness, and winning demeanor. We value not only skilled developers, technicians, and project managers but also effective consultants. We're in the business of assembling winners. Join us, where working for and with K Two is more than just a job; it's a rewarding experience!

Sounds interesting?

We hope so! Throughout the selection process, we will place significant emphasis on personal qualities and your commitment. If you believe you align with the above profile and wish to be part of our successful team, we eagerly await receiving your application!

description:
About Redeploy Run

At Redeploy Run, we specialize in platform engineering and operations, helping our customers simplify their infrastructure and speed up application delivery. Our mission is to make cloud adoption faster and easier.

Our 'Ready-to-Run' platform products, including Technology Platforms and Industry Cloud Platforms, let IT departments and developers manage infrastructure and governance with ease. Leveraging Infrastructure as Code, container-based services, CI/CD, and Kubernetes, and collaborating with cloud providers like Azure and AWS, we tackle complex problems, enhance our tools, and provide guidance to help customers get the most of their cloud platforms.

As a rapidly growing cloud company, we understand that our success depends on the talents we choose to surround ourselves with. Now we are looking for both senior and junior Network Security Engineers who want to be a part of our continued success story. Maybe it's you?

About the role

As Network Security Engineer, you’ll join our Operations team who has a responsibility for ensuring the security and operations of our diverse customers’ network infrastructures across cloud environments (Azure and AWS) and on-premises systems.

In this role, your focus will be on operations and to implement, manage, and maintain network security measures for multiple customers using Fortigate and Checkpoint solutions. Some of your tasks will amongst others be:

Designing and managing security protocols and policies for cloud environments.
Securing on-premises infrastructures, including firewalls and VPNs.
Monitoring network traffic for unusual activities, analyzing security threats, and responding to incidents.
Configuring and managing security settings, firewall rules, and VPN connections to ensure optimal performance and security.
Documenting security configurations, policies, and incidents as well as preparing reports for customers and internal use.
Diagnosing and resolving network security issues for our customers and providing advice and expertise to resolve any related technical problems.
Staying updated with the latest security trends, threats and technologies.

We provide our customers 24/7 support for urgent network security issues and incidents, and you will be part of an on-call rotation scheme and offered extra compensation for your efforts.

Who are you?

We believe you have a keen interest for networking, security and cloud and that you enjoy creating value and solving problems for clients. You are a strong believer in automation, making things faster and have a willingness to continuously learn and adapt to new technologies and security challenges.

We are looking for several new colleagues to join us - either you are senior with several years commercial experience in the field and are searching for your next challenge, or you just started your career in networking and security and are looking for a place where you can learn the ins and outs of the field by experienced professionals.

Other than that, we see that you come with following experiences:

Experience as a Network Security Engineer, with expertise in Fortigate and Checkpoint products.
Strong knowledge of network protocols, firewall management.
Experience with cloud networking and security in Azure and AWS environments.
Familiarity with security best practices, compliance standards, and risk management.
Experience in automation and DevOps practices.
Experience and knowledge of Terraform, Go, Python, Bash, Powershell, or similar to support automation.

(For juniors we see that you have an education in related field, as well as basic understanding of the mentioned experiences above).

And if you come with below experiences, we see it as a great advantage

Relevant certifications such as Fortinet NSE, or Checkpoint CCS(X)

What we offer

Being a member of Redeploy means you have the drive and desire to be the best and work smarter than the rest. We enjoy creative freedom with our projects, benefit from great work/life balance, and thrive in a company culture that is both collaborative and supportive. Everything we do at Redeploy is centered around the simple yet effective idea that we all chip in to ensure our success.

Want to learn more about our benefits package? Find more info here

Location

Our office is located in central Stockholm at Torsgatan 4. As we encourage a mix of in-person and remote work to foster innovation and support work-life balance (and like to have fun together), we see that you are based in commuting distance to our office location.

Ready to join the team?

We hope that we have sparked your interest and that you are curious to know more about the role and us at Redeploy.

We are constantly recruiting, so submit your application as soon as you can by hitting the apply button. For any specific questions about the position, reach out to Head of Redeploy Run Jonas Erikson - Jonas.Erikson@Redeploy.com.

We look forward hearing from you!

description:
We in Regent's business area Quality, which focuses on test, automation and DevOps, need to grow and are now looking for you who are passionate about QA, coding, CI/CD and testing strategies. You want to take the team's QA methodology to new heights. As a person, we see that you are supportive and believe that we perform better together!

Tasks

As a consultant with us, you will mainly work in a development team at one of our customers. The assignments vary with everything from setting up test automation strategies and frameworks to pure test development.

In the Quality team, you will have the opportunity to exchange experiences with and to get help from a bunch of test, deploy and DevOps enthusiasts.

About you

You have a natural drive and a strong interest in development and test

You like to share your knowledge

You are accurate, responsible and quality-conscious

You have several years of experience in most of the following techniques:

JavaScript, Java, C# or Python
Playwright, Cypress and/or Selenium
API testing
SQL
Build and deploy tools, e.g. Jenkins, TeamCity, Octopus
Continuous Integration, Delivery and Deployment
Source code management and versioning
Container platforms
Mocking services

About Regent

As a consultant at Regent, you get a secure job with good benefits in an entrepreneur-driven consulting company that safeguards the individual's development. We can prove this by being named Sweden's, even Europe's best workplace by the organization Great Place to Work for 2 years in a row.

description:
Tavana Tech is growing, and we are now looking for a DevOps Engineer for our exciting customers. Would you like to be a part of our development teams, consisting of a highly inclusive mix of skilled Frontend-and Backend developer, DevOps Engineers, iOS/Android developers and Cloud Architects from all over the world? Also, get the opportunity to be led by our dedicated management team who will guide you forward in your career?

We think our new colleague has:
• 5+ years experience of software development
• Experience within CI/CD and Microservices
• Work experience with Docker/Kubernetes
• Cloud experience (AWS or Azure)

Meritorious if you have experience/knowledge within:
• Scripting languages such as Python, Java, Bash or Go
• Git/Jenkins/Gerrit

We offer:
- National and International opportunities – A wide range of assignments both locally and nationally.
- Individual education budget – For further personal development
- Work life balance
- Other benefits regarding wellness, health care and pension
- Relocation package

Every employee is equally important to our company growth and success, and therefore we value individual feedback and work actively with personal development.

Sounds interesting?
Then we welcome you to apply to us as soon as possible as we handle applications on an ongoing basis. Send us your CV today via "Send application".

If you have questions regarding the position, who Tavana is or the consulting role, you are welcome to send an email to info@tavana.se

We look forward to receiving your application

description:
Recommit is growing and now we are looking for full-stack system developers within C# .Net who want to work as a consultant in a smaller company with growth ambitions. You work individually, are innovative and have the ability to develop useful solutions that contribute to business benefit. You are used to teamwork and familiar with agile development.

To fit in with us you have:

At least 8 years of experience in modern software development
At least 4 years of documented experience in web development.
At least 5 years of experience in Javascript/TypeScript, Node, CSS, HTML, Razor,
Excellent programming skills in C# (.NET Framework, .NET Core, .NET 7, MVC.Good)
In-depth knowledge of automated build and deployment environments
Proficiency in front-end frameworks like React, Blazor or Angular
Solid knowledge of deploying cloud services in Azure and Azure DevOps CI/CD
Understanding of container technology, for example Docker and Kubernetes.

It would be a plus if you have:

Experience using automated unit tests in development.
Worked with version control systems like Git.
Experience in Microservice architecture.
Experience in other languages like Java, Go, SQL, Python, Django, Spark, Scala.
Knowledge of other cloud services like AWS or GCP.
Infrastructure as Code (for example Bicep, Pulumi, or Terraform)
Exposure to PowerShell scripting
General understanding of REST APIs
Experience working in agile.

Above all, you are curious, responsible, flexible, and aspiring to develop innovative products and services.

Perks and Benefits

Competitive Salary
Pension plan
Health and other insurance
Gym, sports & health benefit
Yearly conferences (often abroad)
Full relocation support (work permit fast track, flight ticket, help with finding apartment/housing, bank account, Swedish SSN etc)
Hybrid/remote work

About Recommit:

We have three key words - Care, Share and Commit - something that defines how we are in our daily work, in the meeting with our customers and towards each other

Recommit offers a foundation for our co-workers to enhance their technical skills within IT. We strongly believe in knowledge sharing and are always passionate to learn from each other

Our employees consist of senior technology developers as well as young talents that disrupt with new ideas for innovations and opportunities. We know that the best teams consist of a mixed group of individuals

We endorse cultural diversity and have long experience in relocating new coworkers to our company and country. Recommit is certified by the Swedish Migration Agency and we can in short period of time handle the process of a valid work permit. We also try to help as much as possible in all aspects when in come to integrate to Sweden and the Swedish society .

Recommit AB was founded in 2010 and our office is located in central Stockholm

Application:

Does this sound like something for you? Apply today and meet us for a first Teams meeting. If you have any questions, please contact our consultant manager Jonas Falkowski Källman at jonas.kallman@recommit.se, or +46733113114

We are looking forward to your application!

description:
We need backend developers! Join our fast growing AI-based analytics and personalization venturebacked start-up.

ABOUT THE JOB

At Sift Lab our vision is to give all retailers the ability to leverage their data, and turn it into meaningful actions to improve customer experience and ROI. We have 40+ customers in the Nordics on our Saas platform, such as Nordic Nest, Byggmax, Caia Cosmetics, Bokus and Apohem. You will be part of a creative, ambitious, and fun team where science meets business.

As a data engineer in Infobaleen, you will design and develop data systems and machine learning pipelines. The data-centric platform consists of a data ingestion database, a machine-learning engine, and a dashboard engine. You will be responsible for helping our customer success team master all components and make crucial decisions when deciding which requested features we should prioritize. In addition, you will provide technical leadership and a deep understanding of data modeling. We work from Stockholm, Gothenburg and Umeå.

OUR TECH

We are a tech-agnostic company and have built our service using a wide range of technologies. The core application is built in Go. Supporting tools depend on Rust, Python, Tensorflow, and ClickHouse. We orchestrate and deploy everything with Docker and Kubernetes on Google Cloud Platform.

RESPONSIBILITIES

Be accountable for all aspects of your work, from research and analysis to testing, deployment, and operating the application in production.
Design, develop, and support Infobaleen's data-centric platform for modeling and reporting systems to solve business problems
Help our customer success team master the platform to meet business objectives.
Work closely with analysts to productionalize various machine learning models using data processing pipelines.

QUALIFICATIONS

Background in Computer Science, Engineering, or a related technical field.
Not less than 3-5 years of documented experience with at least one general-purpose programming language, strong preference Go.
Experience writing and maintaining ETLs that operate on a variety of structured and unstructured sources.
Experience with databases. We build and consume SQL solutions for both OLAP and OLTP systems.
Comprehensive understanding of data structures and algorithms
Being able to work in the Stockholm / Gothenburg office at least 3-4 days a week. 100% remote not possible.

description:
OFFER

Net Insight is a pioneering technology company that powers large-scale live broadcast events, connecting millions of viewers globally. Since 2021, they have established a rapidly expanding solution area focused on Synchronization. Leveraging their patented TV distribution synchronization technology, the Zyntai product portfolio is designed for nationwide 5G and power networks. We are now looking for an experienced C++ developer to join them!

Some of the benefits of working at Net Insight:

A world leader in media networks and resource optimization with a strong focus on innovation
Working with the latest tools in a very technologically advanced environment
Open and flat organization and good work culture with a lot of teamwork
Family-friendly company and a great understanding of pick-up/drop-off
Flexible working hours. You mainly report to your team
Unusually low turnover - High employee satisfaction!

THE PRODUCT AREA
5G Synchronization offers solutions to enable faster and more secure 5G rollouts. The core functionality is to distribute time over networks, GNSS independent, and with extremely high accuracy. The solution consists of new purpose-built hardware, advanced software-based automation algorithms, and a cloud-based management system. All are built with modern architecture and technologies.

The Synchronization solution is already making success for 5G worldwide and so far; Net Insight has established collaborations with large telecom operators in Europe and North America and over 20 nationwide TV networks.

For more info about the product, visit: https://netinsight.net/5g-sync

THE ROLE AND TEAMS
In this role, you will work in a smaller team of four to six other senior developers to further develop and improve Net Insight's unique solution using the latest C++ library. Given your experience and interest, there are openings in their two teams;

The Application team builds the application software and focuses on their algorithms for time synchronization. It is about using different time sources (atomic clock, PPS, GNSS, PPT, measurement of round trip times in the network) to be able to calculate the time at the nanosecond level in their nodes. If you have experience and/or interest in working with algorithm development and a mathematical background this is a good match.

The platform team works with the development of middleware, installation handling, monitoring, remote access, node control, and internal communication. They work with the layer between the FPGA and the application software and build in Linux (Yocto), device drivers, etc.

Some short notes from the teams:

We work with precise networked time synchronization. Think NTP, but four orders of magnitude better.
We use C++ 20 and Python for various tasks like test execution and glue scripts.
We take code review very seriously, not only to catch bugs but most importantly to share knowledge within the team. We sometimes do pair programming.
Interacting with other teams and team members is crucial for success.

YOUR PROFILE
Given smaller and self-autonomous teams there is a demand and wish that you thrive working in a more flexible/entrepreneurial way of working. This for example means a high degree of independence and initiative.

We think you are an experienced and social person who is used to working in close collaboration with other developers in agile teams; from system architecture, specification, and implementation of algorithms and functions to testing and verification. Even though you are a skilled engineer you still have a curiosity to learn and evolve but also share your expertise with others.

Seen to the technical elements, you need to have:

Good knowledge of modern C ++ (14, 17, 20) with standard libraries
Development of Linux applications
Solid knowledge and experience from TCP/IP and Network Communication

Good knowledge of Linux and systems with real-time requirement
Agile working methods such as scrum, TDD, and continuous integration

It is an advantage if you have experience in some of the following:

MPC, Model predictive control
Kalman filter
PI/PID Controller
Experience in cloud applications and cybernetics
Graph theory
Signal processing
Statistics
Optimization (in the mathematical sense)
Automatic control
Basic cryptography (TLS certs, AES)

ABOUT NET INSIGHT
Net Insight is a global leader in media networks, resource optimization, and streaming solutions. With more than 25 years of experience, Net Insight is a trusted and important partner and a leading force in the media tech industry in creating a better media experience. More than 500 world-class customers run mission-critical media services using Net Insight’s solutions in more than 70 countries worldwide.

Net Insight is powering the evolving media business in a connected world where technology enables seamless meetings between producers, distributors, and consumers of content – regardless of geographical location, technical resources, or distribution network. With its deep market knowledge and insight, genuine customer focus, and world-leading innovative technology, Net Insight makes it easier to create and deliver better content more reliably and effectively. Net Insight is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm.

For more info, visit https://netinsight.net/

ABOUT PINETREE

At Pinetree, we have a vision and mission to differentiate ourselves from the crowd and are Sweden's contenders in talent search and matching.

By working as an agency, the value to you as an employee is that we have a wide network of partner companies that we continuously ensure high-quality standards.

This recruitment is direct employment at Net Insight AB and all applications, questions, administration, and recruitment processes are managed by Pinetree AB.

It is about using different time sources (atomic clock, PPS, GNSS, PPT, measurement of round trip times in the network) to be able to calculate the time at the nanosecond level in their nodes. If you have experience and/or interest in working with algorithm development and a mathematical background this is a good match.

The platform team works with the development of middleware, installation handling, monitoring, remote access, node control, and internal communication. They work with the layer between the FPGA and the application software and build in Linux (Yocto), device drivers, etc.


Some short notes from the teams:


  • We work with precise networked time synchronization. Think NTP, but four orders of magnitude better.
  • We use C++ 20 and Python for various tasks like test execution and glue scripts.
  • We take code review very seriously, not only to catch bugs but most importantly to share knowledge within the team. We sometimes do pair programming.
  • Interacting with other teams and team members is crucial for success.


YOUR PROFILE
Given smaller and self-autonomous teams there is a demand and wish that you thrive working in a more flexible/entrepreneurial way of working. This for example means a high degree of independence and initiative.

We think you are an experienced and social person who is used to working in close collaboration with other developers in agile teams; from system architecture, specification, and implementation of algorithms and functions to testing and verification. Even though you are a skilled engineer you still have a curiosity to learn and evolve but also share your expertise with others.

Seen to the technical elements, you need to have:


  • Good knowledge of modern C ++ (14, 17, 20) with standard libraries
  • Development of Linux applications
  • Solid knowledge and experience from TCP/IP and Network Communication
  • Good knowledge of Linux and systems with real-time requirement
  • Agile working methods such as scrum, TDD, and continuous integration

It is an advantage if you have experience in some of the following:

  • MPC, Model predictive control
  • Kalman filter
  • PI/PID Controller
  • Experience in cloud applications and cybernetics
  • Graph theory
  • Signal processing
  • Statistics
  • Optimization (in the mathematical sense)
  • Automatic control
  • Basic cryptography (TLS certs, AES)


ABOUT NET INSIGHT
Net Insight is a global leader in media networks, resource optimization, and streaming solutions. With more than 25 years of experience, Net Insight is a trusted and important partner and a leading force in the media tech industry in creating a better media experience. More than 500 world-class customers run mission-critical media services using Net Insight’s solutions in more than 70 countries worldwide.

Net Insight is powering the evolving media business in a connected world where technology enables seamless meetings between producers, distributors, and consumers of content – regardless of geographical location, technical resources, or distribution network. With its deep market knowledge and insight, genuine customer focus, and world-leading innovative technology, Net Insight makes it easier to create and deliver better content more reliably and effectively. Net Insight is listed on Nasdaq Stockholm.

For more info, visit https://netinsight.net/

ABOUT PINETREE


At Pinetree, we have a vision and mission to differentiate ourselves from the crowd and are Sweden's contenders in talent search and matching.

By working as an agency, the value to you as an employee is that we have a wide network of partner companies that we continuously ensure high-quality standards.

This recruitment is direct employment at Net Insight AB and all applications, questions, administration, and recruitment processes are managed by Pinetree AB.
positionName: Sr C++ Engineer to Net Insight's 5G Sync solution

description:
Are you tired of working in monotonous environments? Seeking to level up with cutting-edge technologies and top-tier enterprises? Look no further! SwedQ puts its people first, prioritizing your career journey. We're all ears when it comes to your career aspirations. Want AWS certification? We've got you. Want to lead a team? Do it. Dreaming of becoming an Architect? Let's make it happen together by carving out a role that aligns with your goals.

SwedQ is a consulting company that works towards becoming the first choice within development and digitalization through delivering tangible results based on our clients conditions and business objectives. How do we do it? By harnessing our unparalleled Know-how, extensive experience, and laser-focused competence. We're the go-to team for turning your wildest digital dreams into a reality.

What's in it for you?

At SwedQ, we're looking for a Software engineer who's always pushing the envelope. We're not just offering a job—we're opening up a world of opportunity. Get ready to tackle the latest and greatest tech, tackle unique challenges every single day, and experience a diverse array of environments. And get this: we're not waiting for an assignment to land on our lap. We're designing the role together with you, based on your experience and passions. Our assignments span across various industries, but our IT focus is razor-sharp. Our dynamic consultants are currently rocking out everything from implementing new cloud architectures to setting up back-end systems for self-driving vehicles. Are you ready to join the elite SwedQ crew and take on the digital world?

Our clients

We're partnering with fintech upstarts and big-name giants alike. Our talented consultants are currently flexing their skills at titans like Spotify, H&M, Scania, Ericsson, Schibsted — among many others. The digital world is our playground, and we're constantly on the hunt for new partners to push the boundaries of innovation.

You will bring:

Minimum 7 years of experience working as as Software engineer
Strong analytical / problem solving skills
Good communicator
Fluent in both English
Swedish is meritorious
Experience with cloud solutions like Azure, AWS, GCP
Good knowledge of at least one programming language, Java, Python, Node.js, Scala, Golang, C# etc.
Experience with modern way of working: Microservices, serverless frameworks, Containerisation (Docker and orchestration with Kubernetes)
Understanding of different database structures, NoSQL, SQL, MongoDB etc.

Note that you do not need to fill all of the above requirements, we will be taking into account, other aspects of your experience as well!

SwedQ culture

The culture is very very important to us. We're all about smashing hierarchies, embracing independence and accountability, and driving value-creating work—all while having a blast. Diversity and equal opportunity aren't just buzzwords to us—they're baked into our DNA. So go ahead, come to the office in flip-flops or high heels, as long as you're comfortable and true to yourself. And when it comes to blowing off steam, we take fun seriously. From epic football tourneys to unforgettable trips and dinners, we're all about creating memories that last a lifetime.

Perks & Benefits

Competitive salary
Flexible working hours
Budget to spend on health and gym
Generous developers budget
Monthly payments into you additional pension fund
Private health insurance
Private health care
Office in the City – Stone's throw from public transport and lunch restaurants
Support for open source projects and community engagements
Developers time, to use during work hours for your personal growth
Kick-ass colleagues and mentors at every corner

Other information about the employment

Start - Flexible starting date

Employment - Full time
Location - Stockholm

description:
As a Cloud Engineer at Geins, you will be responsible for ensuring the smooth and efficient operation of our cloud-based infrastructure, with a focus on Azure. You will work closely with our development team to deploy and manage code, automate processes, monitor performance, and troubleshoot issues as they arise.

Responsibilities:
Design, deploy, and manage infrastructure on Azure, including VMs, storage, networking, and security

Build and maintain CI/CD pipelines.
Develop and implement automation scripts using PowerShell, Python or other scripting languages
Monitor system performance and troubleshoot issues in real-time
Work with developers to ensure code is properly deployed and configured on production environments
Implement best practices for security, backup, and disaster recovery
Stay up-to-date with emerging trends and technologies in cloud computing and Cloud

Job Instructions:
You will be responsible for designing, building and maintaining the infrastructure that supports the development, testing, and deployment of our products and services. Below are the job instructions for your role:

Design and implement infrastructure:
Design and implement infrastructure that supports the development, testing, and deployment of our products and services. Use modern infrastructure technologies such as cloud computing, containers, and automation tools to build infrastructure that is scalable, reliable, and efficient.

Automate infrastructure processes:
Automate infrastructure processes such as deployment, monitoring, and scaling to reduce manual effort and increase efficiency. Use automation tools such as Ansible, Chef, and Puppet to automate infrastructure processes, and develop custom scripts and tools as needed.

Ensure continuous integration and delivery:
Ensure continuous integration and delivery of our products and services, enabling fast and frequent releases. Use continuous integration and delivery tools such as Jenkins, Travis CI, and CircleCI to automate build, test, and deployment processes.

Implement and maintain monitoring systems:
Implement and maintain monitoring systems to ensure that our infrastructure and services are performing as expected. Use monitoring tools such as Nagios, New Relic, and Datadog to monitor infrastructure and application performance, and develop custom scripts and tools as needed.

Ensure security and compliance:
Ensure that our infrastructure and services are secure and compliant with industry and regulatory standards. Use security and compliance tools and frameworks to ensure that our infrastructure and services meet security and compliance requirements.

Collaborate with development and operations teams:
Collaborate with development and operations teams to ensure that infrastructure meets their needs and supports their goals. Work closely with the development team to understand their requirements for infrastructure, and with the operations team to ensure that infrastructure is reliable and efficient.

Stay up to date with Cloud trends:
Stay up to date with Cloud trends and best practices, and bring this knowledge to bear in the development and maintenance of our infrastructure. Use this knowledge to ensure that we are delivering infrastructure that is scalable, reliable, and efficient.

Qualifications:

3+ years of experience in Cloud, with a focus on Azure, AWS or Google.
Experience deploying and managing infrastructure on Azure, including VMs, storage, networking, and security
Proficiency in Python, PowerShell or other scripting languages
Experience building and maintaining CI/CD pipelines
Knowledge of containerization and orchestration tools like Docker and Kubernetes
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills
Excellent communication and collaboration skills
Primary Personal Traits:
Problem-solving Skills, The cloud infrastructure landscape is complex and ever-evolving. The ideal candidate should be adept at identifying issues and coming up with efficient solutions.
Attention to Detail, Overseeing cloud infrastructure requires meticulousness. A small oversight can lead to significant security vulnerabilities or system downtimes.
Adaptability, The world of cloud computing is dynamic. New technologies, tools, and best practices emerge frequently. The candidate should be adaptable and willing to learn and evolve with the industry.
Strong Communication Skills, They will need to communicate technical details to non-technical stakeholders and collaborate with different teams. Clear communication is crucial.
Proactiveness, Instead of just reacting to issues, the ideal candidate should be proactive in identifying potential challenges and addressing them before they escalate.
Integrity and Trustworthiness, Given that they'll be responsible for a critical aspect of the company, it's essential that they are trustworthy and handle data and resources with integrity.
Stress Management, Cloud infrastructure roles can sometimes be high-pressure, especially during outages or security breaches. The ability to stay calm and think clearly under pressure is invaluable.
Customer-centric Mindset, Ultimately, the infrastructure is there to support the product and the customers. A mindset that prioritizes customer experience, uptime, and data security is crucial.
Continuous Learning, The cloud domain is vast, with AWS, Azure, Google Cloud, and other providers continuously rolling out new services and features. A passion for continuous learning and staying updated is essential.
Strategic Thinking, Beyond the day-to-day, the candidate should be able to think strategically about the company's infrastructure needs, considering growth, scalability, and cost optimization.
Innovation, As the SaaS landscape becomes more competitive, having someone who can leverage the latest cloud technologies to give the company an edge can be a significant advantage.

description:
Full stack developer

Vizzit develops and markets tools for web analytics and content maintenance, with usability and simplicity as our focus. We are currently looking for a full stack developer who wants to contribute to our vision of an effective and intuitive toolset suite!

A typical week at Vizzit as a full stack developer looks something like this:

You’re sitting at your desk in our bright offices in the middle of Stockholm, together with the rest of the development team. The week begins with a meeting regarding project status, the coming sprint, and the team's current goals. During the day you also participate in a meeting with our system designer and your project lead. Together, you ensure that design and backend can deliver on project goals, while also giving you the chance to influence both design and development processes.

Throughout the week you switch effortlessly between backend and frontend, working with CSS, JavaScript, SQL, and Python 3 in a Linux environment. You report directly to the project lead, and can turn to both the project lead and the rest of the development team if you need support or feedback.

Your qualifications

We maintain a high code standard in our projects, so it’s very important to us that all our applicants do the same. You’re good at writing flexible code, and avoid all forms of hard coding. You are also used to commenting and documenting your code in a way that makes it easy for your colleagues to read and understand.

To fulfil the requirements of working as a full stack developer at Vizzit, you also need to:

Have at least 1 year of experience working full-time as a full stack developer
Master the following languages:
HTML5
CSS
JavaScript
SQL
Python 3
Master Linux services (systemd)
Master DVCS (Git)

Experience using Photoshop/GIMP is considered a merit, but is not required.

What we offer

We offer all our employees a work environment where you’re given the chance to use your creativity and knowledge to their fullest potential. You not only develop programs and services, but also have the ability to influence their design, content, and functionality. All of this, you do as part of a social and welcoming development team, where you’re given room to both be yourself and share your experiences with others.

We also offer regular team building exercises and social events, and opportunities for training and developing your skillset. Naturally, we also provide a generous allowance for exercise and wellness activities.

Questions and how to apply

Want to apply for the position, or hear more about what we have to offer? Send your questions or CV and cover letter to ulf.risberg@vizzit.se, or call us at +468 545 888 60. If you email us, please write “Full stack developer” on the subject line.

We interview applicants continuously, so send us your application today!

Employment type: Full time (100 %)

Salary: Fixed

We look forward to reading your application!

Mvh,
Vizzit
Make your website happy

description:
Are you looking for a unique career opportunity? We are a Stockholm based technology developer looking for full stack developers with hands on experience in Python and AngularJS.

We look for people that like to work in a fast-paced, dynamic environment.

Your Profile

We have multiple positions available:

Software Architect
Team leadership skills
At least 5 years professional experience with Python
Knowledge in software design and application development
Experience with automation in deployments (CI)

Senior Developer
At least 4 years professional experience with Python
Experience working with databases and datasets (MySQL)
Verifiable experience with Angular 2/4 (please supply examples)
Solid understanding of source control and cloud environments

Full stack Developer
At least 3 years professional experience with Python
Entry level experience with Angular 2/4

About you

We are hiring dynamic individuals - always looking to improve themselves and their projects. As we are developing applications that are already live in some stage - experience with client interaction will be a plus.

Supplemental technologies that are beneficial to us are: Git, Java, Ansible, NoSQL database, BigData algorithms and data manipulation, HA application design, BI data handling, ElasticSearch, Agile task management methodology, web scraping, GCP and Super Mario Kart.

About us

alaTest was founded in 2005 as the pioneer of the reviews and product aggregation sector. We collect, structure, match, analyse, present and syndicate product and review data, globally.

Our team is diverse, currently hailing from every continent except Antarctica. We welcome all nationalities and backgrounds - provided that you are legally employable in Sweden.
Our company language is English.

Please send your CV and cover letter to jobs[at]alatest[dot]com.
Note: We require a small coding challenge to be completed by all applicants that pass the first review round.

description:
Who we are

Mirado Consulting is not your average consulting firm. We pride ourselves on working to be the top tech consulting firm in Stockholm. A firm that attracts, develops, excites and retains outstanding people. Our formula is simple, hire pure talents that are insanely passionate about what they do and watch the magic happen. Since our inception in mid 2015, we have grown to 40 top talents, that have a phenomenal impact on our customers’ products and businesses on a daily basis

What makes us different to other consultancies?

Unlike your usual consultancy, we put our Engineers first; do you wish you had more control over the technology and projects you are working on?

We will ask you what you love doing in terms of technologies and products and then find a project that will thrill you.

What you’ll do

You will be working with leading tech companies in Stockholm such as Spotify, King, Klarna, Dice, iZettle, Doktor24 and many more! You will also benefit from Mirado’s extraordinary culture and Learning and Development platform.

Our assignments are longer than usual, lasting 1 to 2 years depending on the project and how you feel about it. It is important for us to match you to assignments that you are passionate about and where you can feel challenged.

Who you are
We love Passionate people - You have a great attitude, you have high energy, you have a hunger to learn and you love to celebrate
We love Humble people - You treat people with respect independent of their position and you take time to help your colleagues
We love High Performers - You run the extra mile and stand responsible for your end results, you keep your deadlines
We love people that take Ownership - You are proactive and self-motivated, you are self-improving, you treat root causes instead of symptoms, you act as a leader
We love Team players - You take time to listen to your colleagues to get a better understanding, you invite other in your work, you communicate in a good manner, you work to improve transparency
Ideal skills & experience
Demonstrable knowledge in distributed backend development, preferably with Java, Node, Python, Go or C#
The ability to design, develop and deploy backend services focusing on high availability, low latency and scalability
Be able to reason about CAP for given use cases
The ability to operate at a strategic level within the organisation to address scalability issues
Experience of working in hi-transactional environments, with an understanding of how physical resources i.e i/o, cpu memory affects software design
Hands-on experience in developing microservices
Be able to maintain and improve our data pipelines
Best practices and patterns for modern API design
Have a good understanding of internet protocols i.e UDP, TCP, HTTP
The ability to undertake devops tasks
Examples of technologies we use

AWS, Azure, GCP
MySQL, Postgres, Cassandra, Redis, Memcached, MongoDB, Elasticsearch
Kafka, ActiveMQ, PubSub, Kinesis
Springboot, Vert.x, Jersey, Micronaut
GRPC
Reactive, functional, actor programming models
Terraform, Cloudformation, Kubernetes

Are some of this ️ new to you? - No problem! We're all about learning and you'll join a supportive environment.

We also offer a best-in-class salary, benefits to support a good work-life balance, share options and 25-30 days paid leave (dependant on seniority level).

At Mirado we are proud to nurture a workplace free from discrimination. We truly believe that diversity of experience, perspectives, and background will lead to a better environment for our employees and a better product for our users. Suitable candidates with equivalent qualifications and more or less experience can and should apply. descriptionHTML:
Who we are

Mirado Consulting is not your average consulting firm. We pride ourselves on working to be the top tech consulting firm in Stockholm. A firm that attracts, develops, excites and retains outstanding people. Our formula is simple, hire pure talents that are insanely passionate about what they do and watch the magic happen. Since our inception in mid 2015, we have grown to 40 top talents, that have a phenomenal impact on our customers’ products and businesses on a daily basis

What makes us different to other consultancies?

Unlike your usual consultancy, we put our Engineers first; do you wish you had more control over the technology and projects you are working on?

We will ask you what you love doing in terms of technologies and products and then find a project that will thrill you.

What you’ll do

You will be working with leading tech companies in Stockholm such as Spotify, King, Klarna, Dice, iZettle, Doktor24 and many more! You will also benefit from Mirado’s extraordinary culture and Learning and Development platform.

Our assignments are longer than usual, lasting 1 to 2 years depending on the project and how you feel about it. It is important for us to match you to assignments that you are passionate about and where you can feel challenged.

Who you are

  • We love Passionate people - You have a great attitude, you have high energy, you have a hunger to learn and you love to celebrate
  • We love Humble people - You treat people with respect independent of their position and you take time to help your colleagues
  • We love High Performers - You run the extra mile and stand responsible for your end results, you keep your deadlines
  • We love people that take Ownership - You are proactive and self-motivated, you are self-improving, you treat root causes instead of symptoms, you act as a leader
  • We love Team players - You take time to listen to your colleagues to get a better understanding, you invite other in your work, you communicate in a good manner, you work to improve transparency

Ideal skills & experience

  • Demonstrable knowledge in distributed backend development, preferably with Java, Node, Python, Go or C#
  • The ability to design, develop and deploy backend services focusing on high availability, low latency and scalability
  • Be able to reason about CAP for given use cases
  • The ability to operate at a strategic level within the organisation to address scalability issues
  • Experience of working in hi-transactional environments, with an understanding of how physical resources i.e i/o, cpu memory affects software design
  • Hands-on experience in developing microservices
  • Be able to maintain and improve our data pipelines
  • Best practices and patterns for modern API design
  • Have a good understanding of internet protocols i.e UDP, TCP, HTTP
  • The ability to undertake devops tasks

Examples of technologies we use


  • AWS, Azure, GCP
  • MySQL, Postgres, Cassandra, Redis, Memcached, MongoDB, Elasticsearch
  • Kafka, ActiveMQ, PubSub, Kinesis
  • Springboot, Vert.x, Jersey, Micronaut
  • GRPC
  • Reactive, functional, actor programming models
  • Terraform, Cloudformation, Kubernetes


Are some of this ️ new to you? - No problem! We're all about learning and you'll join a supportive environment.

We also offer a best-in-class salary, benefits to support a good work-life balance, share options and 25-30 days paid leave (dependant on seniority level).

At Mirado we are proud to nurture a workplace free from discrimination. We truly believe that diversity of experience, perspectives, and background will lead to a better environment for our employees and a better product for our users. Suitable candidates with equivalent qualifications and more or less experience can and should apply. We do not discriminate based on race, ethnicity, colour, ancestry, national origin, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, disability, veteran status, genetic information, marital status or any other legally protected status. We welcome all applicants and look forward to hearing from you!

description:
Profile

For our customer projects and incoming customer requisitions, we need to extend our team with several full-stack developers. A Full Stack developer at ICG is a technology and developer ninja. Flexibility when it comes to frameworks and different technology stacks, as we have different customers with diverse IT landscapes. However, it's important that the knowledge span from scalable backend services, running in containers or serverless, all the way to modern GUI design and full-stack security.

Skills

Extensive and practical knowledge in cloud computing
Modern application deployment based involving container technology, microservices, ServerLess, and more
Solid and extensive programming experience with several common languages (e.g. Java, C#, Python). In addition, other languages as Golang, or functional languages (e.g. Scala) are nice to have but not mandatory
Modern frontend frameworks for both web- and mobile applications
Extensive experience of common backend technologies
Experience from implementing CI/CD

What we offer you

We offer you a dedicated management team, with a solid engineering and software development background. We are all part of the delivery and still active as consultants. This means that we have a better understanding of both our customer's unique situation and your situation as an employed consultant. Basically, we are a company by knowledge workers for knowledge workers, built on a foundation of knowledge, empathy, sharing, and fun.

We expect all employees to be part of this culture.

- Willing to always learn something new and set knowledge into practice.

- Participation in our competence jam sessions, conferences, and trips.

- Willing to share, and spread positive energy.

About us

We help our customers modernize software application delivery to the cutting edge with Infrastructure as Code, containers, and private/public Cloud Computing.

description:
Are you tired of working in monotonous environments? Seeking to level up with cutting-edge technologies and top-tier enterprises? Look no further! SwedQ puts its people first, prioritizing your career journey. We're all ears when it comes to your career aspirations. Want AWS certification? We've got you. Want to lead a team? Do it. Dreaming of becoming an Architect? Let's make it happen together by carving out a role that aligns with your goals.

SwedQ is a consulting company that works towards becoming the first choice within development and digitalization through delivering tangible results based on our clients conditions and business objectives. How do we do it? By harnessing our unparalleled Know-how, extensive experience, and laser-focused competence. We're the go-to team for turning your wildest digital dreams into a reality.

What's in it for you?

At SwedQ, we're looking for a python developer who's always pushing the envelope. We're not just offering a job—we're opening up a world of opportunity. Get ready to tackle the latest and greatest tech, tackle unique challenges every single day, and experience a diverse array of environments. And get this: we're not waiting for an assignment to land on our lap. We're designing the role together with you, based on your experience and passions. Our assignments span across various industries, but our IT focus is razor-sharp. Our dynamic consultants are currently rocking out everything from implementing new cloud architectures to setting up back-end systems for self-driving vehicles. Are you ready to join the elite SwedQ crew and take on the digital world?

Our clients

We're partnering with fintech upstarts and big-name giants alike. Our talented consultants are currently flexing their skills at titans like Spotify, H&M, Scania, Ericsson, Schibsted — among many others. The digital world is our playground, and we're constantly on the hunt for new partners to push the boundaries of innovation.

You will bring:

Minimum 7 years of experience in Software engineering
Strong analytical / problem solving skills
Good communicator
Fluent in English
Swedish is meritorious
JavaScript (React, AngularJS or similar)
AWS, GCP, Azure
CI/CD - Jenkins, TeamCity, Octups deploy or similar
Architectures - Microservices, serverless, N-Tier, REST, SOAP, GraphQL
Other - Elasticserach. Dynamodb, Databases
Python (Django, Flask, Bottle or similar)
Different services within the cloud providers
Setting up deployment pipelines towards the cloud

SwedQ culture

The culture is very very important to us. We're all about smashing hierarchies, embracing independence and accountability, and driving value-creating work—all while having a blast. Diversity and equal opportunity aren't just buzzwords to us—they're baked into our DNA. So go ahead, come to the office in flip-flops or high heels, as long as you're comfortable and true to yourself. And when it comes to blowing off steam, we take fun seriously. From epic football tourneys to unforgettable trips and dinners, we're all about creating memories that last a lifetime.

Perks & Benefits

Competitive salary
Flexible working hours
Budget to spend on health and gym
Generous developers budget
Monthly payments into you additional pension fund
Private health insurance
Office in the City – Stone's throw from public transport and lunch restaurants
Support for open source projects and community engagements
Developers time, to use during work hours for your personal growth
Kick-ass colleagues and mentors at every corner

Other information about the employment

Start - Flexible starting date
Employment - Full time
Location - Stockholm

description:
As our Senior backend developer you will work remotely, or in one of our offices, together with our backend- and frontend team and support our RnD team in building a scalable cloud architecture for our patented people counter and customer experience management platform.

We at Indivd are working to solve the immense sustainability issues within physical retail. One of the biggest issues is that visitors' behaviors are necessary to provide insights into which products the physical retailers should design and, and distribute.

Simply put, we're using sensors and AI/Machine learning to learn about customers and their behavior in retail environments. We do this without invading anyone's privacy. It's like a sci fi movie, but in real life ;-)

In order to be able to build these insights, underlying customer data is required, which leads to major privacy issues. Our solution to this problem is a patented and marketing-leading anonymization method for image data which increases the ability to understand retail visitors while protecting customer privacy

Responsibilities:

Improving and building new version of our analytics platform, including:

Manage databases
Optimize computations
Health monitoring
Security analysis
APIs to customers
APIs to GPU clusters
Requirements:
Python
Django REST
PostgreSQL
Additional valuable experience:
Apache Airflow
Celery, Amazon AQS
Asyncio, aiohttp
Benefits:
Company laptop.
Freedom to work in an office or remotely.
Work together with some of the world's leading experts.
Solve problems for some of the best brands in the industry.

Adopt the latest tech stacks on the market

Design a revolutionary system

description:
Who we are

We are an early-stage startup hell-bent on improving the post-purchase experience in the e-commerce industry, starting with the biggest pain point: returns. We move fast and expect a lot because we're working on something that will truly make the e-commerce industry more sustainable, financially and environmentally. With COVID19 crisis accelerating the migration from offline to online, together with booming acquisition costs, increasing customer loyalty has become paramount. At the same time, with increasing online sales, retailers suffer from booming returns.

yayloh is a SaaS solution for e-commerce retailers, which digitalizes and automates the return process and unleashes the potential of return data. yayloh will increase customer satisfaction and loyalty while improving retailers profitability and reducing environmental impact. Using data analytics and applied machine learning, yayloh allows e-commerce retailers to understand their customers needs on an advanced level. yayloh is backed by the early-stage VC Antler. Also worth mentioning, we have happy customers and a growing pipeline in different countries!

What we’re looking for

We welcome students who are looking for a 3 to 6 months internship in software development. You will be involved in everything from new feature development, bug solving and releasing new versions to our production environment. You will also interact with our UI/UX team and frontend developers. This will enable you to understand everything which goes into building our saas solution.

You will also be involved in requirement gathering and interact with our customers when it comes to enhancements and bug-fixing.

Requirements

Internship should be part of your coursework

Web programming knowledge - preferably python and react.js

Understanding of how websites work end-to-end

Sql skills

Bonus Skills

Knowledge with HTML / CSS / Javascript

What we offer?

Being part of a very early stage start-up where we expect you to be independent, creative, free thinking. We are two co-founders with a strong skillset combination, with respective deep experience in retail and software development.

The dream team

We are international from day-one with a co-founding team from France and India and English is the company language so everyone feels included. Our first market is the Nordics but we dream big and are building a global company.

We’re problem-solvers, disruptors and early-adopters so we don’t see failures but learning opportunities. Innovation is at the heart of everything we do and we believe anything is possible when you can think freely, without boundaries nor pre-set frameworks.

We don’t count hours and you can walk your dog 10 times a day, we don't judge. What we will care about is how your contribution improves our product!

How to apply?

Send Resume and short intro email to nikhil@yayloh.com
